dentist_ca1_cbf_01_01 = "",--The Golden Grin Casino is the largest casino in Vegas. Their hard currency securities rival that of small nations - and they keep it all on-site. Gangster founders had a healthy suspicion of banks. This will require a plan. Study your options, use your intel and carry out your plan with stringency.
dentist_ca1_cbf_01_02 = "",--The Golden Grin Casino has dominated the Strip since its founding. It was built on mobster money. Time to take some of that back. You will need a plan: Study the environment. Assess the variables. Consider your options, and then execute - without hesitation.
dentist_ca1_cbf_01_03 = "",--The Golden Grin Casino was founded on post-war wealth. The time has come to redistribute that wealth. Thorough planning is essential. Observe. Assess. Execute. I'd wish you luck, but luck has nothing to do with it.
dentist_ca1_cnc_01_01 = "",--The Golden Grin Casino: High stakes. High security. Large payday.
dentist_ca1_cnc_01_02 = "",--The level of security at a casino typically reflects the degree of wealth within. The Golden Grin Casino is the most secure casino on the Strip.
dentist_ca1_cnc_01_03 = "",--The Golden Grin Casino: Very wealthy. Very secure. Very soon emptied by you.
dentist_ca1_debrief_01_01 = "",--You have reaped the rewards of a well considered and deliberately executed plan - most impressive. I will contact you when I have further need of you.
dentist_ca1_debrief_01_02 = "",--You executed on your plan with ruthless efficiency. I am impressed. You will hear from me when I require your services again.
dentist_ca1_debrief_01_03 = "",--You benefited from a thoughtful plan. Your discipline impresses. Enjoy your PAYDAY. I will contact you when I require your expertise once again.
dentist_ca1_debrief_02_01 = "",--You have reaped the rewards of a well considered and deliberately executed plan - most impressive. I will contact you when I have further need of you.
dentist_ca1_debrief_02_02 = "",--You executed on your plan with ruthless efficiency. I am impressed. You will hear from me when I require your services again.
dentist_ca1_debrief_02_03 = "",--You benefited from a thoughtful plan. Your discipline impresses. Enjoy your payday. I will contact you when I require your expertise once again.
pln_ca1_brf_01_01 = "コイツはデカい仕事になるぞ。簡単に言えば、Golden Grinにはデカい金庫がある。それもBenevolent Bank並のがな。忍び込むにしろ、最初からドンパチやるにしろ、かなり厳しい仕事になるだろう。今回盗んでくるブツについてなんだが...The Dentistの野郎はハッキリとは伝えてきていないんだ。随分用心深そうに「アレを取ってきたら、それでお終いだ」、とだけいってたよ。まあ、なんにせよこの仕事を終えれば、依頼は全部奴のご希望通りに終わるわけだ、奴の本当の目的が何であれな。",--This is a big job. I'll talk you through it as we go, but the skinny is this: the Golden Grin has a big vault. Big. I mean Benevolent Bank big. Whether you sneak in, or go full assault, you're in for a tough time. $NL;$NL;The Dentist won't say what we're lifting out of there. Being very cagey about that. He just said that once we're done, we're done. The contract is fulfilled... whatever that means.
pln_ca1_intro_01_01 = "ここが Golden Grin Casinoだ。",--Here it is. The Golden Grin Casino.
pln_ca1_intro_01_02 = "オーケー、ギャンブラー共。博打といこうじゃないか。",--Okay gamblers. Let's get gambling.
pln_ca1_intro_01_03 = "パパは新しい靴が必要みたいだ",--Daddy needs a new pair of shoes.
pln_ca1_intro_02_01 = "ロックだぜ!",--Let's rock!
pln_ca1_intro_02_02 = "カッコよく参上!",--Arriving in style!
pln_ca1_intro_02_03 = "ゴールデングリン... バスト!",--Golden Grin, or bust!
pln_ca1_01_01 = "お前らは今市民に扮している。銃は無し、マスクも無い - 警備には気づかれないがな。準備ができたら装備を見つけろ。Michoがどこかにお前らの装備が入ったギターケースを置いてくれている。",--You're in civilian mode. No guns, no masks - invisible to security. When you're ready, find your gear. Micho the janitor left it in a guitar case somewhere.
pln_ca1_01_02 = "いいか、お前たちは今市民に扮しているんだ。銃もマスクも無いってことだが、怪しまれはしない。内通者のMichoがどこかに装備の入ったギターケースを置いておいてくれているぞ。",--Remember, you in civvie mode. That means no guns or masks. You're invisibles. Micho, our Inside Man here, left a guitar case with your gear somewhere.
pln_ca1_01_03 = "お前らは今市民に扮している。銃やマスクはどこかに隠してあるが、それを取るまでは警備に怪しまれないだろう。",--You're in civvie mode. Your guns and masks are stashed somewhere. Until you get them, you're invisible to security.
pln_ca1_02_01 = "オーケー、サツ共が向かってきてる。まず最初に、警備室でC4を探せ。",--OK, cops are inbound. First step, look for C4 in the guard room.
pln_ca1_02_02 = "よし、サツ共が来るまでそう長くない。警備室でC4を探せ。",--Okay, the Fed's won't be long, so time to hit it hard and fast. Find the C4 in the guard room.
pln_ca1_02_03 = "ぐずぐずするな。警察が向かってきてる。C4を探せ! 警備室にあるはずだ!",--We've got cops on the way, so don't dawdle. Find the C4! Check the guard room.
pln_ca1_03_01 = "OK、それじゃあここを爆破してみよう。リムジンにC4が入っている。いくぜ!",--OK, lets blow this place. C4's in the limo. Take it!
pln_ca1_03_02 = "リムジンに入っているそのC4をつかんでここを爆破してみよう。急げ! サツが来るぞ。",--Grab that C4 in the limo and let's blow this place. Hurry! Cops are coming.
pln_ca1_03_03 = "リムジンのC4を忘れるなよ。サツが乗り込んできている。急げ!",--Don't forget the C4 in the limo. Man, cops are close. Hurry!
pln_ca1_04_01 = "睡眠ガスもある。後で必要になるから回収しておけ。",--There's sleeping gas too. Grab it. You'll need it later.
pln_ca1_04_02 = "そこに睡眠ガスが入ってる。後回しにして忘れるなよ。",--Oh, put some sleeping gas in there too. Don't leave it behind.
pln_ca1_05_01 = "まず、警備を無効化するために、監視室と通気口でつながってる部屋を探す必要がある。建物の設計図を探せ。書庫の中にあるはずだ。",--Now, we gotta find out what room shares a vent with the security center. We'll use it to knock out the guards. First, get building blueprints. They should be inside the archives.
pln_ca1_05_02 = "次に、警備室に繋がってる通気口を探さなきゃいけない。建物の設計図を書庫で探すんだ。",--Next, we find the room whose vent connects with the security center. We can use that to knock out the guards with sleeping gas. So, we need blueprints. Check the archives.
pln_ca1_06_01 = "よし、今すぐスキャンして、俺にFaxで送ってくれ。通気口の位置を見つけるぞ。",--Great! Now find a scanner in IT. Fax me a copy of the blueprints. I'll find that vent.
pln_ca1_06_02 = "それだ。今すぐ俺にコピーを送ってくれ。通気口がどこにあるか探してやる。",--That's them. Now scan them in, and fax me a copy. I'll figure out the right vent.
pln_ca1_07_01 = "101号室だ!",--101!
pln_ca1_08_01 = "102号室だ!",--102!
pln_ca1_09_01 = "103号室だ!",--103!
pln_ca1_100_01 = "",--That's it... whatever it is! All right, the drop off is a storage room. Take that there and secure it.
pln_ca1_100_02 = "",--Now just grab that thing and get it out of there. It's what we came for.
pln_ca1_100_03 = "",--There's The Dentist's whatever. Haul it out of there and we are done with him.
pln_ca1_101_01 = "",--All right, we got what we came for. You can bail or go back, clean The Grin.
pln_ca1_101_02 = "",--That's The Dentists' loot saved. Bail now, or really show The Grin how we treat Vegas DC-style.
pln_ca1_101_03 = "",--We can now redeem the Dentists' contract. You can bounce, or treat Vegas to a Payday crew party and loot the place.
pln_ca1_102_01 = "",--Forget the alarms, gang, we're nearly done. Grab The Dentist's loot, and get it out of there.
pln_ca1_102_02 = "",--Screw the alarms, guys. Just grab The Dentists' loot and we can be done.
pln_ca1_103_01 = "",--Hustle it. Get to armory in the guards locker room! We need that C4!
pln_ca1_103_02 = "",--Move it, guys. Find the locker room, and we find the armory.
pln_ca1_103_03 = "",--Come on, gang. Get to the locker room armory.
pln_ca1_104_01 = "",--Find those numbers, gang! We need all three to get into the armory.
pln_ca1_104_02 = "",--Three colored numbers. Look for computer briefcases.
pln_ca1_104_03 = "",--The code has three numbers, each color coded. You'll find them in computer briefcases.
pln_ca1_105_01 = "",--You need three colored digits to enter the armory. Or guess.
pln_ca1_105_02 = "",--A three digit code will open the armory. Find it.
pln_ca1_106_01 = "",--We already got the code. Enter it and get into the armory.
pln_ca1_106_02 = "",--Good job, we already have that code. Use it on the armory.
pln_ca1_106_03 = "",--The code we got works on the armory. Get in there!
pln_ca1_107_01 = "武器庫のC4を取って来い!",--C4 in the armory. Go get it!
pln_ca1_107_02 = "武器庫に行って、C4を取って来い!",--Head to the armory and load up on C4.
pln_ca1_107_03 = "C4を持っていくのを忘れるなよ",--Don't forget to grab C4 from the armory.
pln_ca1_108_01 = "正解はそこか! 金庫があったぞ!",--You bet on the right spot! There's the vault!
pln_ca1_108_02 = "...よし! 金庫の上部が見えたぞ!",--And... great! There's the top of the vault!
pln_ca1_109_01 = "クソ! 金庫は別の場所だ。別の場所にC4を設置しろ",--Damn! All right, that wasn't the vault. C4 the other spot!
pln_ca1_109_02 = "チクショウ! とにかくC4を植え続けるんだ",--Crap! Just plant the C4 at the other spot. It's a sure thing now.
pln_ca1_10_01 = "104号室だ!",--104!
pln_ca1_110_01 = "ホール床を爆破して穴を開けろ。金庫に繋がるはずだ。",--Blast a hole in the floor of the Gambling Hall. That'll give us access to the vault.
pln_ca1_110_02 = "C4をギャンブルホールに植えるんだ、ギャング共。",--Get that C4 planted in the Gambling Hall, gang.
pln_ca1_110_03 = "お前らはギャンブルホールの床にC4を取り付ける必要がある。急げ!",--You need to get the C4 down in the Gambling Hall. Hurry!
pln_ca1_111_01 = "Bileはお前らを待っている! 奴はウィンチを持ってきている。さあ、フレアを焚け!",--Bile is waiting for you guys! He's got the winch. Come on, light the flare!
pln_ca1_111_02 = "フレアを焚け、ギャング。Bileにウィンチを下ろす場所を指示する必要がある。",--Light that flare, gang. Bile needs to drop off the winch.
pln_ca1_111_03 = "Bileはウィンチを下ろすタイミングを待っている。奴のためにフレアを焚いてやれ。",--Bile's waiting to ditch the winch. Light the flare for him.
pln_ca1_112_01 = "",--Signal the blimp with the fireworks. Let's give the good folks of Vegas a show to remember.
pln_ca1_112_02 = "花火を上げるのを忘れるなよ。1999年のベガスみたいにな",--Don't forget the fireworks. Vegas will go up like 1999.
pln_ca1_112_03 = "花火を打ち上げることを忘れるなよ。夜空に光を与えてやれ。",--Remember to sort the fireworks. Light up the night sky.
pln_ca1_113_01 = "",--Good job! Now reactivate BFD!
pln_ca1_113_02 = "",--Great. Now turn her back on.
pln_ca1_114_01 = "",--One of BFD's coolant tanks is empty. She needs that water, guys. Grab a refill from the bathrooms!
pln_ca1_114_02 = "",--Looks like one of her coolant tanks is finished. Be gents and fetch that girl a refill. Uh, from the crapper.
pln_ca1_114_03 = "",--BFD's guzzled a whole coolant tank already. Fill her glass, gang. Bathroom's have water.
pln_ca1_115_01 = "",--Watch out gang! BFD overheats if you don't give her enough water. Get it from the bathroom.
pln_ca1_115_02 = "",--BFD works hard, but drinks a lot of water. Make sure she has coolant. You can find water in the bathroom.
pln_ca1_115_03 = "",--We don't need BFD breaking down on us, crew. Make sure she has plenty of coolant. Get water from the bathroom.
pln_ca1_116_01 = "",--BFD needs cooling. Refill the tank with water Hurry!
pln_ca1_116_02 = "",--Don't let BFD overheat. Refill that tank with water!
pln_ca1_116_03 = "",--BFD will break down if she gets too hot. Keep them water tanks full.
pln_ca1_117_01 = "",--Find The Dentist's loot, guys!
pln_ca1_117_02 = "",--Will one of you clowns just grab that loot, please?
pln_ca1_117_03 = "",--Come on, Dentists' loot is right there.
pln_ca1_118_01 = "",--Whatever it is, we got it! Get it to the limo.
pln_ca1_118_02 = "",--Dunno what that is, but we got it. Now, back to the car!
pln_ca1_119_01 = "",--All right, that's it! Throw it up onto BFD.
pln_ca1_119_02 = "",--Great. Now toss it up onto BFD.
pln_ca1_11_01 = "151号室だ!",--151!
pln_ca1_121_01 = "",--Amazing job! Now, climb up on top of BFD and the blimp will take you to safety. Or grab more loot. Your choice.
pln_ca1_121_02 = "",--Now get onto BFD and let the blimp carry you up, up and away. Or stay and grab more loot.
pln_ca1_121_03 = "",--Amazing! Just climb up onto BFD and we call it a job done. Or stay behind and really pick the place clean.
pln_ca1_123_01 = "よーしわかった、入力するコードは次の通りだ。",--All right, the numbers for the code are:
pln_ca1_123_02 = "コードは...",--The code is...
pln_ca1_123_03 = "よし、コードは...",--Right, the numbers for the code are...
pln_ca1_124_01 = "0",--Zero.
pln_ca1_124_02 = "0!",--Zero!
pln_ca1_125_01 = "1",--One
pln_ca1_125_02 = "1!",--One!
pln_ca1_126_01 = "2",--Two
pln_ca1_126_02 = "2!",--Two!
pln_ca1_127_01 = "3",--Three
pln_ca1_127_02 = "3!",--Three!
pln_ca1_128_01 = "4",--Four
pln_ca1_128_02 = "4!",--Four!
pln_ca1_129_01 = "5",--Five
pln_ca1_129_02 = "5!",--Five!
pln_ca1_12_01 = "152号室だ!",--152!
pln_ca1_130_01 = "6",--Six
pln_ca1_130_02 = "6!",--Six!
pln_ca1_131_01 = "7",--Seven
pln_ca1_131_02 = "7!",--Seven!
pln_ca1_132_01 = "8",--Eight
pln_ca1_132_02 = "8!",--Eight!
pln_ca1_133_01 = "9",--Nine
pln_ca1_133_02 = "9!",--Nine!
pln_ca1_134_01 = "当たり! しかしお前が勝てる運が銀行強盗で奪える額を上回る必要があるぞ。",--Strike! Gonna need to rob more banks if this is your luck.
pln_ca1_134_02 = "ちょっ! お前が今夜たっぷり運試しを楽しもうとしている訳じゃない事を祈るぜ。",--Ouch! I hope that's not a sign of the luck you'll enjoy tonight.
pln_ca1_134_03 = "ギャンブルは病気だぞ! だがまだやめられるぞ、中毒者!",--Gambling is a disease. Stop while you can, sucker!
pln_ca1_135_01 = "カッシャーン、ギャング! ひょっとすると俺たちは銀行強盗をやめてスロットでPAYDAYを得られるかもな!",--Ka-ching, gang! Maybe we can stop robbing banks and earn our PAYDAY on the slots.
pln_ca1_135_02 = "",--Hot damn! You're on a hot streak!
pln_ca1_135_03 = "お前がどれくらい勝てるっつうんだ? それで俺たちが強盗を引退できるとでも?",--How much did you win? Can we all retire?
pln_ca1_136_01 = "落ち着けよ! ここをよく見ろ! ここでどんな盗品を巻き上げられるか想像してみるんだ!",--Whoa! Look at this place! Imagine all the loot we can boost from here!
pln_ca1_136_02 = "ここでは法律の圏内まで豊かになれる。それじゃ法を守る貧乏人になろうか。",--This place is legit rich. Let's make it legit poor.
pln_ca1_136_03 = "",--It's tacky, but it's fun, and knows it. Welcome to Vegas, gang.
pln_ca1_137_01 = "",--These machines are for nickel-and-dime suckers. Don't waste your time.
pln_ca1_137_02 = "",--The Golden Grin never closes. You want to waste time nickel-and-diming the slots...?
pln_ca1_137_03 = "こんなん、へっぽこマシンだぞ。俺たちはもっと大きな景品のためにここにいる。",--These machines are small fry. We're here for a bigger prize.
pln_ca1_138_01 = "ここが受付エリアだ。この場所を覚えておけ。後で使えるかもしれねえ。",--The reception area. Remember the location. Might come in handy.
pln_ca1_138_02 = "これは受付だな。どこにあるか覚えておけよ。",--This is reception. Remember where it is.
pln_ca1_138_03 = "受付だな。よし、ここが後で必要になる時が来るかもしれねえ。ここがどこにあるか注意しておけ。",--Reception. Okay, we may need it later - note where it is.
pln_ca1_139_01 = "このエリアは従業員専用だ。どのオフィスにもここから入れるな。",--This area's employees only. All the offices are accessible from here.
pln_ca1_139_02 = "この場所はスタッフ専用だ。ここからオフィスに侵入できるな。",--This place is for staff only. Offices can be accessed here.
pln_ca1_139_03 = "",--This is where the staff work. Offices, IT, security and so on.
pln_ca1_13_01 = "153号室だ!",--153!
pln_ca1_140_01 = "これは受付だな。",--This is the reception desk.
pln_ca1_141_01 = "メインロビーだ。",--The main lobby.
pln_ca1_142_01 = "バー付きの屋外温水プールだ。",--Heated outdoor pool with bar.
pln_ca1_143_01 = "屋外ラウンジだ。冷たいものを飲むにはもってこいだな..",--Exterior lounge. Nice for a cool drink..
pln_ca1_144_01 = "このゲームルームはまさに、Golden Grinの心臓部だな。",--This game room is the heart of The Golden Grin.
pln_ca1_145_01 = "これらは、ゲストルームか。",--These are the guest rooms.
pln_ca1_146_01 = "従業員専用のエリアだ。",--The employee only areas.
pln_ca1_147_01 = "これはセキュリティ·センターだな。",--This is the Security Center.
pln_ca1_14_01 = "154号室だ!",--154!
pln_ca1_150_01 = "設計図を書庫から手に入れろ。従業員専用エリアのどっかにあるはずだ..",--Get the blueprints in the archives. They're somewhere in the employee only areas..
pln_ca1_150_02 = "設計図は書庫の中だ。たぶん従業員専用エリアのどこかだろう。",--The blueprints are in the archives. My guess would be the employee only areas.
pln_ca1_150_03 = "書庫に設計図が保管されている。スタッフエリアを確認しろ。",--The archives will hold the blueprints. Check the staff areas.
pln_ca1_151_01 = "",--Where are those blueprints, gang? Scan 'em, send 'em. You can do it in IT.
pln_ca1_151_02 = "",--Come on, guys. Get the plans scanned and faxed. Do it in IT.
pln_ca1_151_03 = "",--Gang. You gotta scan and fax over the blueprints. Sure that can be done in IT.
pln_ca1_152_01 = "取ったな。部屋は...",--Got it. Room...
pln_ca1_152_02 = "来たか、部屋は...",--Here it comes. Room...
pln_ca1_152_03 = "この... 部屋は...",--It's... room...
pln_ca1_153_01 = "",--Its vent connects with the Security Center.
pln_ca1_153_02 = "",--Its vent goes right to the Security Center.
pln_ca1_153_03 = "",--It shares a vent with the Security Center.
pln_ca1_154_01 = "",--What was that room again?
pln_ca1_154_02 = "",--Uh, it was number...
pln_ca1_154_03 = "",--Let me check. Room...
pln_ca1_155_01 = "",--Now, the vault is located down in the Security Center. You have to get down and through there to reach it.
pln_ca1_155_02 = "",--You'll find the vault down in The Grin's Security Center. Head there.
pln_ca1_156_01 = "",--Great! That's the door open! Only thing left is disabling the lasers.
pln_ca1_156_02 = "",--Outstanding crew. The door's opening. All you need to do now is disable those lasers.
pln_ca1_156_03 = "",--OK, first things first, look for the gear case.
pln_ca1_157_01 = "",--The blimp could be all the way across Nevada and would see those.
pln_ca1_157_02 = "",--I think they saw that from the ISS!
pln_ca1_158_01 = "何なんだこいつは...",--What the hell...
pln_ca1_158_02 = "なんだ... こりゃ...",--I don't... know...
pln_ca1_159_01 = "どうも、良い午後ですね。",--Good evening, sir.
pln_ca1_159_02 = "",--Thank you for your time, sir.
pln_ca1_159_03 = "",--Can I ask if you are having a good day, sir?
pln_ca1_159_04 = "",--A very good evening to you, sir.
pln_ca1_159_05 = "",--So good to talk to you, sir.
pln_ca1_15_01 = "",--All right. Head to reception, find a terminal and download the guest list.
pln_ca1_15_02 = "",--Nice. Now go get that guest list from reception.
pln_ca1_160_01 = "",--This is, uh, Craig in the, uh, Customer Satisfaction Department calling.
pln_ca1_160_02 = "",--Uh, this is, Francoise. I am calling from the Customer Satisfaction desk.
pln_ca1_160_03 = "",--Um, my name is, uh... Tony. Why not. I'm calling from Customer Satisfaction here at The Grin.
pln_ca1_160_04 = "",--This is... Gerd. I'm calling you from The Golden Grin Customer Satisfaction Department.
pln_ca1_161_01 = "",--I wanted to ask if you were thinking of trying our All You Can Eat buffet today?
pln_ca1_162_02 = "",--I wanted to remind you that our All You Can Eat buffet is now open.
pln_ca1_162_03 = "",--I just wanted to make sure that you know that our All You Can Eat buffet is now available.
pln_ca1_162_04 = "",--Our All You Can Eat buffet is now open, and I wanted to make sure that you knew.
pln_ca1_163_01 = "",--We have some excellent lobster tails for you to enjoy.
pln_ca1_163_02 = "",--You won't find a better New York steak anywhere, including New York.
pln_ca1_163_03 = "",--If you want your beef rare, we'll just wipe its ass and lead it to your table.
pln_ca1_163_04 = "",--We have a fine selection of rare meats from Africa. You ever sampled elephant?
pln_ca1_164_01 = "",--We're serving... uh... soup. Made with... uh... vegetables.
pln_ca1_164_02 = "",--Also... that Italian stuff... uh... spaghetti! You can have as many tins as you want.
pln_ca1_164_03 = "",--We microwave everything so it is as hot and fresh as you can possibly want.
pln_ca1_164_04 = "",--You like bread. We got bread. Uh... yeah. Assloads of bread... Sir.
pln_ca1_165_01 = "",--We got ice cream too. You like ice cream?
pln_ca1_165_02 = "",--Perhaps sir has a sweet tooth? How would you like enough cake to choke a camel?
pln_ca1_165_03 = "",--We got those little pastry balls with the chocolate and cream.
pln_ca1_165_04 = "",--Don't forget we have enough sugary desserts to give you diabetes.
pln_ca1_166_01 = "",--We got rice. We got fries. We got mashed potato. We got grits.
pln_ca1_166_02 = "",--And what would you like as a side? Uh... sausage patties? We got 'em!
pln_ca1_166_03 = "",--You can get a side of cornbread with that. Yummy!
pln_ca1_166_04 = "",--And if you want, we can even make you toast.
pln_ca1_167_01 = "",--All yours for the price of... say... 18 bucks.
pln_ca1_167_02 = "",--And how much will it cost you? Shall we say... 18 bucks?
pln_ca1_167_03 = "",--All You Can Eat, remember. Just 18 bucks.
pln_ca1_167_04 = "",--And the price? 18 bucks. How you like that, huh?
pln_ca1_168_01 = "",--You're wasting time! Repair BFD, get her working and let's finish this caper.
pln_ca1_168_02 = "",--Fix up BFD and let's finish this. Come on, crew, we're so close.
pln_ca1_168_03 = "",--Get BFD fixed up, gang. Come on, stop wasting time.
pln_ca1_169_01 = "",--BFD needs more juice! Hook her up to the other socket. Keep it running.
pln_ca1_169_02 = "",--That's one socket, but that big beautiful girl needs another.
pln_ca1_16_01 = "",--Now find a terminal in IT with internet access. Upload that data to me.
pln_ca1_16_02 = "",--That's the list. Now get back to IT and upload it from an online terminal.
pln_ca1_170_01 = "",--C'mon, gang! Get the bags, and assemble the winch.
pln_ca1_170_02 = "",--Grab those bags, gang, come on!
pln_ca1_170_03 = "",--You gotta grab the parts of the winch, crew!
pln_ca1_171_01 = "",--Screw the winch down!
pln_ca1_171_02 = "",--Get that winch secure!
pln_ca1_171_03 = "",--Remember to screw that winch down good.
pln_ca1_172_01 = "",--Connect the winch to BFD with the hook.
pln_ca1_172_02 = "",--Get the winch hooked to BFD, gang.
pln_ca1_172_03 = "",--You need to hook BFD up with the winch.
pln_ca1_173_01 = "",--All right. Armory uses a three digit code. Look for it in the casino. Numbers and colors. Or you can gamble on guessing.
pln_ca1_173_02 = "",--Armory needs a three digit code. You can find the digits throughout the Grin. Get to it!
pln_ca1_173_03 = "",--We need a code to open the armory. Three digits. Colour coded. They're somewhere in the Grin. Get searching!
pln_ca1_17_01 = "",--Got it! I'll do a background check on this guy. Hang on.
pln_ca1_17_02 = "",--That's it! Doing a background check now. Hold on.
pln_ca1_18_01 = "",--Looks like he's running dry. Bring him another with a little extra flavor in it. I'm sure you can find a bottle in one of the bars and spike it.
pln_ca1_18_02 = "",--Looks like his drink is getting low. Lets serve him another, with a little something added. Find the same bottle at one of the bars.
pln_ca1_19_01 = "",--Find the scotch and spike it. Red bottle.
pln_ca1_19_02 = "",--Our guy likes Red Dragon scotch. Find it, spike it and serve it.
pln_ca1_20_01 = "",--Find the Jaegerheister and spike it. Green bottle.
pln_ca1_20_02 = "",--Our guy has a taste for Jaegerheister. Find the green bottle, spike it and serve it.
pln_ca1_21_01 = "",--Find the pink schnapps bottle and spike it.
pln_ca1_21_02 = "",--Pinky Demon schnapps? Huh. Find it, spike it, serve it.
pln_ca1_22_01 = "",--Find the blue bottle and spike it.
pln_ca1_22_02 = "",--Our guest loves Ocean's Ten vodka. Find another blue bottle and spike it.
pln_ca1_23_01 = "",--Now top up his glass. Soon as he swallows, well, let's say he's going to go loud. Follow him, and get the card for his room.
pln_ca1_23_02 = "",--Fill his glass. Once he downs that, well... he's going to lose interest in the slots. Follow him, and get his keycard.
pln_ca1_23_03 = "",--Pour him a drink. Once he takes a sip, the little something we added should... well, he's going to run for the nearest toilet. Follow him. Get his keycard.
pln_ca1_24_01 = "",--That's it, buddy. Drink up.
pln_ca1_24_02 = "",--Take a nice, long drink, pal.
pln_ca1_25_01 = "",--Pick up that keycard, and get to his room.
pln_ca1_25_02 = "",--That's his keycard. Grab it.
pln_ca1_26_01 = "",--Now look for a vent, and get the gas pumping. Send the security to Neverland.
pln_ca1_26_02 = "",--Find the vent, and start pumping the gas. We'll make their security center fuzzy and warm and... *yawns*
pln_ca1_27_01 = "",--Opening the vault needs a three digit code. Each digit is held by a manager, and each is in a computer briefcase. We need that code. Find them.
pln_ca1_27_02 = "",--Vault needs a three digit code, and each digit is held by a manager. They hold them in computer briefcases. Gang, find that code.
pln_ca1_28_01 = "",--We've all three digits we need for the vault. Get there and enter the code.
pln_ca1_28_02 = "",--That's all three digits for the code. Head to the vault, let's see if they work.
pln_ca1_28_03 = "",--Three digits. Outstanding! Now head to the vault and try them out.
pln_ca1_29_01 = "いいぞ。これでお前は再びマスクを被れる。",--Great. Now you can mask up again.
pln_ca1_29_02 = "よし。これで好きな時にマスクを被れるぞ。",--Okay. Mask up when you're ready.
pln_ca1_30_01 = "警報が鳴ったな。よしギャングども、Plan Bだ。俺たちのやり方でいくぞ。",--That's the alarm. OK, gang. Plan B. Force our way through.
pln_ca1_30_02 = "アラームがなっちまった。問題ないぜ。PlanBだ。ショーの始まりだ。ギャングども。",--There's the alarm. No problem. Plan B. Put on a show, gang.
pln_ca1_30_03 = "アラームだ。大丈夫だ、Plan Bの時間だ。慈悲を捨てろ、お前ら。",--The alarm. All right. Time for Plan B. No mercy, crew.
pln_ca1_31_01 = "武器庫を探してみてくれ。情報によればC4があるんだそうだ。'異常事態'に備えてな。まあ、これはその異常事態ってこった。",--Look for the armory. Intel says they're holding C4. For "extraordinary cases". Well, this is one of those extraordinary cases.
pln_ca1_31_02 = "The Dentistの情報によれば奴らはC4を持っているんだそうだ。警備員のロッカールームの近くに武器庫がある。行ってみよう。",--The Dentist's intel says they have C4. There's an armory near the guards' locker room. Get there.
pln_ca1_31_03 = "Dentistが言うには、武器庫にC4があるんだとよ。行って、取って来るんだ。",--Dentist tells me they have C4 in the armory there. Get there, and get it.
pln_ca1_32_01 = "武器庫だ。たくさんC4が積み重なっているようだな。カジノに何故プラスチック爆弾が必要なのか、キリストは知っている...",--The armory. Looks like they've a bunch of C4 stacked there. Christ knows what a casino needs plastic explosive for...
pln_ca1_32_02 = "C4がそこにあるぞ。何故The GrinはC4が必要なんだ? 神のみぞ知るってやつか。",--The C4 is right in there. Why does The Grin need C4? God knows.
pln_ca1_33_01 = "",--That's the first number. Need two more.
pln_ca1_33_02 = "",--First number. Get the other two.
pln_ca1_34_01 = "",--Second number. Just one more.
pln_ca1_34_02 = "",--That's the second. One more.
pln_ca1_35_01 = "",--That's all the numbers needed for the armory. Go enter that code.
pln_ca1_35_02 = "",--Okay, that's the digits for the armory code. Enter it!
pln_ca1_37_01 = "",--Grab that C4, gang.
pln_ca1_37_02 = "",--Now load up on C4. You'll need it.
pln_ca1_37_03 = "",--Grab as much C4 as you can, gang.
pln_ca1_38_01 = "",--Now plant the C4 in the main hall. The vault is right below. Two possible spots to blow. Hope lady luck is with us!
pln_ca1_38_02 = "",--Now detonate the C4 in the main hall. Place it right above the vault. Hard to say exactly where that is. Two possible spots. Pray for a bit of luck.
pln_ca1_38_03 = "",--Put the C4 in the main hall, right above the vault. Two possible spots, so it's a bit of a lottery. If need be, we'll blow them both!
pln_ca1_39_01 = "",--Light a flare to signal Bile. We need a big damn drill to get down there, which first needs a winch. He'll bring the parts for it.
pln_ca1_39_02 = "",--Now the vaults exposed, we're going to drill down. A big drill. Which needs a winch. Signal Bile with a flare when you're ready.
pln_ca1_40_01 = "",--Now just hold tight and wait for Bile to drop the winch.
pln_ca1_40_02 = "",--Hold the ground. Bile will have that winch to you any second.
pln_ca1_41_01 = "",--Grab those parts, heisters.
pln_ca1_41_02 = "",--All right, snatch up those winch parts.
pln_ca1_42_01 = "",--Now get that winch put together in the main hall.
pln_ca1_42_02 = "",--Assemble the winch in the main hall, gang.
pln_ca1_42_03 = "",--Put the winch together where I marked, crew.
pln_ca1_43_01 = "",--Screw down the winch so that it'll be stable. Trust me, for what's coming, you need it secure.
pln_ca1_43_02 = "",--Screw the winch down good. Believe me, you need it stable for the next part.
pln_ca1_44_01 = "",--All right! Signal the blimp. And do it Vegas style. Find some fireworks and light them up.
pln_ca1_44_02 = "",--Nice! Next, we're going to signal the blimp, and for something like that we need a big signal. A fireworks display! Find them!
pln_ca1_44_03 = "",--We're going to bring the drill in with a blimp. For the pilot to see your signal, you need to set off a firework display. So look for them!
pln_ca1_45_01 = "",--All right, get those fireworks onto the terrace.
pln_ca1_45_02 = "",--Great! Now head to the terrace and place the fireworks.
pln_ca1_46_01 = "",--Light the fireworks, and stand back.
pln_ca1_46_02 = "",--Set off the fireworks. Stand back. Stay safe.
pln_ca1_46_03 = "",--Nice. Now light the fusepaper and...
pln_ca1_47_01 = "",--The drill can't be dropped through that skylight barrier. Gotta open it from the security center.
pln_ca1_47_02 = "",--That damn barrier is preventing the drill from coming down. Get to security and open it.
pln_ca1_48_01 = "",--Hack the skylight controls to open it. Whatever you do, don't let the fuzz disable it.
pln_ca1_48_02 = "",--Okay. The controls. Hack 'em, and keep the cops off.
pln_ca1_48_03 = "",--Get hacking those skylight controls and keep the damn cops off.
pln_ca1_49_01 = "",--The hack was interrupted. Get it going again.
pln_ca1_49_02 = "",--Who the - damn cops messed with the hack. Restart it!
pln_ca1_49_03 = "",--The cops pulled the hack. Get there and reboot it.
pln_ca1_50_01 = "",--Wait for the blimp to get here with the drill.
pln_ca1_50_02 = "",--Okay, the blimp is on the way. Just give it time.
pln_ca1_50_03 = "",--Blimp is over the city and headed for you. Give it a moment.
pln_ca1_51_01 = "",--Here she comes. "BFD". Stands for "Big Goddamn Drill". Almost.
pln_ca1_51_02 = "",--Okay, blimp is lowering her to you. BFD. Look at that beauty.
pln_ca1_51_03 = "",--Hell, that's a sight! "BFD". Or "Big Funky Drill.".
pln_ca1_52_01 = "",--You need to get BFD right above the vault. The winch will move her, so get them hooked up.
pln_ca1_52_02 = "",--All right. Now this is why we brought the winch. Hook it to BFD, and it'll get the position right.
pln_ca1_53_01 = "",--Start the winch and it will move BFD into position. Don't let the cops stop it!
pln_ca1_53_02 = "",--Now fire up the winch! Keep the cops off it.
pln_ca1_54_01 = "",--Restart the winch. And keep the damn cops off it.
pln_ca1_54_02 = "",--Gotta get that winch running again, gang.
pln_ca1_54_03 = "",--Winch isn't working, crew. Fix it!
pln_ca1_55_01 = "",--All right, now let the winch do its job.
pln_ca1_55_02 = "",--There it goes. Let it do its thing.
pln_ca1_55_03 = "",--Okay. It's thing is moving BFD, your thing is keeping it safe.
pln_ca1_56_01 = "BFDは電力を消費する。それもたくさんだ! ソケットのカップルに彼女を引っ掛けろ。これらはカジノ内にある。そしてこいつらの接続が切られない様にするんだ。",--BFD needs power - lots of it! Hook her up to a couple of sockets. They're located inside the casino. Don't let them get disconnected.
pln_ca1_56_02 = "BFDは大食い娘でな。電力をかなり食う。2つのソケットに彼女を引っ掛けろ。カジノ内で出来る筈だ。それと、サツどもが来ないようにし続けるんだ。",--BFD is a greedy girl. Needs a lot of power. Hook her up to two sockets. You can find them inside the casino. And keep the cops off.
pln_ca1_57_01 = "BFDの電源が切れたぞ。ソケットを再接続するんだ。",--BFD's without power. Reconnect the power sockets.
pln_ca1_57_02 = "電源が落ちた。BFDを再接続しろ、ギャング共!",--Power's down. Get BFD reconnected, gang!
pln_ca1_57_03 = "クソッ、BFDの電源が失われちまった。クソったれポリ公どもが...ソケットに再接続するんだ。",--Damn, BFD lost power. Damn cops... reconnect the sockets.
pln_ca1_58_01 = "BFDのスイッチを投げろ! ショーの始まりだ!",--Throw the BFD's switch! Let the show begin!
pln_ca1_58_02 = "ようし、BFDのスイッチを投げろ。BFDの仕事ぶりを見てみるぞ!",--All right. now throw that switch. Let's see what BFD can do!
pln_ca1_58_03 = "BFDの電源を入れろ。いいもん見せてくれ。",--Now turn on BFD. They'll display her for years to come.
pln_ca1_59_01 = "BFDが金庫に穴を開けるまで待ってくれ。こんな怪物でも時間がかかる。サツを近寄せるな。",--Wait for BFD to crack through the vault. Even this monster will take time. Keep the cops away.
pln_ca1_59_02 = "BFDはマイペースなんだ。金庫は彼女に任せて、お前らはサツを近寄らせないことに専念しろ。",--BFD does things in her own time. Let her deal with the vault, you deal with cops getting near her.
pln_ca1_59_03 = "よし、彼女はドリルを金庫に向けて下ろしている。お前らは彼女の安全を確保しろ。",--Okay, she's drilling down into the vault. You keep her safe.
pln_ca1_60_01 = "くそ、サツが彼女を止めやがった! 連中に対処して、BFDを再起動するんだ!",--Damn, cops got to her! Clear the zone and reactivate BFD!
pln_ca1_60_02 = "サツがBFDを止めやがったぞ。連中を処理し、彼女を再起動させろ。",--The cops shut down BFD. Deal with them, and start her up again.
pln_ca1_61_01 = "貯水タンクが空っぽになっちまった。バスルームに連れていってやれ。おい、俺はそれが決して魅力的ではないと約束するぜ。",--Water tanks are empty. Refill them in the bathrooms. Hey, I never promised you glamour.
pln_ca1_61_02 = "BFDのノドが乾いちまった。バスルームで補充することができるぞ。彼女はうるさくはない。",--BFD's tanks are drained. You can refill them in the bathroom. She's not fussy.
pln_ca1_62_01 = "BFDが破損しちまった。修理にはtoolが必要だ。",--BFD broke down. Gonna need tools to repair it.
pln_ca1_62_02 = "くそ、BFDがやられちまった。修理するんだ。",--Damn, BFD is bust. You need tools to fix her up.
pln_ca1_63_01 = "BFDが終わったぞ。さあ、金庫に入れ!",--BFD's done. Now, down into the vault!
pln_ca1_63_02 = "終わったぞ! 早く、金庫に入るんだ!",--She's all done! Quickly, down into the vault!
pln_ca1_63_03 = "BFDはよくやってくれたな。金庫に入ろうぜ、ギャング共。",--BFD did a great job. Down into the vault. gang.
pln_ca1_64_01 = "やったぜ! Dentistの品を見つけて、ここからずらかろう。",--We're here! Find The Dentist's loot, and let's get it out of here.
pln_ca1_64_02 = "Dentistのブツを手に入れろ。俺達の目的はソイツだからな。",--Grab Dentists' loot. That's what we came for.
pln_ca1_64_03 = "ブツを手に入れて帰るぞ。",--Just grab that loot and let's get it out of here.
pln_ca1_65_01 = "やったな! さあ、リムジンに乗って帰るぞ。それとももっと頂いていくかだ。",--Outstanding! Now, get in the limo and end this. Or grab more loot. Your choice.
pln_ca1_65_02 = "よくやった。車にのってずらかるぞ。それか、ココを空っぽにしていくか?",--Great job. Now get in the car and let's end this. Or hang around and really clean the joint.
pln_ca1_65_03 = "もう帰ることもできるが、カジノをキレイにしてからでもいいぞ。",--You can bounce now, or you can stay and give the Golden Grin a thorough cleaning.
pln_ca1_66_01 = "Michoがどこかに置いた装備を見つけろ。ギターケースを探せ。",--Find the gear Micho planted somewhere. Look for a guitar case.
pln_ca1_66_02 = "お前らの装備はプールにあるはずだ。Michoがそこに装備を置いたかどうか確かめろ。ギターケースを探せ。",--Maybe your gear is at the pool. See if Micho left the gear there. Look for a guitar case.
pln_ca1_66_03 = "装備は喫煙所にあるはずだ。たぶんMichoがそこに置いてるはずだ。ギターケースを探せ。",--The gear could be at the smoking area. Perhaps Micho left your gear there. Look for a guitar case.
pln_ca1_67_01 = "あそこだ。お前らの装備はギターケースの中だ。",--Over there. Your gear's in that guitar case.
pln_ca1_67_02 = "あそこのギターケースが見えるか?お前らの装備はあの中だ。",--See that guitar case over there? That's your gear.
pln_ca1_68_01 = "",--Now we need to know who's in this room, steal their keycard. I'll need a guest list. Download that from a terminal in reception. Grab a USB.
pln_ca1_68_02 = "",--Okay, now I need a guest list. Find out who's in that room. We'll need their key. Reception should have a terminal with that info. Grab a USB stick.
pln_ca1_69_01 = "",--Still searching for the USB? Check back in IT.
pln_ca1_69_02 = "",--You got that USB yet? Surely IT will have one.
pln_ca1_69_03 = "",--I'm guessing any decent IT department will have a spare USB.
pln_ca1_70_01 = "",--Still waiting on the guest list, guys. Get to reception and download it.
pln_ca1_70_02 = "",--The guest list, guys. Get it from reception and we can see who's in our room.
pln_ca1_70_03 = "",--Reception will have the guest list, guys. Just head there, download it.
pln_ca1_71_01 = "",--That's it! Downloading. Give it a moment.
pln_ca1_71_02 = "",--Great. Here comes the guest list now.
pln_ca1_72_01 = "",--I need that guest list, guys. Send me those files. IT, internet access, upload. Easy!
pln_ca1_72_02 = "",--Find me the list, gang. Just plug it into an online terminal in IT.
pln_ca1_72_03 = "",--Don't forget to send me the list. Head to IT. Plug it in.
pln_ca1_73_01 = "",--Ok. Got him. Name, social security number, name of his dog... Find him. Check the screen in IT. Oh, and he's a slot machine addict, Might be a good place to start looking.
pln_ca1_73_02 = "",--That's him. Got his name, SSN, last time he took a dump... Check the screen in IT. Find him. Says here he loves the slots, so maybe that will be where he is.
pln_ca1_74_01 = "",--Find the guest. Remember, he's a slot machine addict.
pln_ca1_74_02 = "",--Find the guest so we can steal his keycard. Remember, he's likely on the slots.
pln_ca1_74_03 = "",--We need to track down the guest with the keycard. Probably pumping nickels into the slots.
pln_ca1_75_01 = "",--Got an idea. I got his phone number. I'll call him and distract him. You be ready to top up his glass.
pln_ca1_75_02 = "",--Wait. I have his cell number. Let me call him, try and distract him. Get ready to fill his glass.
pln_ca1_76_01 = "",--Great! He should be back gambling in no time. Wait for him to take a sip, let nature do its thing. When he dashes off to the crapper, follow him and get that card.
pln_ca1_76_02 = "",--All right. Now let's just wait for him to try that drink. He's going to run for the John any second. Follow him. Get his keycard.
pln_ca1_77_01 = "",--Get after him, and wait for your chance.
pln_ca1_77_02 = "",--Now! After him. Wait til he's alone.
pln_ca1_78_01 = "",--Now! Tie him down.
pln_ca1_78_02 = "",--Get him down! Tie him up!
pln_ca1_87_01 = "",--Haha, it worked! The guards in security are sleeping like babies. Don't worry about cameras now.
pln_ca1_87_02 = "",--That did it. They're all fast asleep. No need to worry about cameras from here on.
pln_ca1_88_01 = "",--One last obstacle before the vault. Lasers. Need to shut them down.
pln_ca1_88_02 = "",-- Lasers in front of the vault. Let's shut them down.
pln_ca1_89_01 = "",--Okay, the briefcases. First is held by casino manager, the second one by the pit boss and the third by their head of security.
pln_ca1_89_02 = "",--First briefcase is held by the casino manager. Second by the Pit Boss. Lastly, look for the head of security.
pln_ca1_89_03 = "",--Casino manager has the first briefcase. The Pit Boss has the second. And then the head of security. Need all three for the code.
pln_ca1_90_01 = "",--Guys, the briefcases. Check the owners office. Then find the pit boss. And, lastly, check near the guards' locker room.
pln_ca1_90_02 = "",--The owner likely keeps his in his office. The pit boss will be near the main hall. Security head probably keeps his somewhere near the locker room.
pln_ca1_90_03 = "",--Check the owners office for his briefcase. Pit boss will be around the main hall. The locker room is where the security chief's briefcase likely is.
pln_ca1_91_01 = "",--One down, two more to go. Find the other numbers and we get easy access to the vault.
pln_ca1_91_02 = "",--That's the first number. Keep looking. Two to go.
pln_ca1_91_03 = "",--First digit for the vault code. Keep searching. We need all three.
pln_ca1_92_01 = "",--Good job, that's the second number found. Just one more.
pln_ca1_92_02 = "",--Second digit for the vault. Just the last to find.
pln_ca1_92_03 = "",--Second digit for the code. Now, just get the last number and we're set.
pln_ca1_93_01 = "",--The Grin's vault can only be opened with a three digit code. This is one of the numbers we'll need to open it. Make a note.
pln_ca1_93_02 = "",--Their big vault takes a three digit code. This is one digit. Write it down. We'll need it later.
pln_ca1_93_03 = "",--This is one of the vault codes. Remember it. We're going to be needing it before we close this caper.
pln_ca1_94_01 = "",--Fantastic! We got the code for opening the vault. Now, just gotta get inside the security center unnoticed.
pln_ca1_94_02 = "",--Outstanding! That's the vault code. Once we're in the Security Center, we can open the vault with it.
pln_ca1_94_03 = "",--Good work. We'll need these three digits for the vault once we're through the Security Center.
pln_ca1_95_01 = "",--Got it! The casino manager's code.
pln_ca1_95_02 = "",--That's the managers digit. Serves him right for leaving it lying around.
pln_ca1_96_01 = "",--Nice. Security chief's number. He won't be happy to lose this.
pln_ca1_96_02 = "",--Security chief's code. His ass is in trouble for leaving this around.
pln_ca1_97_01 = "",--Great, That's the pit boss' number.
pln_ca1_97_02 = "",--We got the pit boss' code. Nice.
pln_ca1_98_01 = "",--Outstanding, guys, we're in! Help yourselves, give nothing back. Remember, our goal is the Dentists' loot.
pln_ca1_98_02 = "",--Out-goddamn-standing, crew! Get in, fill your bags. Take as much as you can, but remember, we're here for The Dentists' loot.
pln_ca1_99_01 = "",--Ah crap! More lasers. Must be an independent system. Watch the pattern. Don't want to trigger any alarms now.
pln_ca1_99_02 = "",--Damn it! More frickin' laser beams. All right, no time to figure out where the system is controlled. Just watch the pattern and hurry through.
pln_ca1_99_03 = "",--More laser defences. Forget disabling them. Just watch the pattern and be ready to run through.
zep_ca1_01_01 = "",--Man, this thing turns slower than your mom.
zep_ca1_01_02 = "",--I haven't handled something this big and clumsy since... nevermind.
zep_ca1_01_03 = "",--Getting some crosswind here. Nothing I can't handle.
zep_ca1_01_04 = "",--City looks beautiful from up here.
zep_ca1_01_05 = "",--Guys, I got half a dozen Japanese tourists shitting themselves in here. I hope they get good pics.
zep_ca1_01_06 = "",--Whooo weeeee! I flew B1's in Afghanistan. Never thought I'd drive one of these fuckers though.
zep_ca1_01_07 = "",--It's soooooo damned quiet...
zep_ca1_02_01 = "",-- Be there soon! Ramble on.
zep_ca1_02_02 = "",--On my way, friends!
zep_ca1_02_03 = "",--On approach now. Closing in...
zep_ca1_02_04 = "",--Almost at you, guys. We're gonna groove!
zep_ca1_02_05 = "",--Damn, this drill is a big sucka!
zep_ca1_03_01 = "",--Thank you. I see the fireworks. On our way!
zep_ca1_03_02 = "",--All right, there's the fireworks. Turning towards you.
zep_ca1_03_03 = "",--I see your signal. Rock n' Roll! Here we come.
zep_ca1_03_04 = "",--Those are some beautiful fireworks. We're coming.
zep_ca1_03_05 = "",--You're lighting up the sky. We're inbound.
zep_ca1_04_01 = "",--This is Captain Ford of the Vegas Sky Express. Standing by for your signal.
zep_ca1_04_02 = "",--Captain Ford here, flying the Vegas Sky Express. We're ready and waiting for your signal.
zep_ca1_04_03 = "",--Vegas Sky Express blimp here. Codename "Heartbreaker" commanding. We got a package for your party.
zep_ca1_04_04 = "",--This is Vegas Sky Express blimp, codename "Black Dog". We're ready to deliver on your signal.
zep_ca1_04_05 = "",--Codename "Bonzo Montreau" here! The Vegas Sky Express is standing by to drop your package.
zep_ca1_05_01 = "",--Here comes your package. Have a nice party now!
zep_ca1_05_02 = "",--Package is being delivered. Thank you for choosing the Sky Express!
zep_ca1_05_03 = "",--Your package is being lowered. Hope you have a great party. We'll wait here awhile. Over and out!
zep_ca1_05_04 = "",--Sky Express is in position and lowering the package. We'll hold position 'til you're done. Signing off!
zep_ca1_05_05 = "",--Okay, your package is coming down. Sky Express will stay here 'til you're done. Good luck!
pln_as1_brf_01_01 = "おい野郎ども、ニュースは見たか!? 西海岸に大地震が直撃しやがった! LAは滅茶苦茶になっちまってるが、今回の目的地はそこだ。Vladは、大きな取引のために貨物をシアトルからDCに運ぼうとしていたようだが、運び屋は地震が起こった時間にLAに居たみたいだ。恐らくロングビーチから出荷するつもりだったんだろう。Vladはその荷物を安全な場所まで運んで欲しいと要求している。今回は計画を立てる時間は無い。LAは麻痺っちまって、陸路は使い物にならない。お前らにはヘリで降りてもらうぞ",--Hey, you guys see the news?! Big quake just hit the West Coast! LA is completely messed up. And that's where you're headed.Seems Vlad has set up some big deal to move some freight from Seattle to DC. The shippers he contracted were in LA when the quake hit - I guess they were going to ship out of Long Beach. Vlad wants his freight secured safely. No time for planning on this one. LA is wrecked, and the roads are messed up so we're going to drop you in by chopper.
plt_as1_intro_01_01 = "ここで降ろす。用意はいいな!",--I'm putting you down here. Get ready to clear!
plt_as1_intro_01_02 = "降下地点に着いた。準備しろ!",--Here's the dropzone. Stand by!
plt_as1_intro_01_03 = "用意はいいか?ここが降りる場所だぜ。",--You guys ready? This is where you get out.
pln_as1_01_01 = "なんてこった、この光景は!",--Christ, look at this place!
pln_as1_01_02 = "こいつは、テレビで見た時も酷かったが...",--Jesus, it looked bad on the news, but...
pln_as1_01_03 = "``天使の街``ロサンゼルス...この地震でだいぶ天使さんも増えちまったようだな...",--City of Angeles. Looks like the quake made a few more...
pln_as1_02_01 = "Vladからの通信だ。",--I got Vlad on the line.
pln_as1_02_02 = "Vladがこのヤマの事でぜひ話したいそうだ。",--Vlad's very keen on talking to you on this one.
pln_as1_02_03 = "積み荷の扱いには要注意だそうだ。Vladが直接話したがってるぞ。",--Vlad's pretty upset about these safes. Wants to talk to you.
pln_as1_03_01 = "聞いたな。トラックはこの辺りのどこかだ。",--You heard him. The trucks are around here somewhere.
pln_as1_03_02 = "オーケー、トラックはこの高速道路のどこかにあるぞ。",--Okay, trucks are somewhere on this freeway.
pln_as1_03_03 = "話は済んだか。トラックを探そう。",--You heard the man. Let's find those trucks.
pln_as1_04_01 = "おい、2台目も探すんだ。",--Come on, find that second truck.
pln_as1_04_02 = "2台目のトラックも遠くは無いはずだ。探せ。",--Second truck can't be too far from the first. Find it.
pln_as1_04_03 = "もう1台はどこだ?この周辺のどこかのはずだ。",--Where's that second truck? Gotta be around here somewhere.
pln_as1_05_01 = "いいぞ。じゃあこいつらを開けちまおう。Vladは何を運んでたのやら。",--Great. Now crack those trucks open. Let's see what Vlad was shipping.
pln_as1_05_02 = "さあ、トラックを開けよう。中に入るんだ。",--Now, get those trucks opened. Let's get inside them.
pln_as1_05_03 = "よし。トラックを開けてあのクソロシアンの荷物を見てやろう。",--Good. Now we can open the trucks up and see what that crazy Ivan was shipping.
pln_as1_06_01 = "おお、今度は少なくとも核じゃなさそうだな。",--Well, at least it isn't nukes this time.
pln_as1_06_02 = "Vladが俺たちを地上の地獄に送り込むぐらいにはソイツらが重要に違いないぜ。",--You can bet they're important if Vlad sent us to this hellhole for them.
pln_as1_06_03 = "ティアラ、核弾頭。それに金庫。Vladらしい依頼だな。",--Tiaras, nuclear warheads, and safes. Just another job for Vlad.
pln_as1_07_01 = "これがハリウッドの魅力じゃないのはわかってる。だが、早く安全地帯に逃げないとな。",--I know it's not Hollywood glamour, but someone better gets those safes outta there.
pln_as1_07_02 = "さぁ、クルー共。金庫を背負って外にだすんだ。",--Come on, crew. Get the safes out. Put your back into it.
pln_as1_07_03 = "ギャングども、金庫を取り出せ。あぁ、そいつが100度以上あるってのは知ってるが、取り出すんだ。",--Get the safes out, gang. Yeah, I know it's over a hundred degrees, but get to it.
pln_as1_08_01 = "そこを通る必要がある。C4を送るぞ。",--Gonna have to get through there. I'm sending you C4.
pln_as1_08_02 = "C4で対処しろ。今送るから、少し待て。",--A little C4 will deal with that. I'm sending some now. Hold on.
pln_as1_08_03 = "戻ってきたパイロットにC4を投下するよう指示した。少し耐えろ。",--Telling the pilot to return with the C4 to bust you through there. Just hang in there.
pln_as1_09_01 = "よし、C4を降下したぞ。拾うんだ。",--All right, the C4's on the ground. Grab it!
pln_as1_09_02 = "ギャング共、誰でもいいからC4を取れ。",--There's the C4, gang. Someone grab it.
pln_as1_09_03 = "ギャング共、C4を取れ。建設現場の壁を壊すんだ。",--Take the C4, crew. That will deal with the construction yard wall.
pln_as1_10_01 = "よし、C4を貼り付けろ。出口を作るんだ。",--All right. Now slap the C4 on there. We're busting our way out.
pln_as1_10_02 = "よし。あの壁をぶっ飛ばすんだ。それで道が開ける。",--Great. Now go blast that obstruction. It's your way out.
pln_as1_10_03 = "さあ、あそこの現場につながる壁を破壊するんだ。それで先に進める。",--Now go deal with obstruction to the yard over there. You're getting out that way.
pln_as1_11_01 = "よし。金庫は積んだな。建設現場から脱出するぞ。トラックを移動させろ!",--All right. Safes are in. We're getting out through the yard. Make sure the truck is there!
pln_as1_11_02 = "これで金庫は全部だな。さあトラックを建設現場まで動かせ。こいつを終わらせるぞ!",--And that's it for the safes. Now I want that truck in the yard. We're closing this one!
pln_as1_11_03 = "いいぞ。すべての金庫を積んだな。トラックを元の場所まで動かせ、ギャング共 - がんばれ!",--Great. All the safes are in. Now let's see the truck back at the yard, gang - hustle!
pln_as1_12_01 = "ギャング共、工事現場に行くんだ! 急げ!",--Gang, get into the construction yard! Hurry!
pln_as1_12_02 = "野郎ども、工事現場に向かうんだ。そこから逃げるぞ。",--Guys, I need you in the construction yard. It's the only way out.
pln_as1_12_03 = "工事現場に向かえ! 急ぐんだ!",--Get to the construction yard! Hurry!
pln_as1_13_01 = "野郎ども、パイロットが戻ってくる! フレアを焚くんだ!",--Guys, the pilot is circling! Drop the flare!
pln_as1_13_02 = "ギャング共、パイロットがそちらを視認できない。フレアをたくんだ。",--Gang, the pilot can't see you. You need to light that flare.
pln_as1_13_03 = "フレアを焚け、ギャング共。それが無いとパイロットがそちらを視認できない。",--Light the flare, gang. Pilot is blind without it.
pln_as1_14_01 = "金庫を積んだり降ろしたりしてる暇はない。ヘリはトラックごと運ぶのに向かってる。トラックに乗り込め!",--We don't have time to load and unload the safes. The chopper's just going to carry the truck. It can do it. You just need to get in!
pln_as1_14_02 = "ヘリに積み込みしてる暇はない。ヘリでトラックごと運べる。中に乗り込め!",--No time to load the chopper. It's just going to grab the truck, so you need to be inside!
pln_as1_14_03 = "トラックに乗り込め! ヘリでまとめて空輸する!",--Get inside the truck! The chopper is going to airlift the whole damn thing out!
pln_as1_15_01 = "そして..離陸! クルーよ、よくやった!",--And....lift off! Outstanding work, crew!
pln_as1_15_02 = "ケーブルが掛かってることを祈ろう。ちょっと待て、俺は金庫での重量増を加味したっけ...?",--Hope that cable holds. Wait, did I add the weight of the safes...?
pln_as1_15_03 = "天使のように飛んでる...街は廃墟だ。よくやった!",--Flying like angels over...that ruin of a city. Great job!
pln_as1_16_01 = "神よ、LAが滅茶苦茶だ。がれきだらけだ。",--Christ, LA's wrecked. Rubble everywhere.
pln_as1_16_02 = "おお、街が滅茶苦茶だな。道路に、建物に...全部壊れちまってる。",--Man, the city's a ruin. Roads, buildings...everything's screwed.
pln_as1_16_03 = "お前ら、すげえ壊れっぷりだな。がれきで遮断されてる。",--Guys, the wreckage is incredible. Rubble blocking everything.
pln_as1_17_01 = "トラックはこのあたりにある。Vladの手下もいるから、引き金に気をつけろよ。",--The trucks are here somewhere. Vlad's guys will be too, so watch your fire.
pln_as1_17_02 = "トラックは近くにある。Vladの運び屋にも気をつけろ。殺すんじゃないぞ!",--The trucks are somewhere near. Keep an eye out for Vlad's couriers too. Don't drop them!
pln_as1_17_03 = "トラックを探せ! そしてVladの手下がまだ近くに居たら、撃つんじゃないぞ。",--Find those trucks! And don't shoot Vlad's guys if any of them are still around.
pln_as1_18_01 = "ずっと背負えるような代物じゃないな。待ってくれ、運搬手段を見つけるからな。",--There's no way you're hauling those out on your backs. Hold on, I'm going to find you a transport.
pln_as1_18_02 = "そんなの重くて運べないだろ。運搬と脱出の方法を見つけないと。ちょっと待ってくれ、俺が見つけてやる。",--You'll never carry those out. Gonna need a transport, and a way out. Give me a minute, I'll find something.
pln_as1_18_03 = "金庫はクソ重いし、トラックは壊れちまってる。何か他の運搬手段が必要だ。俺が見つけてやる - やられるなよ。",--The safes are way too heavy to carry, and those trucks are screwed. Gonna need another transport. I'll find something - hang tight.
pln_as1_19_01 = "クソ、滅茶苦茶だな。今探してる。頑張れよ。",--Damn, place is wrecked. Still looking. Hang in there.
pln_as1_19_02 = "街が崩壊してなければもっと簡単なのにな。待っててくれよ。",--This would be easier if the city wasn't a ruin. Just hold on.
pln_as1_19_03 = "まだ探してる。クソ、LAが煙で覆われてる。死ぬなよ。",--I'm still looking. Damn, LA is smoked. Hold them off.
pln_as1_20_01 = "やった! 工事現場にトラックがある。ここから脱出するにはこいつが一番だが、壁を壊すのにC4がいる。今送ったからな。金庫を取られるな!",--Got it! Construction yard, with a truck. Looks like the best way out of here, but you'll need C4 to bust that wall. Sending it now. Mind the safes!
pln_as1_20_02 = "ギャング共、川の対岸の工事現場だ! そこに駐車してるトラックに乗れ。俺の計算だと、脱出ポイントはそこが最善だ。$NL;C4を送る。金庫を守れ!",--Gang, there's a construction yard across the river! Got a truck parked up. Reckon it's our best way out. Sending you C4 now. Protect the safes!
pln_as1_20_03 = "野郎ども、俺のカンでは、道の向かい側の建設現場が脱出地点に一番良い気がする。$NL;そこにはトラックがある。壁を崩すためのC4をそっちに送る。",--Crew, I'm guessing that that construction yard across the way is your best bet for getting out. They have a truck. Sending you some C4 to bring the wall down now.
pln_as1_21_01 = "そのトラックは完璧そうだ。全部の金庫を乗せろ - 全部だ。",--That truck looks perfect. Now get the safes loaded on board - all of them.
pln_as1_21_02 = "いけそうだ! そいつらをトラックに載せろ!",--That will do! Start getting them out and into the truck!
pln_as1_21_03 = "金庫をトラックに載せるんだ!",--Get the safes loaded onto that truck!
plt_as1_01_01 = "神よ、滅茶苦茶だ...3分で着く。",--Jesus, the devastation....with you in 3.
plt_as1_01_02 = "3分だ。空を見とくんだな。",--Three minutes out. You should see things from up here.
plt_as1_01_03 = "マジかよ。街がボロボロだ。今向かってる、3分だ。",--Oh man. City is fucked. On my way, three minutes.
plt_as1_02_01 = "緊急サービスの奴らがこのヘリに被災者を乗せろとか言ってやがる。2分で着く。",--Emergency services are trying to commandeer my chopper for evacs. I'll be there in 2.
plt_as1_02_02 = "このヘリを救護に使えなんて圧力をかけてきやがる。だがクソみたいな見返りだ。2分で着くぞ。",--Under pressure here to turn the chopper over to medical evac. But they pay shit. I'll be there in 2.
plt_as1_02_03 = "権力者が俺のヘリを救助用に使わせようとしてる。だが被災者を助けたところで見返りは少ねえ。あと2分だ。",--Authorities are trying to boost my bird. But injured civs don't pay so well. I'll be with you in 2.
plt_as1_03_01 = "塵まみれだ。見えねえ、クソ。あと1分だ。",--Dust is thick. Hard to see shit. I'm one minute out.
plt_as1_03_02 = "すげぇ壊れっぷりだな。あと1分で着く。",--The wreckage is incredible. I'm a minute away from you.
plt_as1_03_03 = "元通りにするのに何年もかかるなこりゃ。あと1分だ、支度しとけ。",--It'll take years to rebuild this. Just one minute, be ready.
plt_as1_04_01 = "オーケー、フレアを確認した。降下を開始する。",--Okay. I see the flare. Starting descent.
plt_as1_04_02 = "フレアが見えた! 俺は進入中だ。",--I see the flare! I'm coming in.
plt_as1_04_03 = "わかった、あれだな。降下を開始する。",--All right, there's the flare. Beginning descent.
vld_as1_01_01 = "つながってるのか?もしもーし...クソピエロ共返事しろ! 聞こえてるか!",--Is this on? Hello...where are those fucking clow - oh, there you are!
vld_as1_01_02 = "マイクテストマイクテスト...1、2...メアリーは子羊と獣姦した...おぉ、お前ら!",--Testing, testing...One, two...Mary fucked a little lamb. Oh, you there!
vld_as1_01_03 = "クソッタレからの電話だクソ。やあ我が友よ",--Fucking phones are fucked. Ah, my friends!
vld_as1_02_01 = "この仕事は重要だ。トラックの中の金庫を持ってこい...無事にな。聞いてるか?",--This job is important. The safes in those trucks, you need to get them out...uh, safely. You hear?
vld_as1_02_02 = "よく聞け。どの金庫も回収しなきゃならん。俺をがっかりさせるんじゃないぞ。",--Listen closely. Every single one of those safes needs to be recovered. You can't let me down on.
vld_as1_02_03 = "耳かっぽじって聞け。金庫はトラックの中だ。俺には全て必要だ。無傷で持ってこい。$NL;今度は耳を近づけて聞け。金庫を手に入れろ。",--Open ears. The safes are in the trucks. I need every single one to come out. Safely. Now, close ears. Get safes.
vld_as1_03_01 = "ピエロ共、急げ! トラックを探せ! 大きくて緑色でタイヤが付いてる...これら全部だ!",--Come on, clowns! Find the trucks! Big, green, wheels..the whole thing!
vld_as1_03_02 = "景色に見とれてないでトラックを探せ!",--Stop admiring the sights and find those trucks!
vld_as1_03_03 = "テメェはケツの穴で太陽とおしゃべりしてるのか? トラックだ、分かったな?!",--Hey, you assholes taking some sun? The trucks, remember?!
vld_as1_04_01 = "すぐにトラックの荷台をを開けろ! ケツの穴ほじってるんじゃねぇ!",--Pop those trucks open! Get fingers out of assholes!
vld_as1_04_02 = "荷台を切って開けろ、わが友よ。",--Slice those trucks open, my friends.
vld_as1_04_03 = "ピエロ共、急げ! トラックを開けろ!",--Come on, clowns, get the trucks open!
vld_as1_05_01 = "よし、いいぞ! これは金庫だ。俺の赤ちゃん...それも400lbの元気な赤子だ。そのまま持ち運んだら背骨が折れちまう。運搬手段を探せ。",--Yes! Good, there are the safes. My babies. My 400lb babies. They'll break your backs if you try to carry them away. Look for a transport.
vld_as1_05_02 = "これらが金庫だ。なんて美しいんだ。安全な場所まで移してくれ。周りを見渡せ。",--There are the safes. How beautiful they are. You will need transport to get them out safely. Look around.
vld_as1_05_03 = "ハハー、金庫だ。貴重品だ。安全に持ち出してくれ。運搬手段を探せ。",--Ahhh, the safes. My precious little. Bring them safely out. Find a transport.
vld_as1_08_01 = "ハッハー! ロサンゼルス! プール、映画スター...ヤク中、砕けた夢の数々...大好きだぜ",--Ahhh! LA! Swimming pools, movie stars...coke habits, shattered dreams. I love it.
vld_as1_08_02 = "今回の地震が大きいってのは確かだ。マグニチュード8.8だ。俺は科学者じゃないが、LAがクソってのは俺でもわかる。ハッハッハ!",--They're saying it was the Big One. 8.8 magnitude. I'm not a scientist, but I think that means LA's fucked. Haha!
vld_as1_08_03 = "カリフォルニアが太平洋に沈んじまう。そして金庫は海に浮かない。",--California is sinking into the Pacific. And those safes don't float.
vld_as1_08_04 = "カリフォルニアは無礼だ。DCのマナーをいくつか教えてやる。",--These Californians are so rude. Teach them some DC manners.
vld_as1_08_05 = "奴ら、数週間後に瓦礫とサツ共の死体の山を掘る羽目になるな!",--They'll be digging chunks of cop out of the rubble for weeks!
vld_as1_08_06 = "誰が一番力持ちなんだ? さあ、誰が上手く運べるかVladおじさんに見せてくれ!",--Who has the strongest back? Come on, show your Uncle Vlad how well you can carry!
vld_as1_08_07 = "金庫を持ってここから去るんだ。「余震」があるかもしれないからな?",--I want those safes out of here. What if there is an aftershock?
vld_as1_08_08 = "西海岸から東海岸へ金庫のバトントスだ!",--Bringing west coast safes to my east coast players!
vld_as1_08_09 = "お前らがロスの新しいスーパースターだ! ルックスも良くて....自分で危険なスタントだって出来るんだぜ!",--You guys are going to be LA's latest superstars. Good-looking, dangerous..and even do your own stunts!
vld_as1_08_10 = "お前らは自分のラインを知ってる。それは俺も知ってる。ハッハー、スプートニクソさ!",--You guys know your lines. The lines I know. Yeah, fucking sputnik! Haha!
vld_as1_08_11 = "お前達、Badasses oscarのクルーになって最高のパフォーマンスを披露できそうだな!",--You guys are in the running for a Best Performance By A Crew Of Badasses oscar.
vld_as1_08_12 = "見ろよあの瓦礫、火災、悲鳴。何かあったらもっと好きになりそうだ! ハッハー!",--Look at all this fucked up concrete. The fires. The screaming. If anything, I like the place more! Haha!
vld_as1_08_13 = "この災害でどれくらいガイコツが見つかるだろうな",--How many skeletons will be getting thrown up with this earthquake.
vld_as1_08_14 = "西海岸に特別なカスタマイズを行なう奴が居るんだが、そいつは東海岸で俺の部下にした。大した者だぜ! 俺のやり方だ!",--This West Coast crew specialises in shifting huge numbers of customisations, stored in safes. They made me their man on the East Coast. It's a big deal! My way in!
vld_as1_09_01 = "爆発物を恥じるな、友よ。C4は良いぞ。C4は友達だ、いいな?",--Don't be shy of the explosives, friends. C4 good. C4 is friend, yes?
vld_as1_09_02 = "なんで誰もC4を取らない? Vladが失望するぞ。",--Why is no-one getting the C4? Makes no sense to Vlad.
vld_as1_09_03 = "C4を恐れるな。それは勝手に爆発しない。Vladはイカレてる..",--Don't be afraid of the C4. It won't explode. Well, not yet. Vlad is funny..
vld_as1_10_01 = "そのC4? 小さい赤ちゃんのようなもんだ。それを愛し、育て...壁に貼り付けて、吹っ飛ばす! ああ。",--That C4? Pretend it is poor lost baby. Love it, nurture it....then put it on wall and blow it up! Yes.
vld_as1_10_02 = "地震でいくつか壁が立ち塞がってる...取り除かなきゃならん。このクソッタレを吹き飛ばせ。",--Few walls left standing after the earthquake...had to be these ones. Blow the fucking things.
vld_as1_10_03 = "壁のようなものが立ち塞がってて進めない、そうなんだろ?",--You're not going to let a little thing like a wall stand in your way, are you?
vld_as1_11_01 = "いいぞ、最初のトラックは空だ。後ろに下がれそうな感じか?",--Great. That's the first truck emptied. How are your backs feeling?
vld_as1_11_02 = "あー、最初のトラックは空だ。いい眺めだ。金庫はそんなに重くない、そうだろう?",--Ah, the first truck to be emptied. Beautiful sight. Safes aren't too heavy, are they?
vld_as1_12_01 = "これでどれくらいだ?4分の1?よし、続けろ",--How many safes is that? A quarter? Keep going.
vld_as1_12_02 = "お前らの筋肉が痛いのは分かるが、金庫を運び続けろ。",--I know you're muscles are aching, but keep lifting those safes.
vld_as1_12_03 = "金庫はとても重い、その位は俺も分かるが、筋トレに丁度いい。",--The safes are heavy, yes I know, but this is good exercise.
vld_as1_13_01 = "半分の金庫をトラックに積んだ。残り半分だ!",--That's half of the safes out of the trucks. Half way there!
vld_as1_13_02 = "まだ逃げるなよ。いいな?",--Don't slacken off now, yes?
vld_as1_13_03 = "いいぞ、良いぞ。",--Good, good.
vld_as1_14_01 = "お前らの手足がガタガタ言ってるな。だが、まだ手離すなよ。",--Your limbs must be screaming now. But not as much as if you stop grabbing those safes.
vld_as1_14_02 = "もうすぐだ。4分の3は運び終わったぞ。続けろ! お前らのこと信じてるからな!",--So close now. That looks like three-quarters of the safes out of the truck. Keep going! I believe in you!
vld_as1_14_03 = "いいか、まだ逃げるなよ。",--Good, good. Don't surrender now.
vld_as1_15_01 = "陸路は危険すぎる。ヘリをそっちに戻す。お前らの場所を知らせるためにフレアを焚くんだ!",--Not going to risk driving them out. Got the pilot headed back, but he can't see you cos of all the dust and smoke. Light a flare for him!
vld_as1_15_02 = "道路は救急車とその他もろもろで、スシ詰め状態だ。空路を使う。パイロットに位置を知らせるフレアを焚け。",--The roads are too damned jammed with useless things like ambulances, and other shit like that. We're flying you out. Light a flare so the pilot can see you.
vld_as1_15_03 = "この貴重な金庫を陸路で運ぶのは危険すぎる。運搬用のヘリを送るぞ。$NL;そうだ、パイロットからはそっちが見えない。彼のためにフレアを焚け。",--Those safes are too precious to risk on these roads, so I'm sending in a chopper. Thing is, pilot can't see a damn thing. You need to drop a flare for him.
vld_as1_16_01 = "おい、何をグズグズ待ってるんだ? トラックに乗れ!",--Come on, what the fuck are you waiting for? Get in the truck!
vld_as1_16_02 = "金庫はトラックの中にあるが、まだお前らが乗ってない。Vladおじさん悲しいぞ。悲しくて気が狂いそうだ!",--The safes are loaded but you're not. This makes Vlad sad, and sad Vlad's getting mad!
vld_as1_16_03 = "トラックに乗るんだ! 中にお菓子が入ってるぞ!",--Get in the truck, all of you. There's cookies and candy inside, I promise.
vld_as1_17_01 = "お前らをアテにして良かったぞ、わが友よ!",--I knew I could count on you, my friends!
vld_as1_17_02 = "カリフォルニアドリームだ、友人よ! 金、盗品、そして銃、そして...いい一日だ!",--California dreaming, my friends! Dreaming of money, and loot, and guns, and....it's a great day!
vld_as1_17_03 = "母なる自然さえVladとPAYDAYギャングを止めることはできなかった!",--Even Mother Nature couldn't stop Vlad Or the Payday gang!
vld_as1_cbf_01_01 = "俺は西海岸最大のシンジケートと取引をした、その金庫を東海岸に売りさばく。だが残念ながらその最初の運送でトラブルが起きた―クソったれな大地震だ! 信じれるか!? その場に出向いて、金庫を持ってきてくれ! カリフォルニアなんてクソったれだ!",--I've struck a deal with the biggest syndicate on the west Coast, selling their safes on the east Coast. Unfortunately, first shipment of safes ran into a little trouble - a fucking earthquake! Can you believe that!? Get out there, ensure those safes are recovered. Fuck California.
vld_as1_cnc_01_01 = "",--Friends, how would you like an all-expenses paid trip to LA? Sounds good, yes?! And, while you're there....
vld_as1_cnc_01_02 = "",--My friends. I would like to treat you to a little trip to Los Angeles. Maybe do a little job for me there, yes?
vld_as1_cnc_01_03 = "",--My darling friends. I have a little trouble out in LA. Nothing too big. Just a little trouble. You fix for me, yes?
be1_fwb_01_01 = "",--When that fat bail-out comes through, I'm gonna buy another house. Somewhere to hide when the Feds come. And they will.
be1_fwb_01_02 = "",--When that fat bail-out comes through, I'll maybe buy a boat. Always wanted to sail the Spanish Main.
be1_fwb_01_03 = "",--When I get my hands on that bailout money, I'm going to Vegas to hit the ass and the blow. Like a fucking legend!
be1_fwb_01_04 = "",--Soon as the money goes through, gonna smoke me the fattest fucking blunt you ever saw.
be1_fwb_01_05 = "",--When I get that bonus, it's gonna be time to party. Cabo San fucking Lucas, baby!
be1_fwb_01_06 = "",--When my bonus comes through, I'll finally be able to get that guitar. The one Hendrix used. You know, to spank Elvis with.
be1_fwb_01_07 = "",--When that bail-out money comes through, I'm plating my desk in goooooooooold.
be1_fwb_01_08 = "",--Soon as the bail money gets here, I'm getting balls deep in high class booty!
be1_fwb_01_09 = "",--Dude, as soon as the government bail-out arrives, shit, I'm buying Detroit!
be1_fwb_01_10 = "",--Always wanted a helicopter. When the bail-out money arrives, I'm buying two.
be1_fwb_01_11 = "",--When we score that government bail-out, I'm moving to that island with the dinosaurs.
be1_fwb_02_01 = "",--Uh....that's great. Yeah, I might do a bit like that too.
be1_fwb_02_02 = "",--Well....I guess that makes sense. I may do that too.
be1_fwb_02_03 = "",--Oh....Uh, yeah. Well, I guess that would be...prudent.
be1_fwb_02_04 = "",--Oh...yeah. That sounds like a good idea. I guess.
be1_fwb_02_05 = "",--Oh, really? Well, you think...maybe I should too.
be1_fwb_02_06 = "",--That sounds sensible. Yeah. Maybe I'll put a little aside for that.
be1_fwb_02_07 = "",--Uhhh, yeah. You know, fuck it. I'll do that too!
be2_fwb_01_01 = "",--I appreciate that times are difficult. First World Bank truly does. But, with regret, we cannot sanction the loan of $10,000 on a promise to pay it back when "Fat Pat's" insurance comes through.
be2_fwb_01_02 = "",--I'm sorry. We're not able to offer unguided tours of the premises, and especially not "the room where all the money's kept".
be2_fwb_01_03 = "",--No, this isn't that kind of bank. I think you want the one attached to the hospital. Or that bar down the road.
be2_fwb_01_04 = "",--I'm sorry. No. I don't think the pigs would appreciate that. Even if they're dead.
be2_fwb_01_05 = "",--I'm afraid not. We cannot sanction a loan to buy out our bank.
be2_fwb_01_06 = "",--Unfortunately, I have doubts that you are serious about your plan to market and manufacture something like "Fart Crackers".
be2_fwb_01_07 = "",--Unfortunately, we cannot extend your credit line to cover incidental costs like "hookers and blow".
be2_fwb_01_08 = "",--I'm sorry, but I don't think there is much demand for confederate flag bedsheets.
be2_fwb_02_01 = "",--That's pretty sweet. I dunno what I'll spend mine on. Maybe invest it in a long-term CD.
be2_fwb_02_02 = "",--I like the sound of that. I think I'll put mine in my 401k.
be2_fwb_02_03 = "",--That sounds like fun. I think I'll pay off my parents mortgage.
be2_fwb_02_04 = "",--That sounds great. I am going to pay off my credit cards, put a little into a savings account.
be2_fwb_02_05 = "",--Hey, that's awesome! I'm investing in Indian steel.
be2_fwb_02_06 = "",--Great! I think I'll just keep mine in the bank.
be2_fwb_02_07 = "",--That's wonderful! I'm thinking of sharing it with friends and family.
bm_fwb_01_01 = "",--She doesn't? Well, how does she keep in touch with rest of the world?
bm_fwb_01_02 = "",--That's priceless!
bm_fwb_01_03 = "",--Yeah, a loan for heating! So I said, "can't the orphans just huddle closer together?"
bm_fwb_01_04 = "",--Yeah, hahaha. Yeah, told 'em it was an "accounting error".
bm_fwb_01_05 = "",--Well, you know how it is, you smile, nod. But they sign on the line...and you have their soul!
bm_fwb_01_06 = "",--First thing I did when that bail-out came through was buy a Longfellow. Hey, I'm supporting the auto-industry!
bm_fwb_01_07 = "",--Told a guy who wanted a loan we couldn't under FTS regulations. FTS? Fuck. That. Shit!
bm_fwb_01_08 = "",--Student comes in, looking to renegotiate their loan. I know! Hahahahaha. What an idiot!
bm_fwb_01_09 = "",--Hey, good work on that report!
bm_fwb_01_10 = "",--How long did that report take? An hour? Bill them for ten.
bm_fwb_01_11 = "",--So me and the guys took the Longfellow up the coast. Hit a hundred on the i-95. Hit a schoolbus too. Screw those kids!
bm_fwb_01_12 = "",--You see that one asking for the loan for the pasta restaurant? Sure would like to make a deposit there.
bm_fwb_01_13 = "",--So they took me into HR up at head office again. Turns out you can't tell a grandmother to suck a bag of...shit, they might be listening.
bm_fwb_01_14 = "",--Spent the weekend polishing the Longfellow. Took the chief's wife out for a spin. Let her polish the.. you know it, man!
bm_fwb_02_01 = "",--Look, Mother Superior, you either pay the $300, or we're breaking your legs!
bm_fwb_02_02 = "",--I don't care if your crippled kids have dip-fucking-theria!
bm_fwb_02_03 = "",--You want charity? You're gonna get it, 'cos you're headed right to welfare, sister!
bm_fwb_02_04 = "",--Look, you pay back the loan, or you lose the house. I mean it, mom!
bm_fwb_02_05 = "",--I understand we offered you those terms under the Veteran program, but we no longer recognise the Vietnam "incident" as a real conflict!
bm_fwb_02_06 = "",--Yeah, it's standard. 15 working days to make an international transfer. Uh-huh. Well, screw you very much too!
bm_fwb_02_07 = "",--I think we can make more cuts, yeah. We don't need all these tellers. Who gives a rats ass if people queue for an hour!
bm_fwb_02_08 = "",--I could give two shits about your college tuition. Well, if you paid me $50k per shit.
bm_fwb_02_09 = "",--How many times have I got to tell you - we're a bank. We're not supposed to be trusted.
bm_fwb_03_01 = "",--It's a pleasure to talk to the Financial Times in London. Oh, London, Kentucky.
bm_fwb_03_02 = "",--Well, I would describe my management style as bringing a new synergy to the boardroom dynamic of parallel....styling.
bm_fwb_03_03 = "",--The financial world has never been healthier! We only laid off ten employees in the last day.
bm_fwb_03_04 = "",--Investing in a bank is safe as houses. And I mean nice houses, with bricks and everything!
bm_fwb_03_05 = "",--Yes, I assure your readers that the First World Bank is here to stay. We have strong investments the in Colombian submarine industry.
bm_fwb_03_06 = "",--Our competitors were hit hard in the crunch, but we weathered most of it, since our Chairman buried the money in his yard.
bm_fwb_03_07 = "",--I can't comment on the rumors of investment from a Chinese bank, but I for one would welcome our Asian overlords.
bm_fwb_03_08 = "",--Of course we have a very diverse workforce. In fact, I just got out of a conference with our Latin division. "Empty the bin, Miguel," I said.
bm_fwb_04_01 = "",--Hey! what are you doing in here!?
bm_fwb_04_02 = "",--Security? Security!
bm_fwb_04_03 = "",--Stay where you are, I'm calling security!
fe1_fwb_01_01 = "",--No, I don't think we can put money into that idea. Cars with five wheels ain't gonna be 25% faster.
fe1_fwb_01_02 = "",--Well, I think a 100ft statue to Lincoln is fine, but having him crapping on the southern states....I don't think so.
fe1_fwb_01_03 = "",--You want a loan to.....invade Jamaica...and rule it as Great Emperor. *long sigh* I don't think so.
fe1_fwb_01_04 = "",--A loan....for a documentary exposing crooked banking practices? Riiiiight.
fe1_fwb_01_05 = "",--I'm sorry, I don't think providing a loan, to buy guns, to rob a bank, is very sensible.
fe1_fwb_01_06 = "",--You want a loan to rename the Wizards? Back to...the Bastards? I don't think that's correct.
fe1_fwb_01_07 = "",--Personally, I would love to see a wall built across the Canadian border, but the bank can't finance that.
fe1_fwb_01_08 = "",--I'm sorry, but we don't provide loans without capital, and your favorite socks aren't that. No matter how long you've owned them.
fe1_fwb_01_09 = "",--I'm sorry. It doesn't matter how good it would taste, it's scientifically impossible to breed a cow with a chicken. Loan declined.
fe1_fwb_02_01 = "",--Yes. But no. Very definitely no.
fe1_fwb_02_02 = "",--Tempting. But no.
fe1_fwb_02_03 = "",--For the thousandth time, we're not interested.
fe1_fwb_02_04 = "",--Listen to my lips....no!
fe1_fwb_02_05 = "",--Please, step away.
fe1_fwb_02_06 = "",--Have you tried Robert's?
fe1_fwb_02_07 = "",--Perhaps you should apply at the Benevolent Bank.
fe1_fwb_02_08 = "",--Have you considered asking at Harvest and Trustee?
fe2_fwb_01_01 = "",--First World Bank, can I help you? Yes sir, we offer a full range of financial services. No sir, not that kind of "fine" and definitely not that kind of service! Good day!
fe2_fwb_01_02 = "",--This is First World Bank. Yes, ma'am, you can deposit that here. Yes, we have a very secure vault. Yes, ma'am, even *those* kind of people bank here.
fe2_fwb_01_03 = "",--You're through to First World Bank. No ma'am, Troy Templeton does not really work here. That was just a commercial. I know it's upsetting.
fe2_fwb_01_04 = "",--First World Bank, can I help you? Yes, Mr Trump. A $10 loyalty bonus to your servants, sir. I'm sure they'll be very happy, sir.
fe2_fwb_01_05 = "",--This is First World Bank. No, sir, unfortunately the ATM's do not have a code you can hack.
fe2_fwb_01_06 = "",--This is First World Bank. Oh yes, ma'am, we accept any amount of gold, gems, cash or souls!
fe2_fwb_01_07 = "",--First World Bank. Hello, can I help you? Hello? Are you having trouble breathing? Mr Sheen, do we have to talk about this again!?
fe2_fwb_01_08 = "",--Hello, First World Bank. Of course! The current stock value is why don't you call back in an hour?
fe2_fwb_01_09 = "",--This is First World Bank. We have offices in Washington, London, Bogota and Karachi.
fe2_fwb_01_10 = "",--You're through to First World Bank. Yes sir, that's right - a free shotgun when you open an account!
fe2_fwb_01_11 = "",--Hello, First World Bank. No sir, I appreciate the offer but I think you'll find, in the small print, that we screw you. Hard!
fe2_fwb_01_12 = "",--Hello, First World Bank. Of course we can arrange a loan to send your first born to college. After all, we own them.
ism_fwb_01_01 = "",--Can you hear me? The gates require a keycode. Can't use mine or I'm dead, so you need to find a 4-digit code.
ism_fwb_01_02 = "",--Uh, is this on? I can get you through the gates, but only after you find a 4-digit keycode. We can't use mine, or they'll know it was me.
ism_fwb_01_03 = "",--Hello? I can open the gates, but we can't go using my code on the keypad. You need to find another.
ism_fwb_02_01 = "",--I'm coming in the elevator. Meet you up at the gates.
ism_fwb_02_02 = "",--Coming from floor 2, heading to the gates. See you there.
ism_fwb_02_03 = "",--I'm in the elevator and will be headed straight for the gates. Meet you there.
ism_fwb_03_01 = "",--The manager asked me to tell you to do the rounds. I'll be here for a while. Go on now.
ism_fwb_03_02 = "",--My clients are ready to enter the vault. You're not needed here right now. Go for a walk or something.
ism_fwb_03_03 = "",--You guys can take a smoke break, or grab a coffee. I'll be here for a while.
ism_fwb_04_01 = "",--Ready whenever you are. I'm at the gates.
ism_fwb_04_02 = "",--I'm at the security checkin by the gates. Come see me.
ism_fwb_04_03 = "",--Okay. I'm at the gates. Meet me there.
ism_fwb_04_04 = "",--Hey, I'm at the gates. Get over here.
ism_fwb_04_05 = "",--I'm waiting at the gates. Hurry up.
ism_fwb_04_06 = "",--Get over to the gates. Let's get this done.
ism_fwb_04_07 = "",--The guards are gone. Get to the gates.
ism_fwb_04_08 = "",--Right, the gates are clear. Get over here.
ism_fwb_05_01 = "",--The vault is just beyond here. You got that code?
ism_fwb_05_02 = "",--The gates protect the vault area. You have the code, right?
ism_fwb_05_03 = "",--Okay, the code will open these gates. The vault is on the other side.
ism_fwb_06_01 = "",--So far so good...
ism_fwb_06_02 = "",--Looks good...
ism_fwb_06_03 = "",--It's an older code, but it checks out...
ism_fwb_07_01 = "",--Okay. Time to get to the front and act normal.
ism_fwb_07_02 = "",--It's open. And I didn't see anything.
ism_fwb_07_03 = "",--You're through. But I saw nothing, right?
ism_fwb_08_01 = "",--You guys all done? All right, follow me.
ism_fwb_08_02 = "",--So..that's it? You got what you came for? Come on, follow me.
ism_fwb_08_03 = "",--Right, follow me and we'll get you out. Hope you got what you wanted.
ism_fwb_09_01 = "",--You got it? Nevermind, I don't want to know. Just follow me.
ism_fwb_09_02 = "",--So did you...? Better not tell me. Less I know, y'know? Come on.
ism_fwb_09_03 = "",--I guess that you..? Wait, tell me nothing. I'm just an innocent bystander. This way.
ism_fwb_10_01 = "",--Through here. Through the next office, and work your way down. Good luck.
ism_fwb_10_02 = "",--All right. Head through the opposite office, and then head down. Come on, get out of here.
ism_fwb_10_03 = "",--Just head through here and pass through the office on the other side. Make your way down to the basement. Hurry!
ism_fwb_11_01 = "",--I didn't agree to this! I'm out of here!
ism_fwb_11_02 = "",--What the fuck? We didn't even get close!
ism_fwb_11_03 = "",--What? Oh, come on! I'm out of here!
ism_fwb_12_01 = "",--We were close, but....time to bail. Still get my cut, right?
ism_fwb_12_02 = "",--We got pretty far, but I gotta scram. You guys give me my cut later, right?
ism_fwb_12_03 = "",--Almost had it, but...nevermind. I gotta bail. I still get my cut, right?
mc1_fwb_01_01 = "",--So what you're telling me is, if I have this straight, what you're saying, is that you ain't interested in investing in a pager business?
mc1_fwb_01_02 = "",--Now, if I understand you, you don't want to give me some money to provide capital for an operation running smokes out of Mexico?
mc1_fwb_01_03 = "",--Okay. So. Let me see if I understand you, you aren't interested in funding my idea for a tv show - Pig Brother?
mc1_fwb_01_04 = "",--Now, if I understand. As it pertains to my business idea for free bar for my friends, your answer is no?
mc1_fwb_01_05 = "",--So, let me get this straight - I want to build a tower to the moon, and you say no?
mc1_fwb_01_06 = "",--So. All right. You're sure? You don't wanna invest in a campaign to make bananas less banana shaped?
mc1_fwb_01_07 = "",--Now, okay. If I hear ya right, it's a no on a loan to buy a salad bar called Boogers?
mc1_fwb_01_08 = "",--Okay. Let me get this straight. You ain't gonna loan me the money to turn my car into a submarine?
mc1_fwb_01_09 = "",--So. Business plan to observe myself eating lobster and drinking champagne for sixty years? It's a no. Not even for science?!
mc1_fwb_02_01 = "",--Oh. You're sure? 'Cos I kind of spent the money already.
mc1_fwb_02_02 = "",--Uh...I can't change your mind? What if you...look into my eyes!
mc1_fwb_02_03 = "",--I think you're pissing up the wrong tree here.
mc1_fwb_02_04 = "",--You're missing out on a golden opportunity.
mc1_fwb_02_05 = "",--This could have been your chance to make at least...a billion dollars!
mc1_fwb_02_06 = "",--What if I come back? And bring salsa!
mc1_fwb_02_07 = "",--I was hoping you'd say yes. The money could get my underwear back.
mc1_fwb_02_08 = "",--Was banking on you saying yes. I'll try again later.
mc1_fwb_02_09 = "",--Damn. Was kinda banking on you saying yeah.
pln_fwb_brf_01_01 = "",--The vault is buried deep in the back of the bank. Getting through to it will be tough, but we have some help. An Inside Man is prepped and waiting for you. They're going to help us out once you're in there. You can do this loud, or you can take it softly. Up to you.
pln_fwb_cbf_01_01 = "",--We've been eyeing the First World Bank for a while. Now it's time to pull the trigger. Get down there and relieve them of their ill-gotten gains.$NL;$NL;» Locate the manager$NL;» Get access to the server room$NL;» Force your way to the vault$NL;» Bag all the money and escape
pln_fwb_cbf_01_02 = "",--First World Bank was one of those bloodsuckers that got a fat, tax-payer funded bailout deal. Making healthy profits since. Let's do this for the people.
pln_fwb_cbf_01_03 = "俺たちは何年もいろんな銀行を襲ったが、First World Bankはいつも記憶に強く残ってる。さあ中へ入ろう。台無しにしてやれ。",--We've hit a lot of banks over the years, but First World Bank has always been close to my heart. Let's get into theirs. And tear it out.
pln_fwb_cnc_01_01 = "すべての始まりの場所に戻ってきたな。First World Bankに。",--Back to where it all began. First World Bank.
pln_fwb_cnc_01_02 = "懐かしの仕事だギャングども。First World Bankだ。",--Classic job, gang. The First World Bank.
pln_fwb_cnc_01_03 = "First World Bankに仕掛ける時が来た、ギャング共。",--Time to hit the First World Bank, gang.
pln_fwb_intro_01_01 = "もしFirst World Bankの株を持ってたら売っとけよ。じきに買収されて苦しむことになるからな。さあ行こう。",--If you got shares in First World Bank, sell. 'Cos they're about to suffer a hostile takeover. Let's do it.
pln_fwb_intro_01_02 = "First world Bank。ヒル共の集まりだ。やってやれ。",--The First World Bank. Bunch of goddamn bloodsuckers. Go do it.
pln_fwb_intro_01_03 = "そこだ。First World Bankだ。よし、一仕事行こうじゃないか。",--Over there. The First World Bank. Okay, get out and get to work.
pln_fwb_01_01 = "銀行に入れ。",--Just walk straight into the bank.
pln_fwb_01_02 = "中に入れ。",--Go inside.
pln_fwb_01_03 = "やるべきことはわかってるな。 中に入れ。",--You know your roles. Walk inside.
pln_fwb_02_01 = "よし、ここのマネージャーを見つけろ。",--OK. Find the bank manager.
pln_fwb_02_02 = "銀行のマネージャーを見つけろ。",--We gotta find the bank manager.
pln_fwb_02_03 = "よし、まずはマネージャーのKeycardが必要になる。 そいつを見つけろ。",--Right, you're going to need the manager's keycard. Find him.
pln_fwb_03_01 = "マネージャーを見つけたら、そいつを縛り上げてKeycardを奪え。",--Find the bank manager, then tie him down and you'll get the keycard.
pln_fwb_03_02 = "いいか、銀行のマネージャーだぞ。 そいつのKeycardを奪うんだ。",--Remember: the bank manager. Get his keycard from him.
pln_fwb_03_03 = "マネージャーを見つけろ。そいつからKeycardを奪う必要がある。",--Go find the bank manager. We'll need that keycard off him.
pln_fwb_04_01 = "奴はハゲで、黒のスーツを着ている。大体いつも電話に出てる。奴は手を縛られてほしいみたいだな。",--He's balding, wears a black suit. Most likely busy on his phone. Looks like he's ready to hand out pink slips.
pln_fwb_04_02 = "銀行のマネージャーは黒のスーツを着ている。あとハゲてる。ほぼ四六時中電話で話してるキモい奴だ。",--The bank manager wears a black suit. Balding. He looks like the kind of creep who spends all day on his phone.
pln_fwb_04_03 = "マネージャーを探せ。40代で黒のスーツ、ハゲ頭だ。事務所の裏にいるだろう。",--Look out for the manager. 40's, black suit, balding. Probably around the back offices.
pln_fwb_04_04 = "マネージャーを探せ。40代半ばで、ハゲで黒のスーツを着ている。魂は無く、心も無い。貪欲な奴だ...よく知ってるだろ。",--You're looking for the manager. Mid 40's, balding, black suit. Soulless, heartless, greedy...you know the type.
pln_fwb_04_05 = "マネージャーは裏手のほうにいるだろう。奴のようなタイプは庶民なんかに時間を割かないからな。黒スーツのハゲだ。",--The manager will likely be around the back. His type don't spend much time with the plebs. Black suit, balding.
pln_fwb_04_06 = "マネージャーを探せ。スーツを着た醜い野郎だ。40代で、ハゲがかってる。そいつがそうだ。",--Find the manager. Look for the creepy guy in a suit. 40's. Going bald. That'll be him.
pln_fwb_04_07 = "マネージャーがターゲットだ。ハゲた汚ねえ中年オヤジだ。奴のKeycardを奪え。",--The manager is our target. Middle-aged creep with a bald spot. Get his keycard.
pln_fwb_04_08 = "マネージャーを探すんだ。黒のスーツの醜くて、てっぺんが薄い40代半ばの奴だ。奴のKeycardを盗れ。",--Keep an eye open for the manager. Black suited creep, losing a bit up top, mid 40's. Get his keycard.
pln_fwb_05_01 = "さあKeycardを使ってサーバー室に入れ。2階だぞ。",--Now use the keycard to get inside the server room. It's on the second floor.
pln_fwb_05_02 = "いいぞ。Keycardでサーバー室に入れ。2階だ。",--Great. Now use the card to get inside the server room. Second floor.
pln_fwb_05_03 = "よし。Keycardで2階のサーバー室に入るんだ。",--Good. Use the keycard to enter the server room on the second floor.
pln_fwb_06_01 = "金属探知機を無効にするんだ。電源を切ればいい。電気ボックスを探せ。",--You need to disable the metal detectors. Cutting their power will do the job. Look for electricity boxes.
pln_fwb_06_02 = "金属探知機をなんとかしないといけない。単に電源を落とすだけだ。そのへんに電気ボックスがあるだろ。",--We need to deal with the metal detectors. Best way: simply kill the power. There are electricity boxes around.
pln_fwb_06_03 = "金属探知機を切れ。電源を落とせばいい。電気回路ボックスを探せ。",--The metal detectors need to be shut down. You can do that by disabling the power. Look for circuit boxes.
pln_fwb_07_01 = "ギャング共。金属探知機の電源を落とせ。回路ボックスを弄るんだ。",--Gang. Shut down the power to the metal detectors. Crack open the circuit boxes.
pln_fwb_07_02 = "お前ら、金属探知機を切れ。探知機は電力をバカ食いするから電気ボックスを見つけて落とせばいい。",--Crew, you need to deal with the metal detectors. They use a lot of electricity so find and shut down the circuit boxes.
pln_fwb_07_03 = "回路ボックスはそのへんにある。電源を落とせば金属探知機を無効にできる。",--There are circuit boxes around the place. Disabling them will shut down the metal detectors.
pln_fwb_08_01 = "いいぞ、お前ら - 金属探知機は無効になった。",--Nice work, team - the metal detectors are disabled.
pln_fwb_08_02 = "これで金属探知機は切れた。よくやった。",--That disabled the metal detectors. Good job.
pln_fwb_08_03 = "これで金属探知機は電源オフだ。いいぞ。",--That's the metal detectors dealt with. Great.
pln_fwb_09_01 = "ドリルはコピー機に入ってるが、使わなくていいことを願う。いいか、その...使わざるを得ないときのためだ。",--The drill is in the copy machine here, but hopefully we won't need it. Just remember, though...if we should.
pln_fwb_09_02 = "コピー機が見えるか?そこにはこの仕事をプランBで行くためのものが入ってる。だが、そうしないでくれよな?",--See that copy machine? It has the goods should this caper go loud. But let's try and not let them happen, huh?
pln_fwb_09_03 = "そのコピー機には「もし」プランBになったときのためのものが入ってる。",--The copy machine over there has a stash of equipment *if* this caper goes loud.
pln_fwb_10_01 = "そこに内通者がいる。金庫室につながるゲートを開けてくれる。そいつにつなぐぞ。",--We got an Inside Man there. They'll be able to open the gates leading to the vault area. Patching them through now.
pln_fwb_10_02 = "俺が内通者を雇っておいた。奴が金庫へのゲートをよろこんで開けてくれる。そいつにつなぐぞ。",--I managed to get one of the employees onto our side. They willing to open the gates leading to the vault. Let me put them through.
pln_fwb_10_03 = "内通者を取っておいた。そいつが金庫につながるゲートを開けてくれる。そいつにつなぐぞ。",--I got an Inside Man there. They'll help us get through to the gates leading to the vault. Patching them through now.
pln_fwb_11_01 = "聞いただろ。俺がちょっくら4ケタのコードが入ってそうな端末に印を付けておいた。",--You heard her. I've done a little homework and marked some terminals that should have the 4-digit code in 'em somewhere.
pln_fwb_11_02 = "オーライ、ギャング共。コードが入ってそうな端末の目星をつけておいた。そいつらをちょっとハックしてきてくれ。",--All right, gang. I've found some terminals that might have a suitable code. I need you to run a little hack on them.
pln_fwb_11_03 = "あのレディが言ったように、俺が印を付けておいた端末を調べるんだ。どれかにコードが入ってるはずだ。",--As the lady said, get searching these terminals I marked. One of them is bound to have the code we need.
pln_fwb_12_01 = "印の付いた端末をチェックしろ、ギャング共。コードを探せ。",--Check the marked terminals, gang. We're looking for a code.
pln_fwb_12_02 = "端末だ。見えるだろ?そいつらからコードを探すんだ。",--The terminals. You see 'em? You need to check them for the code.
pln_fwb_12_03 = "ゲートのコードが必要なんだ、お前ら。端末を調べてくれ。",--We need the gate code, crew. Get searching those terminals.
pln_fwb_13_01 = "オーライ、中身はなんだ。",--All right, let's see what we got.
pln_fwb_13_02 = "さあ、何が入ってるかな?",--Now, what will we find?
pln_fwb_13_03 = "オーケー、アクセスする...",--Okay, searching...
pln_fwb_13_04 = "よし、何が出るかな...",--Come on, let me see what you got...
pln_fwb_13_05 = "アクセス中だ...",--Acessing now...
pln_fwb_13_06 = "たぶんこいつだ。",--This might be the one.
pln_fwb_13_07 = "こいつであることを祈っとけ。",--Fingers crossed this is the one
pln_fwb_13_08 = "ちょっと待ってくれよ...",--Give me a second to check...
pln_fwb_14_01 = "アカウント報告か。だがコードは無い。次だ。",--Account reports. But no codes. Try the next one.
pln_fwb_14_02 = "マジか、オフィスゴシップだらけだ、だがコードは無い。次。",--Christ, a lot of office gossip, but no codes. Next.
pln_fwb_14_03 = "借り入れ申請書か。許可したぞ! だがコードは無しだ。次。",--Credit applications. Accepted! No codes though. Next one.
pln_fwb_14_04 = "学生ローンを消してやった! だがコードは無い。別のやつだ。",--Student loan erased! But no codes. Try another.
pln_fwb_14_05 = "担保の差し押さえ、無しにしてやった! だがコードは無い。",--Mortgage foreclosures revoked! No codes though.
pln_fwb_14_06 = "CD利子率、50%だぜ! だがコードは無い。探し続けろ。",--CD interest rate, 50%! But no code. Keep looking.
pln_fwb_14_07 = "この譲渡額に0を1つ増やしてやった! だがコードは無い。次。",--Extra zero on this transfer! But no code. Try another.
pln_fwb_14_08 = "クレジットスコア、8-50だ! だがコードは無い。探せ。",--Credit score, eight-fifty! But no codes. Keep looking.
pln_fwb_15_01 = "そして... コードは1138だ",--Aaand here we go: The code is... 1138.
pln_fwb_15_02 = "コードは1138だ",--Here's the code. 1138.
pln_fwb_15_03 = "コードは...1138だ!",--And the code is....1138!
pln_fwb_16_01 = "ゲートを通るのに必要なものは手に入れた。さあ、内通者と落ち合え。",--We got what we need to get through the gate. Now, meet with the Insider.
pln_fwb_16_02 = "オーケー、内通者と会うんだ。ゲートに向かえ。",--Okay, now you can meet with the Insider. Get to the gates.
pln_fwb_16_03 = "よし。内通者と会え。彼女がゲートを開けてくれる。",--Great. Now head to the Insider. She'll be able to open the gates.
pln_fwb_17_01 = "コードを入力しろ。",--Enter the code.
pln_fwb_17_02 = "コードを打ち込め。",--Punch in the code.
pln_fwb_18_01 = "いよいよ、金庫へ侵入するぞ。扉は2つのKeycard端末で制御されていて、数秒以内に2つを認証しないといけない。Keycardを2枚探すんだ。",--Next, we need to gain access to the main vault. It's controlled by two keycard terminals, and each needs activating within seconds of the other. So find two keycards.
pln_fwb_18_02 = "さあ金庫の扉を通るぞ。一定時間内に2つのKeycard端末を認証させないといけない。2枚のKeycardを探せ。",--Now we need to get through the vault door. Two keycard terminals need to be activated, within a small window. Find two keycards.
pln_fwb_18_03 = "お次は金庫の扉だ。2つのKeycard端末で制御されている。両方をなる早で通すんだ、わかったか?さあKeycardを2枚探すんだ。",--Next, the vault door. It's accessed by two keycard terminals. Swipe them both ASAP. Got it? Now find two keycards.
pln_fwb_19_01 = "2枚のKeycardを探せ。机の上やオフィスを調べろ。",--You're looking for two keycards. Look around the desks, offices.
pln_fwb_19_02 = "Keycardは2枚いるぞ。探せ。",--You need a couple of keycards. Look around.
pln_fwb_19_03 = "2枚のKeycardはこのへんにあるだろう。",--The two keycards will be around here somewhere.
pln_fwb_19_04 = "ちゃんと2枚のKeycardを探してるか?",--How are you doing tracking down those two keycards?
pln_fwb_19_05 = "オフィスや机の上を調べろ、Keycardはそのへんにあるはず。",--Search the offices, desks - those keycards are around there somewhere.
pln_fwb_19_06 = "Keycard2枚だ。そのへんにあるはずだ。探せ。",--Two keycards. They'll be there somewhere, I know it. Keep looking.
pln_fwb_19_07 = "Keycardは消えたりしないぞ。どこかにあるはずだ。",--Those keycards can't have vanished. They're there somewhere.
pln_fwb_19_08 = "金庫を開けるにはKeycardが2枚いる。探し続けろ。",--We need two keycards to open the vault. Keep looking.
pln_fwb_20_01 = "オーケー、1枚目のKeycardだな。もう1枚手に入れろ。",--Okay, that's one keycard. Hunt down the other.
pln_fwb_20_02 = "そいつが1枚目のKeycardだな。2枚目はこのへんのどこかにある。",--That's the first keycard. Second one's gotta be here somewhere.
pln_fwb_20_03 = "よし。さあ2枚目のKeycardを探せ。",--Good. Now find the second keycard.
pln_fwb_21_01 = "1枚目のカードはセキュリティ端末に差し込め。で、2枚目を金庫の扉の横のキーパネルに使うんだ。制限時間は短いぞ、急げ。",--Use one of those cards on the security terminal. Then, use the second keycard on the keypanel by the vault door. There's a short window, so don't shilly-shally.
pln_fwb_21_02 = "オーケー、1枚のカードはセキュリティ室で使え。で、急いでもう1枚を金庫の扉のそばにあるパネルに使うんだ。",--Okay, now you gotta use the first card in the security room, and then you gotta be quick to swipe the second on the panel by the vault door.
pln_fwb_21_03 = "よし、1枚のカードはセキュリティ室の端末に、その後急いでもう1枚を金庫の扉の横にあるキーパネルに差し込め。もたもたしていられないぞ。",--Now use the first card on the terminal in the security room, then the second on the vault keypanel. You got a brief window, so no lollygagging.
pln_fwb_22_01 = "さあ、金庫の外のキーパネルだ! 急げ!",--Now, the keypanel outside the vault! Hurry!
pln_fwb_22_02 = "よし、金庫のキーパネルだ! やれ!",--And now the vault keypanel! Hustle!
pln_fwb_22_03 = "さあ、金庫のキーパネルに差し込め! 行け!",--Now swipe the vault keypanel! Come on!
pln_fwb_23_01 = "遅い、もう一度。",--Too slow, try again.
pln_fwb_23_02 = "ダメだ。もう一度。",--Just missed it. Try again.
pln_fwb_23_03 = "クソッ! よし、もう一回だ",--Damn! Okay, just try again.
pln_fwb_24_01 = "よし...ジャジャーン!",--And....ta-da!
pln_fwb_24_02 = "さぁて...開けゴマ!",--And...open sesame!
pln_fwb_24_03 = "そして...いっちょあがり!",--And...voila!
pln_fwb_25_01 = "ここだ。たくさん積まれてるな。ああ、お前らは強盗だろ?盗め!",--There it is. Neatly stacked. Well, you're robbers, ain't you? Get robbing!
pln_fwb_25_02 = "ああ、ここからでもカネの匂いがする! バッグに詰めろ!",--Ahhh, I can smell the wealth from here! Load the bags!
pln_fwb_25_03 = "新鮮でたくさん積まれてる。遠慮するな、ギャング共。かっさらえ!",--Crisp and neatly stacked. Don't be shy, gang. Go get it!
pln_fwb_26_01 = "おい、お前ら。中に入って中身を頂くんだ。",--Come on, crew. Get in there, grab that loot.
pln_fwb_26_02 = "金庫が開いてお前らを待ってるぞ、ギャング共。そいつらを奪ってやれ。",--The vault's open and ready for you, gang. Just grab that loot.
pln_fwb_26_03 = "ギャング共、カネがお前らを待ってるぞ。取ってこい!",--Gang, the money's there, just waiting for you. Get at it!
pln_fwb_27_01 = "カネを詰めたら、エレベーターの横の通気口に投げ込め。心配すんな。またすぐに会える。",--Once you've got your fill, throw the bags through that vent by the elevators. Don't worry. You'll see 'em again soon.
pln_fwb_27_02 = "さあ、バッグをエレベーター横の通気口に放り込め。大丈夫だ、心配すんな。",--Now, ditch the bags into the vent by the elevators. They'll be fine, don't worry.
pln_fwb_27_03 = "カネを詰めたら、ここの通気口にバッグを投げ込んでくれ。後で回収するからな。",--So when you have your fill, I need you to drop the bags into this vent here. We'll pick 'em up later.
pln_fwb_28_01 = "いいか、通気口にカネを入れるんだぞ。",--Remember, stash the loot in the vent.
pln_fwb_28_02 = "通気口にバッグを入れるんだ。",--You need to drop those bags in the vent.
pln_fwb_28_03 = "エレベーターのそばの通気口が見えるか?そこにバッグを投げ込め。",--See that vent by the elevator? That's where you gotta stash the bags.
pln_fwb_29_01 = "よし。脱出する準備はいいか?内通者に会え。彼女が逃げ道を教えてくれる。",--Great. Now, ready to bail? Just meet our Insider man. She'll show you the way out.
pln_fwb_29_02 = "帰る準備はできたか?内通者を探せ。彼女が逃げ道を作ってくれる。",--Now, you ready to call it? Find our Insider. She's going to show you a way to slip out.
pln_fwb_29_03 = "逃げる準備ができたら、内通者に会え。ここから逃げる道を教えてくれる。",--Once you're ready to bounce, find our Insider. She's going to help you slip out of there.
pln_fwb_30_01 = "内通者と会え。彼女が逃げ道を用意してある。",--Find our Insider. She'll show you out.
pln_fwb_30_02 = "内通者が逃げ道を教えてくれる。会え。",--Our Insider can show you the way out. Find her.
pln_fwb_30_03 = "内通者と落ち合え。彼女が逃げ道を確保してある。",--Meet up with the Insider. She'll get you out of there.
pln_fwb_31_01 = "姿勢を低く、静かに。無人のオフィスなんて無いだろ。",--Stay low and quiet. Offices are never empty.
pln_fwb_31_02 = "多分みんな仕事中だ。気をつけろ。",--Probably people working here. Keep an eye out.
pln_fwb_31_03 = "オフィスワーカーがいるだろう。台無しにされるなよ。",--There'll likely be workers here. Don't let them blow this.
pln_fwb_32_01 = "進み続けろ - ガレージまで降りろ。",--Keep moving - get down to the garage.
pln_fwb_32_02 = "こっそり行けよ。ガレージまで降りるんだ。",--Just sneak through. Head downstairs to the garage.
pln_fwb_32_03 = "静かにな、ギャング共、だが止まるなよ。ガレージまで降りろ。",--Keep it quiet, gang, but keep it moving. Get down to the garage.
pln_fwb_33_01 = "オーライ、トラックとバッグが待っている。トラックに積み込め、早く!",--All right, there's the truck and there's our bags. Stash the loot into the truck, quick!
pln_fwb_33_02 = "カネ回収用のゴミ収集車が待ってるぞ。行け!",--The garbage truck is waiting for the money bags, come on!
pln_fwb_33_03 = "オーケー、バッグをトラックに積み込めばこの仕事は終わりだ。",--Okay, now get those bags into the truck and we can call this one.
pln_fwb_34_01 = "よくやった! 昔ながらの強盗だな。楽しかったぞ!",--Great work! A classic takedown of a classic heist. It was a pleasure to watch!
pln_fwb_34_02 = "お前らは幽霊だな。大金持ちの幽霊だ! よくやった!",--You guys are goddamn ghosts. Considerably wealthier ghosts! Well done!
pln_fwb_34_03 = "これでどうだ! 教科書どおりだ、ギャング共! おめでとう!",--And that is how you do it! Text book execution, gang! Congratulations!
pln_fwb_35_01 = "アラームだ、紳士諸君。カウントダウンしろ。",--There's the alarm, gentlemen. Start the countdown.
pln_fwb_35_02 = "アラームだ - プランBで行くぞ。カウントダウンだ。",--That's the alarm - time for plan B. Do the countdown.
pln_fwb_35_03 = "プランBだ。カウントダウン開始。",--Time for plan B. Start the countdown.
pln_fwb_36_01 = "奴はハゲで黒のスーツを着ている。奴を怖がらせちまったみたいだから、オフィスか廊下を探せ!",--He is balding and wears a black suit. You probably scared him off, so look around the offices or in the corridors!
pln_fwb_36_02 = "マネージャーは漏らしちまっただろうな。奴を探せ。Keycardを手に入れるんだ。",--The manager's probably crapping his black threads somewhere. Find him. Get his keycard.
pln_fwb_36_03 = "銀行のマネージャーを探せ! 黒のスーツでハゲだ。奴を縛り上げてKeycardを手に入れろ。",--Find the bank manager! Black suit, balding. Tie him down - get the keycard.
pln_fwb_36_04 = "マネージャーを探せ。Keycardがいるんだ!",--Find the manager. We still need his keycard!
pln_fwb_36_05 = "いずれにせよマネージャーのKeycardがいるぞ。探せ!",--You still need to get the managers keycard. Find him!
pln_fwb_36_06 = "まだマネージャーのKeycardはいるぞ、ギャング共。奴を見つけて、奪え!",--Still need the keycard off the manager, gang. Find him, deal with him!
pln_fwb_36_07 = "マネージャーを見つけて始末しろ、ギャング共。Keycardを手に入れるんだ!",--Find and deal with the manager, crew. Gotta get that keycard!
pln_fwb_37_01 = "さあドリルとThermiteを取ってくるんだ、コピー機の中に隠してある!",--Now pick up the drill and the thermite, it's hidden inside the copy machine!
pln_fwb_37_02 = "サーバー室のコピー機にドリルとThermiteを隠してある。取りに行け!",--Got a drill and some thermite hidden in the copy machine in the server room. Go get it.
pln_fwb_37_03 = "サーバー室のコピー機にプランB用の装備が入っている。取ってこい!",--The copy machine in the server room has the Plan B equipment. Grab it!
pln_fwb_37_04 = "ドリルとThermiteを取りに行け。コピー機に隠してある。",--Go pick up the drill and thermite. It's hidden inside the copy machine.
pln_fwb_38_01 = "もう1つのThermite缶は他のやつが運ぶんだ。",--There's one more can of thermite in the copy machine but someone else needs to carry that one.
pln_fwb_38_02 = "Thermite缶は2つある。持てるのは1人につき1つだ。",--There's two cans of thermite there. One of you other guys grab it.
pln_fwb_38_03 = "もう1つThermite缶がある。誰か持て。",--There's a second can of thermite there. Someone grab it.
pln_fwb_39_01 = "もう1つThermite缶がコピー機に入ってるぞ。取りに戻る事になるかもな。",--There's one more can of thermite in the copy machine. Maybe come back for it?
pln_fwb_39_02 = "2つThermite缶がある。後で取りに戻る事になりそうだな。",--There's two cans of thermite there. Maybe you can come back later?
pln_fwb_39_03 = "もう1つThermite缶があるぞ。1つ目を置いたら取りに戻ってこれるだろう。",--There's a second can of thermite there. Perhaps you can come back once the first is burning?
pln_fwb_40_01 = "ゲートにドリルを設置しろ。",--You need to set up the drill at the gate.
pln_fwb_40_02 = "オーライ。ゲートにドリルを取り付けろ。",--All right. Get that drill set up on the gate.
pln_fwb_40_03 = "さあ、ゲートにドリルを取り付けるぞ。",--Now, let's mount the drill on the gates.
pln_fwb_41_01 = "野郎共、ゲートにドリルを設置するんだ。急げ!",--Guys, get that drill on the gate. Hurry!
pln_fwb_41_02 = "ギャング共、ドリルを設置しないと進まないぞ。",--Gang, we're going nowhere until that drill is working.
pln_fwb_41_03 = "お前ら、ゲートにドリルを付けるんだ。やれ!",--Crew, get drilling the gate. Hustle it!
pln_fwb_42_01 = "内通者がちゃんと用意してくれてたな。ドリルを見張っとけよ - 確実にジャムるからな。",--The insider sure delivered. Now keep an eye on the drill - it'll surely jam every once in a while.
pln_fwb_42_02 = "さあドリルを起動しろ。サツを近づけるな。",--Now let the drill do it's thing. Keep the cops off it.
pln_fwb_42_03 = "ゲートをドリルで開けてやれ。守れよ!",--Let the drill get through that gate lock. Protect it!
pln_fwb_43_01 = "アラームでゲートの磁気シールが作動しちまった。こいつはドリルじゃ無理だ、端末から解除しろ。",--The alarm has activated a second feature on the gate - a magnetic seal. Drill can't touch that, so you need to access a terminal to release it.
pln_fwb_43_02 = "よし野郎共 - ドリルが穴を開けてる間に、俺達はゲートの磁気シールをなんとかするぞ。ちょうどいい端末を探させてくれ。",--OK guys - while the drill does the lock, we're going to deal with the gates' magnetic seal. Let me find a good terminal.
pln_fwb_43_03 = "オーケー、アラームがゲートの第2ロックを作動させやがった - 磁気シールだ。端末から解除しないといけない。俺が探す。",--Okay, the alarm has kicked in a secondary lock on the gate - a magnetic seal. You need a terminal to release that. Let me find one.
pln_fwb_44_01 = "俺が印を付けた端末にアクセスするんだ。そいつで磁気シールを解除できる。",--Access the computer I have marked out for you. Use it to drop the magnetic seal.
pln_fwb_44_02 = "よし、印の付いた端末にいけ。そいつをハックすれば磁気シールを解除できる。",--Okay, see that terminal I marked. Get over there, hack in and let's kill that magnetic seal.
pln_fwb_44_03 = "端末を見つけた。ハックして磁気シールを解除するんだ。",--I've found a terminal. Get to it, hack in and we lower that magnetic seal.
pln_fwb_45_01 = "よし - シールを解除した。ドリルから目を離すな。ジャムったら修理するんだ。",--Good - the seal is history. Now keep watching that drill. If it jams, you need to restart it.
pln_fwb_45_02 = "シールはもう大丈夫だ。ドリルを見張っとけ。",--That's it for the seal. Now keep an eye on the drill.
pln_fwb_45_03 = "オーケー、シールは解除された。ドリルを守れ!",--Okay, the seal is down. Protect the drill!
pln_fwb_46_01 = "ドリルは終わった - ゲートが開いたぞ! さあ金庫室の廊下に向かえ。金庫の真上にある会計室を探してThermiteを注いでこい。",--The drill is done - the gates are opening! Go through and head down the vault corridor. Find the counting room right above the vault and pour out the thermite.
pln_fwb_46_02 = "よし! ゲートを抜けて金庫に向かえ。会計室を見つけてThermiteを注げ。金庫を燃やすぞ!",--Nice! Go through the gate and head to the vault. Find the counting room and pour out the thermite. We're burning down to the vault!
pln_fwb_46_03 = "いいぞ! さあ金庫の真上にある会計室に行け、そこでThermiteの出番だ!",--Great! Now get to the counting room, right above the vault, and get that thermite to work!
pln_fwb_47_01 = "金庫の上にある会計室を見つけてThermiteを撒いてこい。",--Find the counting room right above the vault and pour out the thermite.
pln_fwb_47_02 = "金庫の真上の部屋に入ってThermiteを撒け。",--Enter the room right above the vault and pour out the thermite.
pln_fwb_47_03 = "Thermiteを撒いてこい。",--Go and pour out the thermite.
pln_fwb_48_01 = "いいぞ。さあThermiteが反応しきるまで守るんだ。",--Great, now just hold the fort until the thermite is done.
pln_fwb_48_02 = "オーケー。後はThermiteが終わるのを待て。",--Okay. Now hold them off til the thermite finishes.
pln_fwb_48_03 = "オーライ。持ちこたえろよ、ギャング共。焼き溶かすのを待て。",--All right. Now bunker down, gang. Hold them off until we burn through.
pln_fwb_49_01 = "もし誰ももう1つのThermite缶を取ってないなら戻って取ってこい。量が多けりゃこの工程は短くなる。",--If none of you have picked up the extra can of thermite hidden inside the copy machine, you should go get and get it and pour it out. More thermite means faster melting process.
pln_fwb_49_02 = "誰かもう1つThermite缶を取ってないか? 2つあれば早さも2倍だぜ。",--Did any of you grab that second can? Extra thermite means extra heat which means less time.
pln_fwb_49_03 = "誰が2つ目のThermite缶を持ってるんだ? 量が多いほど熱く燃える。化学の基本だぜ。",--Who has the second thermite can? More thermite means a hotter burn. Basic chemistry.
pln_fwb_50_01 = "オーライ、Thermiteは半分終わった。燃やし続けるんだ、紳士諸君。",--All right, the thermite should be halfway done by now. Keep keepin' on, gentlemen.
pln_fwb_50_02 = "Thermiteが半分くらい反応し終わった。ブタ野郎共を近づけるな。",--Reckon that thermite is half-done. Just keep the pigs away.
pln_fwb_50_03 = "Thermiteは今半分終わったってとこだ。いいぞ。",--Thermite should be half-way through by now. You're doing great.
pln_fwb_51_01 = "計画通り、Thermiteが金庫に穴を開けてくれた。飛び降りてカネを頂け!",--The thermite has melted a hole straight into the vault, just as planned. Jump down and grab the cash!
pln_fwb_51_02 = "Thermiteが終わった - 時間だ! 金庫に入るぞ!",--The thermite's done - about time! Now enter the vault!
pln_fwb_51_03 = "オーライ! Thermiteが終わったぞ。降りろ。",--All right! Thermite's done. Now get down there.
pln_fwb_52_01 = "ほら、金庫に飛び降りろ!",--Come on, jump down into the vault!
pln_fwb_52_02 = "Thermiteが溶かした穴から飛び降りろ!",--Jump down into the hole that the thermite melted through!
pln_fwb_52_03 = "金庫に飛び降りて中身を頂け!",--Jump down into the vault and get the dough!
pln_fwb_53_01 = "どんどんバッグにカネを詰めろ!",--Put the moneybag on the floor and grab some cash!
pln_fwb_53_02 = "いいカネじゃないか。頂け、お前ら!",--There's the beautiful cash. Get bagging it, crew!
pln_fwb_53_03 = "おお、見ろよこの札束の山。よし、バッグに詰めろ、ギャング共!",--Ahhhh, look at all that cash. Okay, fill your bags, gang!
pln_fwb_54_01 = "よし、もうすぐ終わりだ。カネを取れ!",--Come on, we're almost done. Get the money!
pln_fwb_54_02 = "お前ら! 集中だ。カネのために来たんだろ、すぐそこで待ってるぞ。",--Crew! Don't lose focus. We're here for cash, and it's there for you.
pln_fwb_54_03 = "カネを詰めろ、ギャング共!",--Get bagging the money, gang!
pln_fwb_55_01 = "サツが金庫の扉のコントロールを握った。扉を開けてくるぞ - 気をつけろ!",--The cops are in control of the vault doors. They will open any second - be ready!
pln_fwb_55_02 = "クソ警官共が扉の前にいる。覚悟しろ!",--Damn cops are at the door. Get ready for them!
pln_fwb_55_03 = "サツが扉を開けるぞ。PAYDAY流にもてなしてやれ!",--Cops are about to open the door. Give them a Payday welcome!
pln_fwb_56_01 = "よくやった! 地下につながる通気口にバッグを投げ込め。",--Good job! Now drop off the loot into the vent leading into the basement area.
pln_fwb_56_02 = "よし、いいぞ! エレベーター横の通気口にバッグを入れろ!",--Okay, great! Now stash that loot in the vent by the elevators!
pln_fwb_56_03 = "オーライ、さあ通気口にバッグを入れるんだ!",--All right, now start stashing that money in the vent!
pln_fwb_57_01 = "よし、脱出プランはこうだ:サーバー室まで行って、壁をふっ飛ばし隣の建物の地下から脱出だ。",--OK, escape plan: Go up to the server room, blow up the wall and escape through the basement of the neighboring building.
pln_fwb_57_02 = "よし、脱出するぞ。上階に戻って、隣の建物の壁にC4で穴を開けるんだ。",--Right, here's our way out. Get back upstairs, and C4 the wall into the adjoining building.
pln_fwb_57_03 = "正面からは逃げられないぞ。上階に行って、隣の建物のオフィスに穴を開けるんだ。いいな。",--You're not going to just stroll out the front. Get upstairs, and blast through into the office next door. That's the way out.
pln_fwb_58_01 = "クソロビーから離れろ!",--Get out of that damn lobby!
pln_fwb_58_02 = "ああこのクソロビーめ、そこから離れろ!",--Argh this damn lobby, you gotta get out of there!
pln_fwb_58_03 = "ロビーはヤバいぞ! 上だ!",--The lobby's too hot! Get upstairs!
pln_fwb_59_01 = "上に行ってオフィスの廊下へ向かえ!",--Head upstairs to the office corridors!
pln_fwb_59_02 = "サーバー室前の廊下に向かえ!",--Go to the corridor outside the server room!
pln_fwb_59_03 = "階段を上れ、お前ら! そこで爆破するんだ!",--Get upstairs, crew! That's where you'll be blasting through!
pln_fwb_60_01 = "壁に穴を開けて駆け抜けろ!",--Blow a hole in the wall and get ready to run!
pln_fwb_60_02 = "壁にC4を取り付けろ!",--Apply some C4 to the wall!
pln_fwb_60_03 = "壁に穴を開けて逃げるぞ!",--Blow a hole in the wall and run!
pln_fwb_60_04 = "壁にC4を付けて離れろ!",--Put the C4 on the wall and stay back!
pln_fwb_61_01 = "壁にC4を設置しろ、お前ら!",--Slap some C4 on that wall, crew!
pln_fwb_61_02 = "逃げ道を作るぞ。壁にC4を取り付けろ!",--We're blasting out the back door. Get C4 on that wall!
pln_fwb_61_03 = "壁をC4で吹き飛ばせ! 逃げ道を作るぞ。",--C4 that wall, gang! We're making our own escape route.
pln_fwb_62_01 = "穴を通れ! 隣の建物に移るぞ!",--Go through the hole! Head to the neighboring building!
pln_fwb_62_02 = "そこを通れ! そこから逃げるぞ!",--Now, get through there! That's the way out!
pln_fwb_62_03 = "穴を通るんだ、ギャング共! そこから脱出だ!",--Through the hole, gang! You're getting out of there!
pln_fwb_63_01 = "ゴミ収集車が地下のガレージで待っている。降りてそいつにバッグを積めるんだ、早く!",--There's a garbage truck waiting in the basement garage. Get down there and stash the loot there, quick!
pln_fwb_63_02 = "ガレージにゴミ収集車を待たせてある。降りてバッグを確保しろ!",--The garbage truck is waiting in the garage for the money bags. Get down there, get it secured!
pln_fwb_63_03 = "このオフィスには地下ガレージがある。ゴミ収集車が待ってるぞ。降りてそいつにバッグを投げ込め!",--This office has a basement garage. A garbage truck is waiting for the bags. Get down there, and get them secured!
pln_fwb_64_01 = "走り続けろ、ガレージに行くぞ!",--Keep moving - get down to the garage!
pln_fwb_64_02 = "走り抜けてガレージまで降りてこい!",--Just dash through and head downstairs to the garage!
pln_fwb_64_03 = "もうすぐ終わりだ。ガレージに降りて、戦利品を確保しろ!",--We're almost done. Get down to the garage, secure that loot!
pln_fwb_65_01 = "",--Outstanding, gang! I wish all trips to the bank ended so happily.
pln_fwb_65_02 = "",--That was a great show, gang! Watching those accounts rise, and their shares topple.
pln_fwb_65_03 = "",--Great work, crew! It got a little messy, but you finished it like pros!
pln_fwb_66_01 = "",--Use the keycard to get inside the server room. It's on the second floor.
pln_fwb_66_02 = "",--Now use the card to get inside the server room. Second floor.
pln_fwb_66_03 = "",--Use the keycard to enter the server room on the second floor.
pln_fwb_67_01 = "",--Cops aren't going to let us walk out with the bank's bail-out money.
pln_fwb_67_02 = "",--This will be a high-profile catch if the cops drop us. Don't let it happen.
pln_fwb_67_03 = "",--The cops will go all out to stop us here. Show 'em what we do.
pln_fwb_68_01 = "でかした。これでフロントと上階のカメラは無効になった。残るは金庫のエリアだけだ。",--Great, you've disabled all cameras in the front and upstairs. Just a few in the vault area.
pln_fwb_68_02 = "いいぞ、これでフロントと上階はカメラで見つかることはない。よくやった。後は金庫のエリアに少しあるだけだ。",--All right. They're blind in the front and upstairs. Good work. Only a few in the vault area left.
pln_fwb_68_03 = "これでフロントと上階にあるカメラはオダブツだ。金庫のエリアにある奴は配線が違うから別だがな。",--That's the front and the upstairs dark as far as cameras are concerned. Cameras in the vault area run on a seperate circuit though.
pln_fwb_69_01 = "金庫のエリアのカメラを全て無効化したな。これで奴らはもう目が見えないも同然だ。",--You've disabled all cameras in the vault area. They're blind back there now.
pln_fwb_69_02 = "金庫のエリアのカメラはそいつでおしまいだ。よくやった。",--That's the last camera in the vault area. Good job.
pln_fwb_69_03 = "金庫のエリアにある\"目\"は潰された。もうカメラはないぞ。",--You poked out their eyes in the vault area. No more cameras back there.
pln_fwb_70_01 = "これで俺たちの悪さを監視するカメラは1つも無いぞ、でかした! ",--All right! Not a single camera left to watch our shenanigans. Great work.
pln_fwb_70_02 = "全てのカメラを片付けたな。これで銀行内の\"目\"は無くなったわけだ。いいぞ!",--That's all the cameras dealt with. The whole bank is blind to us now. Great!
pln_fwb_70_03 = "これで...この銀行内は真っ暗も同然というわけだ。よくやったぞ。",--And... The bank is dark to us. Good work, crew.
pln_dn1_brf_01_01 = "Murkywaterはここ数か月の間、武装した車両部隊を使い物資をDCを通って移送している。私は大当たりを引くまで、これに手を出す事を我慢し続けている。これだ、金塊だ。Woodrow上に、我々が望む場所に誘い込めるよう\"迂回路\"が設置された後、我々は武装された車列から輸送車を切り離す。一度切り離したら、そいつを襲い甘い輝きを担ぎだせ。 Au(Oh) yeah. *元素記号 Au=金",--Murkywater's been moving stuff through DC by convoy for months. I've resisted hitting these til we got a shot at a big prize. Here it is. Gold bullion. Got a "diversion" on the Woodrow set up to get it where we want it, then we're gonna seperate an armored truck from an armed convoy. Once it's isolated, hit it and boost that sweet bling. Au yeah.
pln_dn1_cbf_01_01 = "金塊いっぱいのトラックにクソを食らわせたら、問題は - 我々の旧友である - Murkywaterだ。だけどよ?手懐けられないものなんてないだろ?",--Got word on a truck filled with gold. Only problem is, it's guarded by our old friends - Murkywater. But hey, nothing you guys can't handle right?
pln_dn1_cbf_01_02 = "",--We're ambushing a convoy down by the docks. The cargo is gold. The convoy is Murkywater. Questions?
pln_dn1_cbf_01_03 = "Murkywateは密かに船から金塊を奴らの倉庫に運んでいる。待ち伏せしてみるか?",--Murkywater are trying to sneak a shipment of gold out of their warehouse. You guys up for an ambush?
pln_dn1_cnc_01_01 = "Murkywateの車列を叩いて金塊をいただくとしよう。",--Smash and grab on a Murkywater convoy laden with gold.
pln_dn1_cnc_01_02 = "Murkywaterが大量の金塊を護送してるぞ。襲撃の時間だ。",--A Murkywater convoy filled with gold. Time to hit it.
pln_dn1_cnc_01_03 = "",--We're hitting a convoy loaded with gold.
pln_dn1_intro_01_01 = "",-- ...and also on the 45 going south, there's been a major accident that's clogging the entire freeway. It's like a war zone out there this morning so you better take a scenic rout.
pln_dn1_intro_01_02 = "",--Traffic is backed all the way along the southbound I45. If you were planning on getting through that area, forget it.
pln_dn1_intro_01_03 = "",--Serious accident near the Woodrow Bridge when a limousine caught fire. Emergency services are still at the scene so if you're in the tailback, sit back and enjoy our calypso hour.
pln_dn1_01_01 = "コンボイが近くまで来ている。配置に就くんだ。",--The convoy is nearly here. Take your positions.
pln_dn1_01_02 = "",--The Murkies are headed towards you. Lock and load.
pln_dn1_01_03 = "オーケー、コンボイは近い。配置に就け。",--Okay, the convoy is close. Get in position.
pln_dn1_02_01 = "トラックの準備はできたか?",--Truck's ready?
pln_dn1_02_02 = "準備はいいか?",--Tackle ready?
pln_dn1_03_01 = "",--What? We didn't lay a damn thing. How is that possible?
pln_dn1_03_02 = "よし、車は全部止まったな。",--Ok. All vehicles stopped.
pln_dn1_03_03 = "狙い通りだ、ギャング共!",--Bang on target, gang!
pln_dn1_04_01 = "野郎ども、金塊を取りに行くんだ。",--Move it guys. Follow that gold.
pln_dn1_04_02 = "よし、野郎ども、金塊を追え!",--Ok guys, Get after that gold!
pln_dn1_04_03 = "トラックを追うんだギャング共。急げ!",--After the truck, gang. Hustle!
pln_dn1_05_01 = "トラックが俺たちの金塊を持ってるぞ。取りに行け!",--That truck has our gold. Get after it!
pln_dn1_05_02 = "トラックのところまで行け。金塊を頂くぞ!",--Close down on that truck. Get that gold!
pln_dn1_05_03 = "トラックを追いかけろ。さぁ行け!",--Follow the truck. Come on!
pln_dn1_06_01 = "よし、屠殺場に入る必要があるな。近くにC4が隠してある。そいつを使うのがいいだろう。",--All right, you need to get into that slaughterhouse. There's C4 stashed nearby. That should make a way in.
pln_dn1_06_02 = "トラックは屠殺場の中だ。C4がゴミ箱の中に隠してあるから、そいつを爆破させて入れ。",--The truck is in the slaughterhouse. There's C4 stashed in those bins. Grab it and bust in.
pln_dn1_06_03 = "よし、トラックはココを突き抜けたんだな。ゴミ箱からC4を取り出して扉を爆破してやれ。",--All right, the truck is through there. Grab the C4 from the bin and blow that door.
pln_dn1_07_01 = "C4を取るんだギャング共!",--Grab the C4, gang!
pln_dn1_07_02 = "C4を取るのを忘れるな。それでドアを通過出来る。",--Remember to grab the C4. That is your way through the door.
pln_dn1_07_03 = "お前ら、C4はゴミ箱の中だ。そいつでドアを爆破してやれ。",--C4 is in the bins, crew. Blast the door with it.
pln_dn1_08_01 = "ワイヤーを撃って切ってやれ!",--Shoot at the wires to make em snap!
pln_dn1_08_02 = "野郎共、そこから彼女を降ろしてやれ。",--Get her down from there, guys.
pln_dn1_08_03 = "そのデカブツを落とすんだ、ギャング共。",--Bring that beast down, gang.
pln_dn1_09_01 = "お前達、ワイヤーを打ってトラックを下ろすんだ。",--Guys, get the truck down! Shoot away those wires.
pln_dn1_09_02 = "ギャング共、トラックを降ろすんだ。衝撃を与えろ。",--Gang, you need to get the truck down. Maybe a little firepower.
pln_dn1_09_03 = "お前ら、ソイツを落とせ。力づくででもだ。",--Crew, bring it down. Perhaps a little force will do it.
pln_dn1_10_01 = "いいぞ。ドアを吹き飛ばせ!",--Great. Now, blow the doors!
pln_dn1_10_02 = "よくやった。C4をドアにつけろ!",--Good work. Now, C4 the doors!
pln_dn1_10_03 = "流石だ! ドアを吹きとばせ!",--Great work! Now breach those doors.
pln_dn1_11_01 = "C4をトラックのドアにつけろ、ギャング共。",--Plant C4 on the truck doors, gang.
pln_dn1_11_02 = "",--Come on, crew - focus! C4 the doors!
pln_dn1_11_03 = "",--C4 those truck doors, gang. Hurry!
pln_dn1_12_01 = "",--The gold is inside the safe. No time to waste now. Set up the drill and drill it open.
pln_dn1_12_02 = "",--The gold is inside the safe. Drill it open!
pln_dn1_12_03 = "",--Crack that safe, guys. Get that gold out of the firezone.
pln_dn1_13_01 = "",--Guys, the safe! Get the drill on it - pronto!
pln_dn1_13_02 = "",--Drill on the safe, just like we planned. Hurry!
pln_dn1_13_03 = "",--Mount the drill on the safe in the truck. Hurry!
pln_dn1_14_01 = "",--Nice. Out in the yard, I have a container ready to stash the gold. Number 61. Get it there!
pln_dn1_14_02 = "",--Now boost that gold to the readied container in the yard. Number 61!
pln_dn1_14_03 = "",--All right. Container 61 is where you need to stash the gold. It's out in the yard.
pln_dn1_15_01 = "",--Gang, remember: boost the gold out to container 61.
pln_dn1_15_02 = "",--Get the gold out to container 61, crew.
pln_dn1_15_03 = "",--Haul that beautiful gold out to container 61. Hurry!
pln_dn1_16_01 = "",--Put some gas on those tires. We need to block that eye in the sky.
pln_dn1_16_02 = "",--Ok I have an idea for that heli. Pour some gas on those tires and light it up. Should create a smokescreen.
pln_dn1_16_03 = "",--Now light up those tires. Get the gas on them. That'll deal with the chopper.
pln_dn1_17_01 = "",--Remember: set fire to the tires. Get gas all over them!
pln_dn1_17_02 = "",--Gang, ignite the tires. Give that chopper a nice thick smokescreen to worry about!
pln_dn1_17_03 = "",--Light up those tires, gang. Get some gas on them.
pln_dn1_18_01 = "",--Remember: you need to find some gas and get it on the tires!
pln_dn1_18_02 = "",--Gang, find gas and ignite the tires. Give that chopper a nice thick smokescreen to worry about!
pln_dn1_18_03 = "",--Light up those tires, gang. Find some gas and get it on them.
pln_dn1_19_01 = "",--Now the helicopter won't see where we load the containers.
pln_dn1_19_02 = "",--The helicopters are flying away. It's working.
pln_dn1_19_03 = "",--The smoke looks thick enough from here. All right, choppers are bugging out.
pln_dn1_20_01 = "",--Container 12. Lay a nice trap to cover our escape.
pln_dn1_20_02 = "",--Dump some gas in container 12. It'll cover our escape.
pln_dn1_20_03 = "",--To cover our escape, you gotta set a fire trap in container 12. Use gas.
pln_dn1_21_01 = "",--Okay. Now get it over by our exit. Use the control panel.
pln_dn1_21_02 = "",--All right. Let's get it over to where we need it. Find the crane controls.
pln_dn1_21_03 = "",--Great. Now get it across the yard. Look for the crane controls.
pln_dn1_22_01 = "",--Gang, we need that firetrap by our escape. Use the crane controls.
pln_dn1_22_02 = "",--Use the control panel in the yard to move that firetrap.
pln_dn1_22_03 = "",--The crane can lift the firetrap container. Look for the controls.
pln_dn1_23_01 = "",--Move the gold onto the truck! The crane can do it.
pln_dn1_23_02 = "",--Ok guys. Get the crane to move the containers as we practiced.
pln_dn1_23_03 = "",--Use the crane to lift the gold container onto the truck.
pln_dn1_24_01 = "",--Move the gold! Let the crane get it on to the truck.
pln_dn1_24_02 = "",--Put the container with the gold on that truck. Use the crane!
pln_dn1_24_03 = "",--Gotta get the container with the gold loaded on the truck. The crane can do it.
pln_dn1_25_01 = "",--Time to end this caper! Get to the escape. Follow the blue containers!
pln_dn1_25_02 = "",--Great! Now we can get out of here. Get to the escape. Follow the blue containers!
pln_dn1_25_03 = "",--Outstanding. We're almost done - now get to the escape. Just stay with the blue containers!
pln_dn1_26_01 = "",--Gang, stop standing around, and get to the escape point. Follow the blue containers!
pln_dn1_26_02 = "",--Crew, you need to bail. The blue containers will mark the path to the escape.
pln_dn1_26_03 = "",--Get to the escape point, clowns! Follow the blue containers!
pln_dn1_27_01 = "",--Now stop any pursuit. Blow that gas!
pln_dn1_27_02 = "",--Close the door in their faces. Blast the gas!
pln_dn1_27_03 = "",--Stop them following. Set off the trap!
pln_dn1_28_01 = "",--Gang, ignite the trap!
pln_dn1_28_02 = "",--Burn that trap before you leave! Hurry!
pln_dn1_28_03 = "",--Remember - the trap, set it off!
pln_dn1_29_01 = "",--Ok guys. I'm opening container 57 remotely. Get ready to run.
pln_dn1_29_03 = "走れ! 走れ!",--Run! Run!
pln_dn1_30_01 = "",--Come on, we're nearly done!
pln_dn1_30_02 = "",--Just get out of there!
pln_dn1_30_03 = "",--We're almost finished. Get to the escape, come on!
pln_dn1_31_01 = "",--We bloodied their nose AND got their gold. Great job!
pln_dn1_31_02 = "",--That's a LOT of beautiful gold. Outstanding work, gang!
pln_dn1_31_03 = "",--We'll have this melted down and on the market before the Murkies pay out their early retirements on this job.
pln_dn1_32_01 = "",--Great you got the gas. Might need more though.
pln_dn1_32_02 = "",--Grab as much gas as you can.
pln_dn1_32_03 = "察しがいいな。後でそのガソリンが必要になるだろう。",--You're reading my mind. We're going to need that gas later.
pln_dn1_33_01 = "",--Swats are spreading all over the roof. Look up guys.
pln_dn1_33_02 = "",--We got regular cops and SWATS on the scene.
pln_dn1_33_03 = "",--Guys, guys! The garage doors. Murkys!
pln_dn1_34_01 = "",--As expected, they've got helicopters. A smokescreen will force them away.
pln_dn1_34_02 = "",--The helicopter will see where we load our containers. Gotta deal with that.
pln_dn1_34_03 = "",--Police chopper is over you. We can't let them see which container we use.
pln_dn1_35_01 = "",--OK, remember the plan. Extract the gold, move the gold, set the smoke screen, set the trap, escape. Lets go!
pln_dn1_36_01 = "次に、トラップを12番コンテナに仕掛けろ",--Next, set a fire trap in container 12.
pln_dn1_36_02 = "トラップを仕掛ける必要がある。12番コンテナはガソリンまみれだぞ。",--Now, we need to set the trap. More gasoline in container 12.
pln_dn1_36_03 = "12番コンテナにトラップを仕掛けろ。ガソリンを撒くんだ",--Now, lay a fire trap in container 12. Dump some gas in there.
pln_dn1_38_01 = "おい! お前達が中に居ると、コンテナを持ち上げられない",--Hey! Gang, we can't lift the container while you're inside.
pln_dn1_38_02 = "お前らがそこにいるとコンテナが持ち上げられない。計画に従うんだ!",--We can't go lifting the container while you're inside there. Follow the plan!
pln_dn1_38_03 = "コンテナから出ろ! お前らをどこかに運ぶためのものじゃないぞ!",--Guys, out of the container! It's not going anywhere with you inside.
pln_dn1_39_01 = "車はそこに挟まった! C4を植えつけて、花火を咲かそうぜ。",--The van's stuck up there! Plant the C4 on the bottom, blow it open.
pln_dn1_39_02 = "",--Well, we're not getting the van down any time soon, so blast the doors.
pln_dn1_39_03 = "車はそこにある。だが、必要なのは中身だ。ドアにC4を植えろ!",--The van can stay up there, but we still need what's in it. Plant the C4 on the doors!
pln_dn1_40_01 = "",--Great. Now get that gas on those tires
pln_dn1_40_02 = "",--All right, good find. Now get that gas all over the tires.
pln_dn1_40_03 = "",--Good work. Now let's see that gas poured over the tires.
pln_dn1_41_01 = "",--Great. All right, now put that gas down in the container. We'll light it later.
pln_dn1_41_02 = "",--Okay, that gas will help secure our escape. Put the can into the container.
pln_dn1_41_03 = "",--All right, nice work! Now get to the container. Drop the gas can there.
vld_dn1_01_01 = "PAYDAYギャング共、Vladだ。その倉庫にはマークの付いた豚があるが、そいつは俺にとってマジで重要でな。そいつはな...あー...ママへのプレゼントだ。ああ、そうだ。サツなんかに持ってかせるんじゃないぞ。俺の為に取ってこい。",--Payday crew. Vlad. There's a marked pig in that warehouse. It's very important to me. It's for... er... present for mamma. Yes, that's it. Don't let the Feds get it. Grab it for me.
vld_dn1_01_02 = "ピエロ共! Vladだ。お前らがそこで何をやらかしてるかだが、それは気にしねえ。Xのマークが付いた豚がそこにあるが、科学捜査の奴らが来ればサツ共にそれが気づかれる。そこからそいつを取ってきてくれ。",--Clowns! Vlad here. What the hell are you doing in that - nevermind. There's a pig marked with an X in there. The Fed's will notice it when forensics come in. Get it out of there for me.
vld_dn1_01_03 = "Vladだ。クソ野郎共、屠殺場で何してやがんだ?まあいい、そのことは気にしねえよ。俺が気にしてるのはそこにある特別な豚のことでな、Xのマーク付けされたやつだ。そいつはサツ共もまだ感づいてねえ、マジで重要なやつだ。そいつをそこから取ってきてくれりゃお前らをずっと愛してやるぜ。",--This is Vlad. What are you fuckers doing in that slaughterhouse? Nevermind, I don't care. What I do care about is a special pig there - marked with an X. It's really important that the Fed's don't sniff around it. Get it out of there, and I will love you forever.
pln_nai_brf_01_01 = "",--We're working in the lab, late tonight, letting your eyes behold an eerie sight. Get cooking on the table, bubble and boil.And keep the cops from bringin', trouble and toil.
pln_nai_cbf_01_01 = "",--Trick or treat, smell my feet. Give me something to put on the street. If you don't, I don't care. Just don't cook in your underwear.
pln_nai_cnc_01_01 = "今夜の森は暗くて怖えな、ギャング共。ちょっとばかりMethの調理をしよう。",--The forest is dark and spooky tonight, gang. Let's cook a little meth.
pln_nai_cnc_01_02 = "ハロウィンのお菓子だ、野郎共。森のキャビンにまた行くぞ。",--Halloween treat, guys. Headed back to the cabin in the woods.
pln_nai_cnc_01_03 = "ハロウィンのお菓子作りの時間だ。森の中の調理場に行くぞ。",--Time to bake some Halloween treats, crew. Get to the forest meth lab.
pln_nai_intro_01_01 = "ここでMethを少し作るぞ。今年の夏にやったようにな。",--Here to cook a little meth. Just like we did last summer.
pln_nai_intro_01_02 = "やり方は知ってるな、ギャング共。Methを少し作るぞ。",--You know the drill, gang. Let's cook a little meth.
pln_nai_intro_01_03 = "ゲームをしようか? ’Meth'お料理ゲームを?",--You wanna play a game? A meth-cooking game?
pln_nai_01_01 = "飛び出して\"ばあ! \"と叫ぶ準備をしろ、ギャング共。",--Get ready to jump out and shout "boo!", gang.
pln_nai_01_02 = "Methを作る、相変わらずだな。",--Cook meth. Same as always.
pln_nai_01_03 = "着いたぞ。奴らを驚かす準備をしろ、お前ら。",--We're here. Get ready to scare 'em, crew.
pln_nai_02_01 = "まぁ、良いだろう...",--Uh, okay....
pln_nai_02_02 = "よし。予想外の展開だが仕事はまだ残ってるぞ。",--Okay. This is unexpected, but we still have a job to do.
pln_nai_02_03 = "お袋がいつも言ってたな、外の世界は大きいって。だがこれは...",--Momma always said it was a big world out there, but this...
pln_nai_03_01 = "調理を開始する為にエフェドリンの錠剤を加える必要がある。見つけてミキサーに加えろ。",--We need to add ephedrine tablets to start the cooking process. Find some and add it into the mixer.
pln_nai_03_02 = "まず、エフェドリンの錠剤をミキサーに投げ入れろ。",--First, grab some ephedrine tablets and throw 'em in the mixer.
pln_nai_03_03 = "よし。それで、錬金を始める為にエフェドリンの錠剤をいくらかミキサーに入れろ。",--Okay. So. Ephedrine will start the alchemy. Get some tablets in the mixer.
pln_nai_04_01 = "いい加減にして、私のイゴール達 - 錠剤をミキサーに入れろ。",--Come on, my little Igors - get the tablets in the mixer.
pln_nai_04_02 = "あの錠剤を手に入れてミキサーまで運べ。",--Get hauling those tablets to the mixer.
pln_nai_04_03 = "あれらの錠剤をミキサーに放れ、お前ら。",--Toss those tablets into the mixer, crew.
pln_nai_05_01 = "必要な材料を送る。しっかり掴めよ。",--I will send in the necessary ingredients for you. Hold tight.
pln_nai_05_02 = "よし、材料を向かわせる。準備しろ。",--Okay, I have ingredients on their way. Stand by.
pln_nai_05_03 = "準備しろ、お前ら。一回分の材料を向かわせる。",--Stand by, crew. I got a batch of ingredients on their way.
pln_nai_06_01 = "しっかりしろ、グルーヴィーグールども。もうすぐだ。",--Just hang tight, my groovy ghoulies. Almost there.
pln_nai_06_02 = "もうすぐで材料が着くぞ、お前ら。",--Ingredients are almost with you, crew.
pln_nai_06_03 = "敵を倒し続けろ。材料はもうすぐ届くぞ。",--Just hold off the armies of darkness. Ingredients are almost with you.
pln_nai_07_01 = "オーケー、材料だ。結構必要みたいだな。バッグ1つじゃダメそうだ。",--Okay, there's the ingredients. Going to need a little extra in there, though. More than one bag.
pln_nai_07_02 = "材料が届いたぞ。どうやら1つ入れるだけじゃ足りないみたいだ。入れ続けろ。",--Ingredients have arrived. Going to take more than one load though. Keep throwing them in.
pln_nai_07_03 = "よし、材料だ。だが1つじゃ無理そうだな。何個か入れるんだ。",--All right, there's the ingredients. But this is going to take more than a single load. Keep throwing it in.
pln_nai_08_01 = "オーケー、いいぞ。さあもっと入れろ。",--Okay. That's good. Now get more in there.
pln_nai_08_02 = "よし。うまくいってる。もっと必要だ。入れ続けろ。",--Yes. It's working. Just need more in there. Keep loading.
pln_nai_08_03 = "オーライ。ああ、いいぞ。だが、もっと必要だ。",--All right. Yeah, this is good. Going to need more, though.
pln_nai_09_01 = "よし、Methは砕く必要がある。破壊して手に入れろ、お前ら!",--Okay, now you need to smash up that meth. Get wrecking, crew!
pln_nai_09_02 = "Methの固まりだ、砕かないと手に入れられないぞ。破壊しろ、撃って、爆破して - それを粉々にしろ!",--The meth's set, but we can't get it out like that. Break it down. Smash it, shoot it, blast it - just break it down!
pln_nai_09_03 = "あー、Methが出来たな。だが手に入れるには砕かないといけないぞ。粉々にして手に入れるんだ、ギャング共!",--Ahhhh, the meth is done, but we can't get it out as it is. Need to break it down. Get smashing, gang!
pln_nai_10_01 = "忘れるな。Methを粉砕して小さく寸断しろ!",--Don't forget. Smash the meth into smaller chunks!
pln_nai_10_02 = "覚えてるか、Methを砕いてくれ。",--Remember, you gotta smash up that meth.
pln_nai_10_03 = "Methは小さく砕かないといけない。怒りを込めろ、ギャング共!",--The meth needs breaking up into little pieces. Get angry on it, gang!
pln_nai_11_01 = "料理を続けるならまた錠剤を放れ。それか脱出用のヘリに合図を送れ - お前ら次第だ。",--Add more tablets to continue the cooking. Or signal the helicopter to escape - your call.
pln_nai_11_02 = "よし。料理を続けてもいいし、ヘリに合図を送ってお遊戯を終わってもいい。",--All right. Now you can keep cooking, or signal the chopper and end this caper.
pln_nai_11_03 = "もしまだ料理を続けたいなら、また錠剤をミキサーに放り込め、お前ら。それかフレアを焚いて逃げるかだ。好きにしろ!",--Throw more tablets in the mixer if you want to keep cooking, crew. Or light the flare and bail. Up to you!
pln_nai_12_01 = "良い位置だな。待ってろ。",--Good spot. Now we wait.
pln_nai_12_02 = "OK、パイロットを待て。",--Okay, now wait for the pilot.
pln_nai_12_03 = "よし。パイロットが合図を確認するのを待て。",--That's it. Now wait for the pilot to signal in.
pln_nai_13_01 = "ヘリだ、ギャング共。乗り込め!",--There's the chopper, gang. Get to it!
pln_nai_13_02 = "ヘリが来たぞ、乗るんだ。",--Chopper's here. Get on it.
pln_nai_13_03 = "ヘリコプターが着いた。乗るんだ、お前ら!",--That's the helicopter. Get on it, crew!
pln_nai_14_01 = "床にあるコンテナの1つにバッグを投げ込め。俺が後で... 誰か回収できる奴を送る。",--Just throw the bags into one of the containers on the floor. I'll send...someone to pick it up later.
pln_nai_14_02 = "床にあるコンテナの1つにバッグを投げ込め。誰か回収できる奴を見つけておくから。",--Now stow those bags in the container on the floor. I'm sure I can find someone to collect it.
pln_nai_14_03 = "バッグを床にあるコンテナに投げ込め。後で回収しに行く。",--Now get those bags in the containers down on the floor. We'll return and collect them.
pln_nai_15_01 = "見るんじゃねえぞ、だが...",--Don't look now, but...
pln_nai_15_02 = "子供のおやすみの曲じゃねえな。",--That ain't the sweet music of the children of the night.
pln_nai_15_03 = "何か聞こえた...",--I heard something...
pln_nai_16_01 = "",--Well, in the annals of criminal cock-ups, that ranks high. I can hear the cops laughing from here. Better luck next time.
pln_nai_16_02 = "",--Bubble, bubble, toil and trouble. Mostly toil and trouble. Especially trouble.
pln_nai_17_01 = "バッグ無しだと!? 悪夢だ!",--Not a single bag?! This is a nightmare!
pln_nai_17_02 = "何も取ってないのか?俺を殺す気か!",--You got nothing? You guys are killing me!
pln_nai_17_03 = "何も手に入れてないのか?",--You didn't get anything out?
pln_nai_18_01 = "さて、ちょっと少ないな。ガソリン代を賄えるくらいか。次はもっと取ってきてくれよ。",--Well, you got a decent amount. Just about covers the gas money. Maybe next time we can push it further.
pln_nai_18_02 = "今回の失敗じゃなかったが、レザーフェイスの階段下のぬいぐるみよりもバッグの量が少なかったな。",--The job wasn't a total bust. Still, fewer stuffed bags than under Leatherface's stairs!
pln_nai_18_03 = "ノルマギリギリの回収量だが、それでもいいほうだ。来年はもっとよく集められるよといいな。",--It's a bare bones haul, but it'll do. Better luck next year, crew.
pln_nai_19_01 = "",--Nice haul! This will bring in a nice chunk of change. Good job!
pln_nai_19_02 = "お前ら、十分な量のバッグを回収したな。よくやった!",--You snatched a decent amount of bags there. Well done!
pln_nai_19_03 = "近所を回ってお菓子を集めた時くらいの収集量だな。帰ってこい、野郎共分け前を分配しよう!",--That's a nice haul of trick or treat goodies. Come home, gang, let's share it out!
pln_nai_20_01 = "ひゃっはー! お前ら良くやった! 給料日を楽しめ! お前達にはその価値がある。",--Hot damn! You guys did great! Enjoy your payday - you deserve it.
pln_nai_20_02 = "来たぞ、見たぞ、ぶちかましてやったぞ!",--We came, we saw, we kicked their ass!
pln_nai_20_03 = "お前らすげーぜ! 俺がお前達の一番のファンだぜ!",--You guys are great! I'm your number one fan!
pln_nai_21_01 = "彼等はここだ。",--They're here.
pln_nai_21_02 = "お客さまだよ!",--Here's Johnny!
pln_nai_21_03 = "恐れろ...ひどく恐れろ...",--Be afraid... Be very afraid.
pln_nai_21_04 = "この警察共が泣き叫ぶのが聞きたいぜ!",--I want to hear a cry of fear from those cops!
pln_nai_21_05 = "1,2,警察が向かってるぞ。",--One, two, cops are coming for you...
pln_nai_22_01 = "生きてる! 生きてるぞ!",--It's alive! Alive!
pln_nai_22_02 = "化け物になってるぞ!",--This is going to be a monster!
pln_nai_22_03 = "これは料理だ。それが奏でる音楽!",--It's cooking. What music it makes!
mer_jr1_intro_01_01 = "侵入者だ! 撃て!",--Intruders! Fire!
loc_jr1_cbf_01_01 = "Black Ridgeと呼ばれる砂漠に我々の施設がある。そこの金庫には重要なお宝が保管されているのだ。我々の新たな仕事関係の手始めとして、協力してこのMurkywaterの金品を我々のものにしようではないか。いいだろう?なあ。",--We've a facility in the desert called Black Ridge. There is a some significant loot secured in its vaults. As an initial test of our new working relationship, we'll combine our talents and turn this Murkywater money into our money. Sounds good, yeah? For sure.
loc_jr1_cnc_01_01 = "NevadaにあるBlack Ridgeの施設に向かってくれ。Murkywaterのブツが奪って欲しいみたいだぞ。",--Please, head to the Black Ridge facility in Nevada. It has Murkywater loot for you to steal.
loc_jr1_cnc_01_02 = "砂漠地帯にあるMurkywaterの施設に金品がある。協力して奪おうじゃないか。",--An amount of loot is at a Murkywater facility in the desert. We shall combine forces to take it.
loc_jr1_cnc_01_03 = "MurkywaterはNevadaに金品を保存している。重要な品だ。奪って山分けしようじゃないか。",--Murkywater is holding loot in Nevada. Significant loot. Let's get it and share it.
loc_jr1_01_01 = "我が新しい友よ! Black Ridgeにようこそ! 略奪品の倉庫みたいなものだ 完全武装の倉庫だが、高価な略奪品が詰まってる。",--My new friends! Welcome to Black Ridge. Like a storehouse for loot - an armored storehouse, with very valuable loot.
loc_jr1_01_02 = "友よ! Black Ridgeへようこそ。最重要機密だ! 私が君たちに教えられるのはここに金品があるということだ。非常に価値のあるものだぞ。",--Friends! Welcome to Black Ridge. Top secret! What I can tell you is that there is loot here. Very valuable loot.
loc_jr1_01_03 = "ああ! 友よ! Black Ridgeへようこそ。ここは、そうだな、今は貴重な宝が保管されている。さあ盗もうではないか!",--Ah! My friends! Welcome to Black Ridge. It's used for, well, for now is holding loot of a significent value. Let's steal it!
loc_jr1_02_01 = "あらかじめ、私がちょっとしたものを諸君のために用意しておいた。赤いストロボが焚かれた木箱を探してくれ。",--Before we begin, I've arranged for a few small articles to be left for you. Find the crates with the red strobe.
loc_jr1_02_02 = "ビジネスのために! 入口の近くに木箱がある。赤いストロボが付いたものを手に入れるのだ。探せ。ちょっとしたプレゼントが入っているぞ。",--To business! There are crates near the entrance. Got a little red strobe on. Find them. They have a few little presents within.
loc_jr1_02_03 = "この仕事に必要な道具を用意しておいた。木箱に入っているから見つけるのだ。小さなストロボが目印だ。",--I've managed to organise some necessary tools for this job. Find them in the crates. They got a little strobe on them.
loc_jr1_03_01 = "諸君? ストロボの付いた木箱だよ? なあ?",--Gentlemen? The crates with the strobes? Please?
loc_jr1_03_02 = "邪魔したくはないのだがね、まずは木箱を探してくれ。",--I hate to bother you,I really do, but finding the crates is our primary objective.
loc_jr1_03_03 = "木箱だよ、諸君? ストロボ付きのだよ?",--The crates, gentlemen? With the strobes?
loc_jr1_04_01 = "Keycardにアークカッター、そしてブリーチングチャージ。私が関与していないように見せなければいけない。集めろ。",--Keycard, arc cutter and, yes, those are breaching charges. We need to make it look like I am not involved. Collect them.
loc_jr1_04_02 = "諸君のために、Keycardと溶接カッター、そしてブリーチングチャージを置いてきたぞ。私は、ボタンを押して入ることが出来るが、私が侵入に関与した証拠をのこしたくないのでな。",--I've left you a keycard, an arc cutter and some breaching charges, my friends. I could press a button and open a door, but we must hide my involvement, yes.
loc_jr1_04_03 = "そこにKeycardと溶接カッター、そして数個ブリーチングチャージがあるだろう、回収してくれ。押し入るのはスマートではないが、私が関わったという疑いは避けられる。",--There is a keycard, an arc cutter and a small number of breaching charges, that you must collect. Blasting in is crude, but it will help deflect suspicion from me.
loc_jr1_05_01 = "諸君のために置いていった道具を集めてはくれないか?",--If you would be so kind as to collect the articles I have left for you.
loc_jr1_05_02 = "道具を集めさえすれば進めるのだよ、友よ。",--We can only proceed once you have acquired those items, my friends.
loc_jr1_05_03 = "道具だ、友よ。回収するのは面倒だが、なあ、この任務には必要なのだよ。",--The items, friends. Collecting them is a bother, I know, but necessary to this operation.
loc_jr1_06_01 = "よし、そこのメインドアに爆弾を置くのだ。",--Good. Now, drop the charges at the main door over there.
loc_jr1_06_02 = "いいぞ! さあ、メインドアの近くに爆弾を置くのだ。",--Superb! Now, just drop the charges near the main door.
loc_jr1_06_03 = "素晴らしい。恐縮だが、ドアの近くに爆弾を置いてくれないか。",--Excellent. Now if you would be so kind as to deposit the charges near the door.
loc_jr1_07_01 = "忘れるな、ドアの近くに爆弾を置くのだ。",--Remember, drop the charges near the door.
loc_jr1_07_02 = "私の記録を確認させてくれ。ああ、確かに爆弾をドアのところに置けと言っていた。",--Let me check my records. Yes, I mentioned that the charges must be dropped near the door.
loc_jr1_07_03 = "頼む、ドアを破壊してくれ、我が友よ。",--Please, leave the charges at the door, my friends.
loc_jr1_08_01 = "よし、いいぞ! さて、4か所のロックを爆破してくれたまえ。",--Okay, good! Now, please to place the charges onto the four locks you see there.
loc_jr1_08_02 = "さあ、ブリーチングチャージを設置してくれ。4つをそれぞれつなげるんだ、頼むぞ。",--Now wire up those breaching charges. One for each of the four locks, if you please.
loc_jr1_08_03 = "ブリーチングチャージをロックの部分に設置してくれ。リハーサルなどしなくていいぞ。",--Those charges must be hooked up to the four locks. I am sure you don't need walking through the procedure.
loc_jr1_09_01 = "アフリカーン語が出てたか? すまない! 「ロックに」「爆弾を」「設置して」「ほしい」って言ったのだよ...クソが。",--Did I speak in Afrikaans? My apologies! I meant to say "please" "plant" "the" "charges" "on the locks"... you kaks.
loc_jr1_09_02 = "通信にノイズが入っていたかもしれんな、繰り返すぞ。ロックにクソ爆弾を設置するのだ。頼む。",--Perhaps there was interference on the radio, so let me repeat. Plant the fucking charges on the locks. Please.
loc_jr1_09_03 = "君のクソッタレな仕事を思い出したまえ。4ヶ所のロックに爆弾を設置して突破するんだ。",--Please remember your fucking jobs - the breaching charges need to be attached to all four locks.
loc_jr1_10_01 = "素晴らしい。さあ、起爆装置も設置したまえ。",--Excellent. Now, let's just get a detonator on there too.
loc_jr1_10_02 = "よくやった。次は起爆装置を設置するのだ。",--Nicely done. Next, we need a detonator on those charges. Rig it up, won't you?
loc_jr1_10_03 = "ブラボー! さて、起爆装置を設置したまえ。",--Bravo! Now, why don't we get a detonator on there too.
loc_jr1_11_01 = "「起爆装置を設置しろ」と言っただろう?",--Do the words "rig the detonator to the charges" ring a bell?
loc_jr1_11_02 = "てんてこ舞いでとても忙しいのは分かっている、だが起爆装置を爆弾に設置してくれないかね?",--I know things are hectic and you are very busy, but would you mind getting the detonator onto the charges?
loc_jr1_11_03 = "なあ?起爆装置を設置したまえ?",--Please? Attach the detonator?
loc_jr1_12_01 = "カウントダウンが始まった。警官どもを近づけないでくれたまえよ?停止させるな。",--The countdown has started. Keep the police off the detonator, yes? No snippy-snip!
loc_jr1_12_02 = "起爆装置のタイマーが作動した。敵から守ってくれ。くれぐれも停止させないでくれたまえ。",--Detonator is counting down. Keep the kerels away from it. Don't need them cutting it, for sure.
loc_jr1_12_03 = "起爆装置がチクタク鳴っているな。敵を近づけるな。",--Tick-tock, said the detonator. Keep the kerels away.
loc_jr1_13_01 = "もうすぐだ...。",--Almost... there.
loc_jr1_13_02 = "さあ...来るぞ...",--Any... second...
loc_jr1_13_03 = "もうすこし...",--Just a little longer...
loc_jr1_14_01 = "クソ共が起爆装置を止めたぞ。直したまえ!",--Those poes fucked the detonator, mans. Fix it!
loc_jr1_14_02 = "敵に掘られてどうする。やり返して起爆装置を修理するのだ。",--You let the kerels fuck you. Fuck 'em back and fix the detonator.
loc_jr1_14_03 = "おい、クソ野郎共に押されてるじゃないか。倍にしてやり返せ。そしてクソ起爆装置を直したまえ!",--Hey man, the kerel poes are fucking you in the ass. Fuck 'em back, harder. And fix the fucking detonator!
loc_jr1_15_01 = "ドーン! よし! 入りたまえ。Skop,skiet en boomklim!",--Boom! Good! Now, inside. Skop, skiet en boomklim!
loc_jr1_15_02 = "ドカーン! 大当たりだったな。敵が中で待ってるぞ!",--Ka-boom! That was on the bullseye, yes. Fight your way in!
loc_jr1_15_03 = "あれがここにあると思っていたのだ! 中に入って戦い続けろ。",--I felt that one here! Now, inside, keep fighting.
loc_jr1_16_01 = "来い、全員中へ入るのだ! 早く!",--Come now, everyone inside! Hurry!
loc_jr1_16_02 = "恥ずかしがらなくていいぞ。入りたまえ!",--Don't be shy now. Into the complex!
loc_jr1_16_03 = "頼む、来てくれ。中でパーティといこう!",--Come on, please, join the party inside!
loc_jr1_17_01 = "先ほど手に入れたKeycardはエアロックを開けることができる。そこから内部へ繋がっている。クソ共を追い払え。",--The keycard you collected earlier will initiate the opening of this airlock, which leads to the inner complex. Swipe that little kaka.
loc_jr1_17_02 = "さて、お前たちのためにKeycardを置いてある。あの大きな扉は二段階のセキュリティがあり、その先にエアロックがある。ひとつ目はKeycardだ。だから...",--Now, the keycard I left for you. That large door has two security stages, and an airlock beyond. The first is using the keycard. So...
loc_jr1_17_03 = "この扉には二段階のセキュリティプロトコルが採用されている。ひとつ目はKeycardを使うんだ。だから...頼むぞ。",--This door has a two-stage security protocol. First stage is using the keycard. So...if you please.
loc_jr1_18_01 = "忘れるな... Keycardをロックに通したか? 腐れロケット工学じゃないんだぞ。",--Remember - the keycard on the lock there? Not fucking rocket science.
loc_jr1_18_02 = "",--Can one of you please, when time permits, swipe the keycard in the lock?
loc_jr1_18_03 = "",--I still require one of you poes to swipe the card.
loc_jr1_19_01 = "",--Good. Secondly, there is a security room close by. Cut through to it, and approve the airlock sequence.
loc_jr1_19_02 = "",--Bravo! Now, second step - find the local security station, cut through and approve the opening sequence.
loc_jr1_19_03 = "",--Kwaai kwaai. Now secondly there should be a security station nearby. Head there and approve the opening.
loc_jr1_20_01 = "",--The local security station, dear friends. That's your next stop.
loc_jr1_20_02 = "",--The door needs approval, remember. Hurry. Stop playing with your dicks.
loc_jr1_20_03 = "",--We need approval from the security station. I would do it myself, but alas...
loc_jr1_21_01 = "",--Superb! Everything is proceeding perfectly. Now, please, everybody into the airlock.
loc_jr1_21_02 = "",--Bakgat! Now, onwards, my friends. The airlock awaits you!
loc_jr1_21_03 = "そして... 開けゴマ! ブラボー、我が友よ! さあ、クソッタレなエアロックに入ってくれたまえ。",--And..open the sesame! Bravo, my friends! Now, please, get in the fucking airlock.
loc_jr1_22_01 = "",--Make sure all you fine people are inside, The outer door must close before the inner door can open.
loc_jr1_22_02 = "",--Make sure your gang are safely gathered in the airlock. The outer door cannot close until this is so.
loc_jr1_22_03 = "",--Please, everyone into the airlock. The doors are designed so that the inner cannot open until the outer is closed.
loc_jr1_23_01 = "",--It will just take a moment, gentlemen. Perhaps use the time to assess your current situation re ammo.
loc_jr1_23_02 = "",--It will open in a second or two. And then...
loc_jr1_23_03 = "",--Any second now. Does anybody know any jokes?
loc_jr1_24_01 = "",--Ah! There it is! Now, please, out of the airlock and into the inner complex!
loc_jr1_24_02 = "",--The door is opening! Good! Now, if you would be so kind, please storm the inner complex.
loc_jr1_24_03 = "",--Ah, the door opens! Now, let us proceed into the inner complex with speed and violence.
loc_jr1_25_01 = "",--Come on, no need to be nervous. Out of the airlock, friends!
loc_jr1_25_02 = "",--The inner complex is nothing to be scared of.
loc_jr1_25_03 = "",--It would be beautiful if we could do this with you hiding in the airlock, but... alas...
loc_jr1_26_01 = "",--Get to the control room - the black heart of the facility. From there, you can open the vaults and grab all that, as you say, 'good shit'.
loc_jr1_26_02 = "",--Now. Overlooking this area you will find the control room. From there the vaults in this part of the facility are controlled. That would be useful, yes?
loc_jr1_26_03 = "",--This area has several vaults, which can be opened from a control room. We want what's in the vaults so necessity demands we get to the control room.
loc_jr1_27_01 = "",--The control room is up there. You see?
loc_jr1_27_02 = "",--The control will be found overlooking the complex.
loc_jr1_27_03 = "",--You see the control room up there?
loc_jr1_28_01 = "",--You can only open one vault at a time, and I should make you aware that not all vaults contain loot. How you figure out which to open is your problem.
loc_jr1_28_02 = "",--Now, only one vault can be opened at a time, and not all vaults are containing the loot. I will leave it to you to figure out which is worth opening.
loc_jr1_28_03 = "",--Only one vault can be opened at a time. Further, only certain vaults have loot within them. How that is determined is up to you, but I have confidence in your ability.
loc_jr1_29_01 = "",--Yes, I do believe I hear a vault opening. Excellent! Keep at it, gentlemen!
loc_jr1_29_02 = "",--Ahhh, do my ears deceive me or is that the sound of a titanium vault opening. Maintain your efforts, friends!
loc_jr1_29_03 = "",--Ahhh, if any sound is sweeter than that of an opening vault it is that of bagging loot. You are producing a symphony for my ears!
loc_jr1_30_01 = "",--All right, my dear friends. That's enough loot to make this op worthwhile. You decide if you want to keep going. Every extra dollar, rand and rouble strengthens our friendship, yeah? For sure.
loc_jr1_30_02 = "",--Great. That loot will satisfy our arrangement... however, if you wanted to carry on... I am just saying... hmmmm?
loc_jr1_30_03 = "",--That is a good amount of loot, friends. Enough to make this worthwhile. Still, if you feel like you still got a little lead in your pencil and wanted to fuck Murkywater a little longer... you can get more.
loc_jr1_31_01 = "",--That is the first of some fucking sweet loot! Excellent! Now, you will find a large vertical shaft nearby. Send loot up it by cable. I will look after it.
loc_jr1_31_02 = "",--Ah! The first bag! You will find a vertical conveyance near the vaults that will relay the loot up to me. It will be perfectly safe!
loc_jr1_31_03 = "",--The first bag! Bellissimo! Now, close to the vaults you will find a tall vertical shaft with cables. Attach the bags to the cables, and they will be lifted to me.
loc_jr1_32_01 = "",--And I believe that about does it, my friends! Now, please ensure that our hard-earned loot is placed on the cables and conveyed up to me.
loc_jr1_32_02 = "",--Wonderful! I believe that that is enough to make this a worthwhile venture. Please, ensure all of the bags are placed on the cables and sent up to me.
loc_jr1_32_03 = "",--Bravo, my friends! Now, to proceed, please attach the bags to the cables in the large vertical shaft. I am at the top, and will receive them safely.
loc_jr1_33_01 = "",--It's a beautiful painting. Last seen on the walls of a well known South American dictator. See how the artist captured the light and all that shit? Beautiful.
loc_jr1_33_02 = "",--I don't know much about fine art, but I know some poe will pay through the arse for that.
loc_jr1_33_03 = "",--It's a masterpiece. Thought lost for decades. I'd hang it in my crapper, but it's worth a shitload of cash.
loc_jr1_34_01 = "",--Fuck knows what that thing is. They say it has a curse. Makes your nose look like a dick. So why people pay craploads for it, I don't know.
loc_jr1_34_02 = "",--Maybe I should've studied this ancient stuff more. Could the curse be true? Ah, it's just old shit worth money to me.
loc_jr1_34_03 = "",--This was found by our "tomb raider" division. They're great guys. Drink like fucking micks though.
loc_jr1_35_01 = "",--This thing has secrets that can topple the government. Wanna see what the President keeps in a folder called "Gentlemen's Interests"? Yeah, you do - for sure!
loc_jr1_35_02 = "",--This server has secrets, recordings, data that can change the world. And all my saved games. Yeah, for sure.
loc_jr1_35_03 = "",--It's made of metal and plastic, but this server has secrets that makes Pandora's Box look like a fucking kiddies toy-chest.
loc_jr1_36_01 = "",--I won't tell you what this is, 'cos you'll fucking shit your undies. Just don't press any buttons.
loc_jr1_36_02 = "",--We stole this from a lab not a million miles from here. Two hundred thirty eight thousand six hundred and six miles, to be precise.
loc_jr1_36_03 = "",--All right now, careful with this. You press the wrong buttons and there's no telling what you might turn into.
loc_jr1_37_01 = "",--Yoohoooooo! Send the bags up here, my friends!
loc_jr1_37_02 = "",--The bags will be perfectly safe with me. Send them up, please.
loc_jr1_37_03 = "",--Do you see the shaft? Yes, just send the bags of loot up here.
loc_jr1_38_01 = "",--And... yes, that is a satisfactory piece of business! All of the bags! Now, please, attach yourselves to the cables, join me up here and let us meet in person!
loc_jr1_38_02 = "ちょっとまってくれ、1つ、2つ。よし、全部あるな! さて、ケーブルを使って私の元へ上がってきてくれ。",--Let me see, one, two. Yes, all here! Now, please use the cables to join me up here.
loc_jr1_38_03 = "",--One, two, buckle my shoe. Yes, it would seem all of the bags are present. Now, please, attach your good selves to the cables and join me.
loc_jr1_39_01 = "こっちだ、諸君! 照れないでくれ! こっちで挨拶させてくれ",--Come on, gentlemen! Don't be shy! Come and say hello.
loc_jr1_39_02 = "よし、いいぞ。シャフトをあがってきてくれ",--Yes, that's right, all of you up the shaft, please.
loc_jr1_39_03 = "",--I'm keen to meet you all. Please, zipline up the shaft.
loc_jr1_40_01 = "やぁ諸君! 挨拶しよう!",--Ah! Gentlemen! Greetings!
loc_jr1_40_02 = "我が友! 我が喜びよ!",--My friends! My pleasure!
loc_jr1_40_03 = "やぁ、君が新しい友か!",--Hello, to you, my new friends!
loc_jr1_41_01 = "",--Now, there will be time for longer hellos later, but we should really make our escape now, yes?
loc_jr1_41_02 = "",--We can get better acquainted later, but I feel now would be the opportune time to, how you say, GTFO, yes?
loc_jr1_41_03 = "",--We can get to know each other over whiskey and cigars later, because I feel that now would be the perfect time for a getaway, yes?
loc_jr1_42_01 = "こちらだよ",--Over here, please.
loc_jr1_42_02 = "諸君? こちらだ",--Gentlemen? Please?
loc_jr1_42_03 = "",--This way, my friends, with all haste.
loc_jr1_43_01 = "",--Our escape chopper is out here, but you will also see a lot of radar equipment. With this, they could follow us anywhere we could fly to.
loc_jr1_43_02 = "",--Once we are outside you will see our escape helicopter, as well as a large array of advanced radar equipment. State of the art. It could track us anywhere west of the Rockies.
loc_jr1_43_03 = "",--Our escape by helicopter is imminent, but we must cover ourselves. Beyond the door Murkywater has an impressive array of radar equipment.
loc_jr1_44_01 = "",--It would be best if these radars were destroyed. Yes?
loc_jr1_44_02 = "",--We want to get away cleanly so these must be destroyed. I can leave that to you, yes?
loc_jr1_44_03 = "",--Please, destroy the radars. Stab their fucking eyes out, so to speak.
loc_jr1_45_01 = "いくつか仕事で使うC4を持ってきた。",--I've got some C4 for the job right here.
loc_jr1_45_02 = "",--Thankfully, I have a supply of C4 right here.
loc_jr1_45_03 = "",--This cache of C4 should deal with the radars, yes?
loc_jr1_46_01 = "",--Do not forget. Take out those radars. I'll get the chopper ready.
loc_jr1_46_02 = "",--So. I will prepare the helicopter. You will deal with the radar dishes. Agreed?
loc_jr1_46_03 = "",--Almost open. Remember, you deal with the radars, and I will prepare the helicopter.
loc_jr1_47_01 = "",--And... we go!
loc_jr1_47_02 = "",--Apres vous!
loc_jr1_47_03 = "",--After you!
loc_jr1_48_01 = "C4を使ってレーダーを破壊するんだ、我が友よ!",--Use the C4 to send those radars tumbling, my friends!
loc_jr1_48_02 = "",--That's right. C4 each of those dishes.
loc_jr1_48_03 = "忘れるな、すべてのレーダーにC4を設置するんだ",--Remember, you must apply the C4 to each of those radars.
loc_jr1_49_01 = "",--Excellent. They are blind! Blind as a bat. Though bats are supposed to be blind, and locate prey by echolocation, so that is...
loc_jr1_49_02 = "",--That was a bulleye, yes! Now we can fly away and worry not a jot about being followed!
loc_jr1_49_03 = "",--It saddens me to see such beautiful hardware reduced to ruins, but it is a necessary evil. Now, our clean escape is assured!
loc_jr1_50_01 = "",--Okay, friends, let us now move the lootbags to the helicopter. Do not dawdle now!
loc_jr1_50_02 = "",--And now, if you would be so kind, the loot bags to the helicopter? Please?
loc_jr1_50_03 = "",--Now, please, bring the loot bags to the helicopter.
loc_jr1_51_01 = "",--I have a nice spot, just for those loot bags... right here.
loc_jr1_51_02 = "",--We're almost done, but may I remind you again about bringing the bags to the helicopter?
loc_jr1_51_03 = "",--Just bring thoses bags to the chopper, dear friends.
loc_jr1_52_01 = "",--Damn, and shit. The aircrew are sloppy as kak. Helicopter ain't got no fuel. Hey, can you hook up the fuel line?
loc_jr1_52_02 = "",--Kak! Some sloppy bastard forgot to refuel the chopper. Hook up the fuel, would you?
loc_jr1_52_03 = "",--Ach! Some poes has been joyriding this bird. Gas is empty. Can you be a good chap and hook up the fuel line?
loc_jr1_53_01 = "",--I know it is an imposition, but do you think you could connect the fuel hose to the helicopter?
loc_jr1_53_02 = "",--Can I remind you that this chopper is grounded until it is refueled?
loc_jr1_53_03 = "",--Yes, it would be most agreeable to get some fuel in this chopper.
loc_jr1_54_01 = "",--Ah kak, they know we're trying to fuck off. They're going all in! Hold steady, friends!
loc_jr1_54_02 = "",--Looks like a last desperate attempt to clip our wings, hey? Stand firm, brave warriors.
loc_jr1_54_03 = "",--They're throwing everything into this. Hold them off, my friends. They'll kill you, but they'll fuck me proper. For sure.
loc_jr1_55_01 = "",--Right, the fuel tank is full, the blades are spinning and the cargo is secure. Time to get out of here. Gentlemen, please join me aboard!
loc_jr1_55_02 = "",--Great. We got a full tank, lots of green lights and we're fat with stolen loot. Hop aboard, my friends. Let's conclude this.
loc_jr1_55_03 = "",--Ah, bravo! We're fueled and ready to go. Please, make your way aboard and let us get out of here. This was a fine day.
loc_jr1_56_01 = "",--We are finally almost finished! Please, join me at the helicopter!
loc_jr1_56_02 = "",--The end is upon us. And it is a good ending! Please, into the helicopter!
loc_jr1_56_03 = "",--We are done, my good friends! Everyone into the helicopter!
loc_jr1_57_01 = "ああっ! このクソに20ドル貸しっぱなしだった! まぁいい。",--Ah! That fucker owed me $20. Ah well.
loc_jr1_57_02 = "",--I liked that guy. We'll send his wife a ham. Yeah, for sure.
loc_jr1_57_03 = "",--Thanks. I hated that poes. Kept stealing my shampoo.
loc_jr1_57_04 = "",--I've seen him take a bullet before. Thought he'd last longer.
loc_jr1_57_05 = "",--He knew he was going to die tonight. Just knew it.
loc_jr1_57_06 = "",--He only had a week left on his contract.
loc_jr1_57_07 = "",--Ha! I bet he didn't expect that, for sure!
loc_jr1_57_08 = "あー、彼は私の友達だ。さて、ここで何している?",--Ahhh, he was my friend. Well, what can you do?
loc_jr1_57_09 = "",--Saw that one gun down a village in Uganda. Good man.
loc_jr1_57_10 = "あいつはつまらん奴だったんだ。ありがとうよ。",--He was a boring poe. Thank you.
loc_jr1_57_11 = "",--He was officer material. Was!
loc_jr1_57_12 = "",--I didn't like that poephol's manners.
loc_jr1_57_13 = "ハッ、彼はよく売春宿で死にたいと言っていた。さて、少なくとも彼はヤッたな、そうだろ?",--Ha, he always said he wanted to die in a brothel. Well, at least he got fucked, yeah?
loc_jr1_57_14 = "彼は小学校を爆破した。いい気味だ。",--He bombed a school. Good riddance.
loc_jr1_57_15 = "何故彼がここにいる? 彼は調理師だぞ!",--Why was he there? He's the cook!
loc_jr1_57_16 = "",--That was our chaplain. You guys are stone cold.
loc_jr1_57_17 = "",--He was a bakvissie anyway.
loc_jr1_57_18 = "",--Right in the bradley, yeah.
loc_jr1_57_19 = "",--He was my chomma. Shit happens though, right?
loc_jr1_57_20 = "",--Yeah, die you fucking cuiter.
loc_jr1_57_21 = "",--What a mompie. He's better dead.
loc_jr1_57_22 = "",--That kak woulda sold his mother for a dollar.
loc_jr1_57_23 = "",--Don't feel bad. He was a bad man, for sure.
loc_jr1_57_24 = "",--He was always on the vuvuzela, so my thanks.
loc_jr1_58_01 = "",--A luta continua!
loc_jr1_58_02 = "",--These coppers ain't worth a yak's baff.
loc_jr1_58_03 = "",--Make these guys believers.
loc_jr1_58_04 = "",--Make them earn their tom tonight, yeah? For sure.
loc_jr1_58_05 = "",--Do it like you did it at the warehouse. Yeah, I saw that. For sure.
loc_jr1_58_06 = "",--We could have done with you guys in Rhodesia.
loc_jr1_58_07 = "",--You guys know how to fight.
loc_jr1_58_08 = "",--Hey, you wouldn't be interested in a little mercenary work, eh? No?
loc_jr1_58_09 = "",--You fellas hit harder than my first wife.
loc_jr1_58_10 = "",--Don't worry about all the bodies. We have... a facility.
loc_jr1_58_11 = "",--Yeah. For sure.
loc_jr1_59_01 = "",--Okay, patience now, my friends. Each vault has a short timelock. You know, for security.
loc_jr1_59_02 = "",--And now we wait for the vault timelock to run down. This is a secured site, you know.
loc_jr1_59_03 = "",--Now just let the timelock run down, dear friends. It will be worth it, I promise.
loc_jr1_59_04 = "",--Friends, let the timelock go tick-tock, yeah? Your patience will be rewarded.
loc_jr1_59_05 = "",--Just hold on to your horses, friends. The vault will be open any second.
loc_jr1_59_06 = "",--Vault's take just a moment to open. A security measure. Security is important, you know.
loc_jr1_60_01 = "",--Shit, those fucking shit-eating kerels shut down the unlocking. Get it going again!
loc_jr1_60_02 = "",--Well, fuck and shit. Cops shut down the vault's opening. Get it going again, and kill any fucking kerel that goes near it.
loc_jr1_60_03 = "",--Hey, what happened? Ah, shit - cops interrupted the vault. Get it going again. And kill the fucking cops.
loc_jr1_61_01 = "",--Ah! Yes. The vault is opening again! Good!
loc_jr1_61_02 = "",--That's it. Well done! The vault is opening again!
loc_jr1_61_03 = "",--Fuck yes, my friends. Okay, the vault is opening again. Good!
loc_jr1_62_01 = "",--You do the shooting, my friends, I'll just blend in a bit with my Murky Uniform. Don't get me mixed up, okay?
loc_jr1_62_02 = "",--You do all the killing, yeah? I'm cyberwarfare, not a fucking commando. My uniform should keep me out of the fray.
loc_jr1_62_03 = "",--I need you guys to distribute the violence, yeah? My uniform should let me blend in with them, keep out of the fight.
loc_jr1_63_01 = "",--I'm hearing over the comms that they've set up a sniper ambush ahead. Watch your heads!
loc_jr1_63_02 = "",--Protocol means they'll have snipers ready to ambush up ahead. You fellas watch yourselves, yeah?
loc_jr1_63_03 = "",--If they're going by the book they'll have snipers set up ahead. These cocks always go by the book.
loc_jr1_64_01 = "",--Just heard they've got a squad of bulldozers up in the area ahead. They'll fuck us in the ass. I don't want that. Watch it!
loc_jr1_64_02 = "",--Standard response is to get a strong line of armor in there, so expect bulldozers up ahead. Get ready!
loc_jr1_64_03 = "",--If I know them, and I know them, trust me on that, they'll have bulldozers up ahead. So get ready for those shits, yeah.
loc_jr1_65_01 = "",--Well, fuck me, that was a waste of time. The vault is empty. Find the good ones, you hear?!
loc_jr1_65_02 = "",--Well, I'll be a donkeys uncle - empty fucking vault! Only open the good ones, yeah? For sure.
loc_jr1_65_03 = "",--Of all the vaults, you had to open an empty one! Try again, friends.
loc_jr1_66_01 = "",--Okay, you can only zipline up two at a time. And there's no going back down, friends.
loc_jr1_66_02 = "",--Only two of you at a time up the zipline, please. And it's a one way trip. But what a trip, yeah?
loc_jr1_66_03 = "",--Only two riding the ziplines at a time, my good friends. And once you're up, that's it. So come on.
loc_jr1_67_01 = "",--It's simplicity itself, friends. Just press the button of the vault you want to open. Just be sure it actually contains something.
loc_jr1_67_02 = "",--This system is built to be simple. All you got to do is choose a vault and press a button. Easy, yeah? For sure.
loc_jr1_67_03 = "",--It's easy. Just choose a vault, and press the button. That will start the timelock, and the vault will open. Abracadabra!
loc_jr1_68_01 = "ドカーン! 上出来だ、続けろ!",--Kaboom, good work! Keep it up!
loc_jr1_68_02 = "",--That was a bang! Most satisfying!
loc_jr1_68_03 = "",--That was fun!
loc_jr1_69_01 = "",--And another one bites the dust! Nice!
loc_jr1_69_02 = "",--Boom, bang and tumble! Great!
loc_jr1_69_03 = "",--Shame to see nice tech blow up like that. But fuck it!
loc_jr1_70_01 = "",--Listen! That vault contains the prototype. It's in one of the crates. The others are decoys..
loc_jr1_70_02 = "",--Ahhh! There's a valuable prototype in that vault. It's in one of the crates, and not in the others. Open them to find it.
loc_jr1_70_03 = "",--There's a lovely little prototype in one of those crates, dear friends. Open them to find it.
loc_jr1_71_01 = "",--Another vault opens. Bravo!
loc_jr1_71_02 = "",--That's another vault open and ready.
loc_jr1_71_03 = "",--Ahhh, and another vault is ready to be plundered!
pln_jr1_brf_01_01 = "砂漠にあるMurkyの「Black Ridge」の襲撃をLockeが依頼してきた。かつで空軍施設だった建物だが、冷戦後にMurkyが買い取り、「フォート·ノックス」と姿を変えた。金目のものがあるのは間違いなしだ。が、内部については調べがついてない。内部はネットにあまり接続してないせいで、事前調査であまり得られなかったんだ。ただ1つハッキリしてる物がある...こっそり忍び込むなんてことはできないって事だ。ドンパチの準備をしていけ。",--Locke has us hitting a Murky facility out in the desert. Black Ridge. Was an old air force place, back in the day. Murkywater bought it up after the Cold War, turned it into their own Fort Knox, so you can bet they're holding some serious loot here. Not sure what to expect. Not much online, so we got little in the way of intel. One thing is certain though - you're not going to sneak through this one. Dress for loud.
pln_jr1_01_01 = "許可しよう、ギャング共",--Give 'em the authorization, gang.
pln_jr1_01_02 = "ショーの時間だ",--Show 'em, gang
pln_jr1_01_03 = "それにしよう!",--Let em have it, gang!
pln_jr1_02_01 = "お前ら、Lockeの箱を見つけろ。ストロボ付きの箱だ。",--Find Locke's crates, gang. Look for the ones with the strobe on.
pln_jr1_02_02 = "Lockeの箱を見つけろ。ストロボ付きの木箱だ。",--Hey guys, remember to find the crates Locke has left. They got a strobe on.
pln_jr1_02_03 = "お前ら、Lockeの箱を見つける必要がある。ストロボ付きの箱だ。次にやるべきことがわかる。",--Come on, crew. Locke needs us to find those crates. Show him how we do it.
pln_jr1_03_01 = "野郎ども、ドアを捨てちまえ。",--Ditch the charges at the door, guys.
pln_jr1_03_02 = "Lockeはドアを吹き飛ばすように指示があった。設置して離れるんだ。",--Locke wants us to blow that door. Better drop the charges off there.
pln_jr1_03_03 = "Lockeの指示に従え。爆薬をドアに設置するんだ。",--We better follow Locke's directions on this one. Take the charges to the door.
pln_jr1_04_01 = "彼の話をよく聞けよ。",--Better do what he says.
pln_jr1_04_02 = "すこし揺れてるな。ベストな状況だ。",--Sounds a little unhinged. Best do it.
pln_jr1_04_03 = "Lockeは少し怒ってるようだ。彼の指示に従ったほうがいいな。",--Locke sounds a bit...mad. We'd better do what he says.
pln_jr1_05_01 = "近くにセキュリティルームがあるはずだ。溶接でエアロックを外して、ライトを緑色に点灯させろ。",--There should be a security room close by. Use the arc welder to cut through and green llight the airlock.
pln_jr1_05_02 = "Lockeはセキュリティルームに行けと指示してる。そいつを見つけて、シーケンスを承認しろ。",--Locke wants us to cut through to the security room. Find it, gang, then approve the sequence
pln_jr1_05_03 = "お前ら、警備室を探せ。扉を溶接で外して、シーケンスを認証しろ。",--Guys, look for a security room around there. Use the arc welder to cut through, and approve the sequence.
pln_jr1_06_01 = "お前ら、早くLockeのところにバッグを持って行け。大きなシャフトを探すんだ。",--Get the bags up to Locke as soon as you can, crew. Look for the large vertical shaft around there.
pln_jr1_06_02 = "シャフトにあるzip-lineにバッグを固定して、Lockeのところに持っていけ。",--Find the shaft and zipline those bags up to Locke ASAP.
pln_jr1_06_03 = "聞いたぞ。バッグをzip-lineで上に上げろ。Lockeが上で待ってる。",--You heard him. Get the bags onto the ziplines in the shaft. Get them up to Locke.
pln_jr1_07_01 = "彼がLockeだ。",--That's him. Locke.
pln_jr1_07_02 = "彼がLockeだ。",--So that's Locke.
pln_jr1_07_03 = "そこにいる彼がLockeだ。",--There he is. Locke.
pln_jr1_08_01 = "Lockeの脱出計画ではレーダーを吹き飛ばす必要がある。気にしておけよ。",--Locke's escape plan depends on blasting the radars, gang. See to it.
pln_jr1_08_02 = "Lockeからレーダーの破壊を頼まれた。やってくれ。",--Locke wants us to sabotage the radars. Better get to it.
pln_jr1_08_03 = "野郎ども、次はレーダーを破壊しろ。",--Putting those radars out of action is our next job, gang. Do it.
pln_jr1_09_01 = "よくやったお前達。Lockeは既に俺たちに分け前を送っている。彼について詳しくはわからないが、少なくとも信用するに値するはずだ。",--Great job, crew. Locke's already wired our cut. Still not sure about this guy, but maybe we can trust him.
pln_jr1_09_02 = "激しかったな。Lockeは既に報酬を送って来てる。彼についてはまだ不安な点が多いが、様子見だな。",--That was intense, gang. Locke already sent over our share. Still uneasy about him, but let's see where things go with this guy.
pln_jr1_09_03 = "上手くやったな。Lockeは俺たちの分け前をもう送っている。彼についてはまだ不安な点が多いが、どういう男か見定める必要がありそうだな。",--Nicely done, guys. Locke transferred our cut. I don't know about this guy, yet, but let's see how things pan out with him.
loc_jr2_cbf_01_01 = "",--You've really put the shits up Murkywater, man. They're moving a large portion of their cash reserves away from the East Coast. Heavily guarded cargo plane, yeah. For sure. It's gonna be most vulnerable when its in flight so I'm smuggling you onto that plane. Deal with the guards, open the cargo doors and let that money spill down. Hardly sounds like work at all, huh?
loc_jr2_cnc_01_01 = "",--Murkywater are transferring some huge amounts of currency by plane. We're going to get it.
loc_jr2_cnc_01_02 = "",--Murkywater are moving some huge currency reserves by cargo plane. I've got an idea to get it.
loc_jr2_cnc_01_03 = "",--Just heard that Murkywater are going to try and shift some cash by plane. Gives me an idea.
loc_jr2_01_01 = "",--My friends! We are approaching the location I have selected for the drop point. So, without further ado...
loc_jr2_01_02 = "",--Friends! Beautiful friends! How is the flight? We are getting close to the drop location. So, please, open the hatch and...
loc_jr2_01_03 = "",--Dear friends! Enjoying the flight so far, yes? You're almost at the location I have selected as a drop point. So...
loc_jr2_01_04 = "",--Hello, friends. You're almost at the drop point I have selected, so, if you would emerge and, as you say, get the party started.
loc_jr2_01_05 = "",--Locke to Payday gang, come in. Okay, so, the plane is nearing the drop point! Let's not dilly-dally here in the dark, let us rise!
loc_jr2_01_06 = "",--Greetings, friends. The plane is almost above the drop point. Please, get out, kill some Murkies and let's make that money ours, yeah?
loc_jr2_02_01 = "上がれ! 上がれ! 上がれ、上がれ、上がれ!",--Up! Up! Up, up, up!
loc_jr2_02_02 = "そこを出るんだ! 貨物室に行くんだ!",--Get out of there! Into the cargo hold!
loc_jr2_02_03 = "早くそこから出ろ!",--Out of there, come on!
loc_jr2_02_04 = "そこから出るんだ!",--Out of that compartment!
loc_jr2_02_05 = "上るんだ!",--Now, rise, my friends!
loc_jr2_03_01 = "まずは、スイッチを操作して貨物室のドアを開くんだ!",--First, hit the switch to open the cargo doors!
loc_jr2_03_02 = "そのスイッチで、貨物室のドアが開くぞ!",--The switch there will open the cargo doors!
loc_jr2_03_03 = "貨物室のドアスイッチを操作するんだ!",--Hit the cargo door switch, friends!
loc_jr2_03_04 = "いいぞ! すぐにドアを開けるんだ、そのスイッチで!",--Yes, good - now open the doors. The switch there!
loc_jr2_03_05 = "",--Get those doors open! The switch is right there!
loc_jr2_04_01 = "",--I would do it from here if I could, dear friends, but I can't. So please open the fucking cargo doors.
loc_jr2_04_02 = "",--Let me give your memories a jog, yeah? Open the cargo bay door. Please.
loc_jr2_04_03 = "",--Don't forget, dear friends - you need to open the cargo bay doors.
loc_jr2_04_04 = "",--Stop standing around. Open the doors. Fuck me, what's wrong with you.
loc_jr2_04_05 = "",--Your dicks ain't for holding. They're for fucking. And there's a lot of Murkies up there waiting for it. Apologies to any ladies in the crew.
loc_jr2_05_01 = "よし。あぁ空気がうまい! 現在パレットは機械制御の留め具でデッキに固定されているんだ。その留め具を制御してるヤツがいて、それを操作するものは...ああ、その上にある。この飛行機の前方に向かっていくと上に上がれるはずだ。",--Good. Ah, fresh air! Now, the pallets are secured to the deck by mechanical fasteners. These fasteners are controlled by the logistics officer, and his controls are... ah, up there. And the access to the upper deck is at the front of the plane.
loc_jr2_05_02 = "",--Excellent. The increased drag will slow the plane and force the pilot to fly lower. As expected. Now, get to the cargo controls. You see them above you? So close, yet so far. The only way to get up there is by the stairs at the front of the plane.
loc_jr2_05_03 = "",--Superb. The cash is loaded on pallets, which are secured to the deck. Only the logisitics officer can release them, and his controls are up above you - you see? To acces them, you must get to the stairs at the front of the aircraft, and then return this way.
loc_jr2_06_01 = "",--Bravo! Now, simply operate the officer's controls. It is a tier-7 job, monkey work, anyone can do it.
loc_jr2_06_02 = "",--Now, just have a go at those logistics controls. It's a simple job. Even a retarded samango could do it. And sometimes they do, the little shits.
loc_jr2_06_03 = "",--Good. The logisitic officers' controls are right in front of you. Operate them. Let the money go.
loc_jr2_07_01 = "",--Just press the button. You can understand that, yeah?
loc_jr2_07_02 = "",--You see the button there? All you need to do is press it.
loc_jr2_07_03 = "",--Be a good little criminal, and press that fucking button!
loc_jr2_08_01 = "",--Great. The money is in the sky! Drifting down exactly where I want it to. Like a million-dollar snowflake. Oh, and grab the parachutes!
loc_jr2_08_02 = "",--Yes, good...picking up telemetry from the money now. Right on target. Oh, why don't you grab those parachutes there.
loc_jr2_08_03 = "",--So, the money is falling, for you. Good. Now, grab yourselves some parachutes and join it. Come on, my little angels.
loc_jr2_09_01 = "さあドアから出るんだ、いけ!",--And out the door you go!
loc_jr2_09_02 = "空に飛びだすんだ、友よ!",--Out into the sky, friends!
loc_jr2_09_03 = "恐れるな、さあ飛べ!",--Don't hesitate - just jump!
loc_jr2_10_01 = "ドロップゾーン付近だ、さあ飛ぶんだ!",--Dropzone is directly below! Jump now!
loc_jr2_10_02 = "怖がるなよ。とにかく飛ぶんだ!",--Don't be scared. Just jump!
loc_jr2_10_03 = "",--The dropzone will be long gone if you don't hurry. Jump!
loc_jr2_11_01 = "",--The first pallet hit the ground around here somewhere. Find it, mark the position and I'll come and collect it.
loc_jr2_11_02 = "",--Everyone on the ground, sound as a pound? Great. Now look around for the first money pallet. When you find 'it, pop a flare and I'll be right over.
loc_jr2_11_03 = "",--You're all down, yes? No broken ankles? Good. Now find the first money pallet. They're there somewhere. Find em, and light a flare.
loc_jr2_12_01 = "",--Check roofs, buildings, car parks - all those kinds of places. That pallet is around there somewhere.
loc_jr2_12_02 = "",--Come on, keep looking. Have you checked every roof? I know it's in the area.
loc_jr2_12_03 = "",--Don't stop looking, you kaks. I tell you the pallet is there somewhere.
loc_jr2_13_01 = "",--Good. That's the first. Now find the second.
loc_jr2_13_02 = "",--You're doing good, my friends. But that's just the first. Find the second pallet.
loc_jr2_13_03 = "",--That's the first pallet. All right, good. Now, onto the second.
loc_jr2_14_01 = "",--Come on, keep looking. There's only so many places it can be.
loc_jr2_14_02 = "",--Don't get distracted by the beautiful little town. You're looking for a fuck-ton of money, friends.
loc_jr2_14_03 = "",--Remember what you're looking for. Big pile of cash. Shit big pile.
loc_jr2_15_01 = "",--And that's the second. Oh, I can smell the wealth! But greed is good, yeah. For sure. Find the third pallet.
loc_jr2_15_02 = "",--There's two pallets found. Now the third. Come on, beautiful friends. Keep looking.
loc_jr2_15_03 = "",--The second pallet! Good. But good things come in threes. Like that week all my wives died. Find the third pallet.
loc_jr2_16_01 = "",--Come on, stop playing with your little dick cop friends. Find the third pallet, you poes.
loc_jr2_16_02 = "",--I don't care if you gotta shinny up a wall like fucking Spiderman. Look everywhere for that third pallet.
loc_jr2_16_03 = "",--Are you so dumb that the third pallet - a fucking inanimated object - can hide from you? Find that cunt.
loc_jr2_17_01 = "",--Ah, fuck me with a firestick. Fucking pallet broke and we got fucking bundles of cash scattered around like an old whore's knickers. Find them and bag them.
loc_jr2_17_02 = "",--Jesus fucking Mugabe. Look at this. Fucking pallet broke! You're going to have to bag all the spilled loot, get it back to the pallet.
loc_jr2_17_03 = "",--Ah shit, this one broke on impact. We got bundles of cash scattered about. You're going to have to find them, bag them and get them back here.
loc_jr2_18_01 = "",--Come on, what's fucking wrong with you. Those bundles can't have gone too far.
loc_jr2_18_02 = "",--Find those fucking bundles, will you? Analysis of trajectory indicates...they must be fucking close!
loc_jr2_18_03 = "",--Look, my friends, if this is going to work, sometimes you have to do what I say. And I'm saying find those fucking bundles!!
loc_jr2_19_01 = "",--Okay. Well, you know where it is, but I don't fucking know. Light a flare, yeah?
loc_jr2_19_02 = "",--Okay. Now help your friend Locke. Light a flare. Show me where the money is.
loc_jr2_19_03 = "",--Nice, nice. Now spark a flare close by. Show me where I'm flying.
loc_jr2_20_01 = "",--Okay. Good. Makes things easier. Tell you what else would make it easier - lighting a flare to guide me in.
loc_jr2_20_02 = "",--That should make things easier. Say, why don't one of you guys light a flare for me too.
loc_jr2_20_03 = "",--Nice. That should help. And speaking of help, so would lighting a flare. You get my hint, friends?
loc_jr2_21_01 = "",--My eyes aren't what they were. Help an old man out and light a flare, yeah?
loc_jr2_21_02 = "",--Was there a radio problem earlier? Need a flare lit, friends, yeah?
loc_jr2_21_03 = "",--Come on, chums. No dawdling. Light that flare for me!
loc_jr2_22_01 = "",--All right. I'm coming in. You see a big black fucking chopper, that's me. Unless we're talking about what's hidden in your mums knicker drawer.
loc_jr2_22_02 = "",--I'm flying in. Don't shoot if you see a big fucking helicopter flying at you, right?
loc_jr2_22_03 = "",--Don't shoot down the big helicopter that's coming in for the money, okay? That's me. Yeah, for sure.
loc_jr2_23_01 = "",--Ah! Yes, I see it. I'm coming in. Be ready to attach the pallets to the helicopter. And do it quickly, if that is possible. Things are hot.
loc_jr2_23_02 = "",--I see the flare. Bravo! On approach. When I am there, would you please attach the pallet to the helicopter. With all haste, I might add,
loc_jr2_23_03 = "",--The flare is burning nicely. Here I come. If I may crave another boon, would you mind attaching the pallet to the helicopter when I am in position?
loc_jr2_24_01 = "",--Okay. Here I am. Now, if you could just affix the straps to the pallet and I can evacuate this beautiful mountain of money.
loc_jr2_24_02 = "",--Friends! I am here and in position! Please, when the opportunity allows, take the straps and attach them to that wonderful stack of money.
loc_jr2_24_03 = "",--Dear hearts! You see me? Yes, I am here. For sure. I hate to be a bother, but would you mind strapping that lovely money to my helicopter?
loc_jr2_25_01 = "",--Come on, you kaks! Strap the money to the chopper so I can take it away!
loc_jr2_25_02 = "",--Hey! Don't forget to strap the fucking money to the chopper!
loc_jr2_25_03 = "",--Are you fucking stupid? I said strap the money to the chopper!
loc_jr2_26_01 = "",--Ah kak - those poes are bringing in more SWAT turrets, with the express purpose of bringing me down. All right, I can't pick you up in town, but I am prepared for this.
loc_jr2_26_02 = "",--I'm hearing that the kerel are sending more SWAT turrets to take out my helicopter. I can't pick you up in town. But I prepared for this.
loc_jr2_26_03 = "",--Seeing a lot of SWAT vans rolling in. Those kaks can bring this chopper down. I can't pick you up here. But I have a plan...
loc_jr2_27_01 = "",--I'm going to meet you just outside town. Best way for you to shake these kerel is the sewers. Get down there. I've arranged a little something.
loc_jr2_27_02 = "",--I will meet you on the edge of town, but I don't want you bringing the whole fucking cop army. Get in the sewers. I've organised transport.
loc_jr2_27_03 = "",--I will collect you on the edge of town but get there are quickly and without the cops in tow. Get down to the sewers!
loc_jr2_28_01 = "",--You'll see a bit of thermal paste down there. Just in case those sewers have any obstructions, you know.
loc_jr2_28_02 = "",--I left a case of thermal paste for you down there. Make sure you grab it.
loc_jr2_28_03 = "",--There might be grates in the sewer, so I left you a little present - some thermal paste. Aren't I nice to you?
loc_jr2_29_01 = "",--Grab that paste and burn through the gate. Fucking hell.
loc_jr2_29_02 = "",--Look, do I need to tell you everything. Use the thermal paste to burn through the grate.
loc_jr2_29_03 = "",--Come on. Just stick the thermal paste on the grate and burn through. It's not hard.
loc_jr2_30_01 = "",--And another grate. Same as before. Just use the thermal paste.
loc_jr2_30_02 = "",--Another grate, so just treat it like you did before. Burn through with the thermal paste.
loc_jr2_30_03 = "",--It's another grate, but that's fine. Use another batch of thermal paste.
loc_jr2_31_01 = "",--For the sake of a good fuck! You've done this already. Just put paste on the grate!
loc_jr2_31_02 = "",--You're too close to finishing to fuck up now. Just slap the paste onto the grate and burn through!
loc_jr2_31_03 = "",--Holy shit, what is the delay. Burn the grate away with the thermal paste!
loc_jr2_32_01 = "",--There's the boat. Hop in, my good friends! Let us take her for gentle cruise.
loc_jr2_32_02 = "",--A nice rubber dinghy. All aboard!
loc_jr2_32_03 = "",--See that boat? That's your way out right there. Yeah, for sure. Get in.
loc_jr2_33_01 = "",--I need all of you in the boat, as soon as possible, thank you very fucking much.
loc_jr2_33_02 = "",--That boat needs people inside it. You people. Do what the boat needs, yeah?
loc_jr2_33_03 = "",--Come on, just get into the fucking boat. Fuck me, what's wrong with you people?
loc_jr2_34_01 = "",--That's it. Good! I'm waiting for you.
loc_jr2_34_02 = "",--I'm waiting for you. Keep driving that boat to me.
loc_jr2_34_03 = "",--That's right. Keep going. Almost here, my friends!
loc_jr2_35_01 = "",--Get aboard! That was a fucking excellent job, my friends!
loc_jr2_35_02 = "",--Come on. Climb aboard! Well fucking done, my friends!
loc_jr2_35_03 = "",--Get aboard, dear friends! That was fucking beautifully done!
loc_jr2_36_01 = "",--The pallet fell on the roof, huh? All right, so get on the roof. Look for a ladder.
loc_jr2_36_02 = "",--Have a look around for a ladder, if you want to get up on that roof. And you want to get up on that roof, I assure you.
loc_jr2_36_03 = "",--Look around for a ladder. I'm sure that with energy properly applied to a search you will profit. For sure.
loc_jr2_37_01 = "",--Get up on the roofs, friends. Maybe you will see things clearer up there, yeah? You'll probably need a ladder to get up.
loc_jr2_37_02 = "",--Might be good to see things from the roofs, huh? For sure. Look for a ladder to get up.
loc_jr2_37_03 = "",--Don't forget to check the roofs of the buildings. Look for a ladder.
loc_jr2_38_01 = "",--Don't forget. Look for the ladder, dear friends.
loc_jr2_38_02 = "",--Let me remind you - look for a ladder.
loc_jr2_38_03 = "",--You poes need to find a fucking ladder. Fuck me. Come on!
loc_jr2_39_01 = "",--It looks like one of the pallets landed on the roof of the diner. Imagine all that money falling in your eggs and grits, eh! For sure.
loc_jr2_39_02 = "",--One of the pallets hit the roof of the diner. I bet that had those Yanks shitting in their coffee, yeah. For sure.
loc_jr2_39_03 = "",--One of the pallets is on the roof of the diner. What would those burger-flippers do to have that kind of cash, eh?
loc_jr2_40_01 = "",--There's a service ladder leading to the roof. You'll need a keycard to access it though. Got to be one here somewhere.
loc_jr2_40_02 = "",--That diner has a service ladder leading up to the roof, but you'll need a keycard to get to it. Look around for one.
loc_jr2_40_03 = "",--The roof of that diner can be accessed by a service ladder, but you're going to need a keycard to get to it. Surely there's one around somewhere.
loc_jr2_41_01 = "",--Listen you fucking poes. You're only getting on the roof from the store room ladder, and you're only getting in that with the keycard. Look for it!
loc_jr2_41_02 = "",--It's like talking to a fucking Frenchman. Listen. If you want to use the service ladder in the diner, you need the keycard. Mon dieu!
loc_jr2_41_03 = "",--Let me remind you. Look for a keycard if you want to get access to the roofs. Kak...
loc_jr2_42_01 = "",--Ah! Those fucking shit-eating poes are stealing my money. Our money...sorry. Stop them!
loc_jr2_42_02 = "",--Well, looks like we have some crafty litte thieves, trying to steal our money. Put them down.
loc_jr2_42_03 = "",--Look over there. Little cop shits are stealing the money. The fuck is the world coming to! Kill them!
loc_jr2_43_01 = "",--Ah! Yes, I believe that ladder will be useful!
loc_jr2_43_02 = "",--Take that ladder, my friends. Take it, and profit!
loc_jr2_43_03 = "",--I do believe we can put that ladder to good use. Yeah, for sure!
loc_jr2_44_01 = "",--Another successful acquisition! Well done, my friends!
loc_jr2_44_02 = "",--Yet another successful collaboration! You have my thanks, my admiration and, most importantly, your share of the money.
loc_jr2_44_03 = "",--That was a fucking great job, friends. It had it all. Excitement, action - like a movie! And best of all, a happy ending.
loc_jr2_45_01 = "",--Now, everyone to the chopper! Come on!
loc_jr2_45_02 = "",--Almost here. Hurry! You beautiful bastards!
loc_jr2_45_03 = "それだそれだ。さぁ来るんだ!",--That's it. That's it! You're almost here, come on!
pln_jr2_brf_01_01 = "よし、作戦はこうだ。Lockeの手引きでお前らは機内に忍び込んでおく。奴からの合図を待って、飛び出せ。激しい抵抗には遭わないだろう―なにしろ乗員だけだからな。金はでかい塊になってまとまっている。貨物扉からそいつを放り出し、地上に着いたら回収する。簡単だろ?",--Okay, here's the plan. Locke is going to have you smuggled onto the plane. Wait until you get his signal and burst out. Resistance should be light - just the crew. The money is packed into large pallets. Get them out of the cargo doors, and we'll collect them when they hit the ground. Simple.
pln_jr2_intro_01_01 = "よしお前ら... Lockeとつなぐぞ。",--Okay gang...patching Locke through to you.
pln_jr2_intro_01_02 = "大丈夫か、お前ら。ほら、Lockeだ。",--Hope you're okay up there, crew. Here's Locke.
pln_jr2_intro_01_03 = "オーライ、お前ら。Lockeだ...気をつけろよ。",--All right, guys. Here's Locke... Be careful up there.
pln_jr2_01_01 = "",--Hurry, guys! Into the hold!
pln_jr2_01_02 = "",--Come on, gang. Out of that hidey-hole!
pln_jr2_01_03 = "",--You heard Locke, crew - into the cargo hold!
pln_jr2_02_01 = "",--You're going to have to fight your way to the end of the plane, get up the stairs and then fight back along. Only way to reach the cargo controls.
pln_jr2_02_02 = "",--Just fight to the front of the plane, up the stairs and then all the way back. It's the only way to reach those controls.
pln_jr2_02_03 = "",--You need to make your way to the front of the plane, gang. Then up the stairs, and all the way back. Only way to get to the controls.
pln_jr2_03_01 = "",--Hustle it, guys. You need to get on the ground near the money.
pln_jr2_03_02 = "",--Gang, hurry with the parachutes. Don't get off course.
pln_jr2_03_03 = "",--Guys, get the parachutes, quickly! Don't get too far from the money!
pln_jr2_04_01 = "",--Light that flare for Locke, crew.
pln_jr2_04_02 = "",--Gang, don't forget - you need to light a flare before Locke will come in.
pln_jr2_04_03 = "",--Crew, remember - Locke needs you to light that flare.
pln_jr2_05_01 = "",--That money needs to be tightly secured by the straps before Locke can take off.
pln_jr2_05_02 = "",--Make sure those straps are nicely fastened. Don't want Locke dropping the loot too early now.
pln_jr2_05_03 = "",--Ensure all of the straps are secure. Don't give Locke an excuse to accidentally drop the money.
pln_jr2_06_01 = "",--The hell he have in mind?
pln_jr2_06_02 = "あいつは何を考えてるんだ?",--What's he thinking?
pln_jr2_06_03 = "",--How's he going to get you out of this?
pln_jr2_07_01 = "",--Get into the boat, gang! We're almost done here!
pln_jr2_07_02 = "",--Don't hang around, crew. Everyone - into the boat!
pln_jr2_07_03 = "",--You heard what Locke said, guys. Into the boat and let's get out of here.
pln_can_01_01 = "あのチンピラ共を全員片づけるんだ、ギャング共。",--Kill every one of those thugs, gang.
pln_can_01_02 = "野郎共、あのチンピラ共を放っておくわけにはいかねえ。対処しろ。",--Guys, we can't risk leaving those thugs around. Deal with them.
pln_can_01_03 = "あのチンピラ共を始末するんだ。",--You need to eliminate those thugs.
pln_can_02_01 = "妖精さんを見つけるんだぞ。仕事するように脅すんだ。",--Don't forget to find the elves. Shout at them to make them work.
pln_can_02_02 = "妖精さんを見つけろ。おもちゃをまた作るように脅せよ。",--Find the elves in the toyshop. You need to shout at them to get them making toys again.
pln_can_02_03 = "妖精さんの仕事を再開させろ。怒鳴りつければいい。",--Get the elves working on the product. Just holler at them.
pln_can_03_01 = "サツ共を片づけて、妖精さんに作業を続けさせろ、ギャング共!",--Keep the cops dropping, and the elves hopping, gang!
pln_can_03_02 = "サツに妖精さんに手を出させるなよ、野郎共!",--Don't let the cops interfere with the elves, crew!
pln_can_03_03 = "サツに妖精さんを好き勝手にさせるなよ。",--Don't go letting the cops mess with the elves.
pln_can_04_01 = "Vladはプレゼントを煙突に入れてほしいそうだ。",--Vlad needs you to secure those bags in the chimney.
pln_can_04_02 = "そこの煙突が見えるか?Vladはそこに「プレゼント」を入れてほしいんだとよ。",--You see the chimney there? That's where Vlad needs those "presents".
pln_can_04_03 = "Vladの話を聞いたろ。バッグを煙突に入れるんだ。",--You heard Vlad. Get those bags into the chimney.
pln_can_brf_01 = "こいつは単純な仕事だ。チンピラ共がちょっとした店を運営している。Vladが欲しがっている「妖精さん」が詰めたコカインを手に入れろ。チンピラを始末して、妖精さんに詰めるよう脅すんだ。Vladが欲しいだけコカインを集めれば、それで終わりだ。",--Straightforward job, this one. A bunch of thugs are running a little operation. Got a bunch of "elves" cutting coke that Vlad wants. Deal with the thugs, and then get the elves producing. Shouting at them should do it. Get as much coke as Vlad needs, and we're done.
pln_can_intro_01 = "よし、ここだ。",--Okay, here it is.
pln_can_intro_02 = "目の前にあるのが「おもちゃ屋」だ。",--There's the "toyshop" right ahead.
pln_can_intro_03 = "ああ。いわゆるおもちゃ屋だ。行くぞ。",--All right. The so-called toyshop. Just ahead.
vld_can_01_01 = "ホッホッホ、クソッタレ共!",--Ho ho ho, bitches!
vld_can_01_02 = "メぇぇぇぇぇ～～～～リぃぃぃぃぃぃ～～～～クリッスマぁぁぁぁぁぁぁ～～～～～～～～ス!!!!!!!",--Merrrrrrrry Christmas!
vld_can_01_03 = "ジングル \"マジクソッタレ\" ベ～ル!!",--Jingle their motherfucking bells!
vld_can_02_01 = "あのチンピラ共はショボいおもちゃ屋をやってんだ。あいつらは悪い子だった。始末して中へ入れ。",--Those are the thugs running this little toyshop. They've been naughty boys. Drop 'em, and get inside.
vld_can_02_02 = "よし、あのチンピラ共がクリスマスに暴れる前にやってやれ。それから工場へ入れ。",--All right, drop those thugs before they can steal Christmas. Then into the workshop.
vld_can_02_03 = "チンピラ共がいるな。奴らを始末して妖精さん達に会いにいけ。",--There's the thugs. Take 'em down and get to the elves.
vld_can_03_02 = "Cokeを詰めてる奴らを探せ。その「妖精さん」達に作ってるおもちゃはサンタ·「クソ」スマス、俺のためのものだって教えてやれ! いいな?",--Look for the guys packing the coke. Make sure these "elves" know they're making toys for Santa fucking Christmas! Me! Okay?
vld_can_03_03 = "さあ、妖精さんを探すんだ。俺におもちゃを作るように言い聞かせろ。おもちゃってのはつまり、Cokeのクソ塊のことだよ!",--Now, search the toyshop for the elves. Convince them they're making toys for me now. And when I say toys, I mean fuckloads of coke!
vld_can_04_01 = "サツが来るぞ! クリスマスをぶち壊しにな。好き勝手やらせるなよ、あとバカ妖精共の作業を止めるな。",--Here come the cops! Come to fuck up Christmas. Hold them off, and make sure those elf bastards don't slacken off.
vld_can_04_02 = "いつも誰かが俺のクリスマスを滅茶苦茶にしたがるんだよ! サツがこっちに来る。奴らに妖精さんを止めさせるなよ、いいな?",--Someone always wants to fuck my Christmas! Here come the cops. Don't let them screw the elves, yes?
vld_can_04_03 = "ポリ公め。あいつらはクリスマスの亡霊かクソ! 対処しろ! 妖精さんを守れ! 全力で妖精さんを守るんだ!",--Damn cops. They're the ghost of Christmas fuck! Deal with them! Protect the elves! At all costs, protect the elves!
vld_can_05_01 = "いいぞ! さて、プレゼントはどこに入れるかな?煙突だよ!",--Nice! Now, where do presents go? Into the chimney!
vld_can_05_02 = "サンタがどうやってプレゼントを届けるかは知ってるよな?この箱を煙突に入れるんだ。",--Now, you know how Santa delivers presents, yes? Into the chimney with those packages.
vld_can_05_03 = "ワンダフル。冬のワンダーランドみたいだな?ああ! さあ、Cokeのバッグを煙突に入れてくれ。",--Wonderful. Like winter wonderland, yes? Yes! Now, please let's get those bags of coke into the chimney.
vld_can_06_01 = "雪よ降れ、雪よ降れ、雪よ降れ...",--Let it snow, let it snow, let it snow....
vld_can_06_02 = "ホワイトクリスマスをVladに!",--Another white christmas for Vlad!
vld_can_06_03 = "クルミは火薬でローストされて、ジャックフロストは鼻を鳴らす...",--Chestnuts roasting on an open fire, Jack Frost snorting up his nose...
vld_can_06_04 = "プレゼントの季節だから、お前らにちょっとしたものをやるよ。",--Since it's the season of giving, here's a little something for you.
vld_can_06_05 = "Vladは幸せだ。ほら、受け取りな!",--You've made Vlad happy. Here, have this!
vld_can_06_06 = "いい子にしてたな。ほら、プレゼントだ。",--You've been good little heisters. Here, have a gift.
vld_can_07_01 = "おい! 製品が完成したみたいだ。取りに行って妖精共に役割を忘れさせるな! 要は怒鳴りつけろってことだ!",--Hey! Looks like productivity is dropping. Go and give those elves a tongue-fucking they won't forget! That means shout at them!
vld_can_07_02 = "妖精のペースが落ちてるな。奴らに歯医者のことを伝えろ。テキトーにしてたら、その歯を抜いてやるってな!",--The elves are slowing down. Go and tell them about the dental plan we offer. Work harder, or get your fucking teeth smashed in!
vld_can_07_03 = "妖精共にペースを上げないとケツの穴に俺の拳をプレゼントしてやるって伝えろ。",--Tell the elves to work harder, or the only thing they'll get in their stocking is my fist in their ass!
vld_can_07_04 = "あの妖精サボってやがるな?あいつにここでは俺が法律で、いつでもお前をローストできるって伝えろ。",--Is that an elf slacking off there? Go tell him the only union law here is the union of my flamethrower with their chestnuts!
vld_can_07_05 = "おい、妖精共を働かせ続けろ! 奴らに褒美をやれ。働けば、皮を剥がないってな。",--Hey, keep those elves working! Offer them a performance reward. They perform, and I won't fucking skin them.
vld_can_07_06 = "あれでも妖精は一生懸命やってるのか?あいつらに「気合」を入れてやってくれるか?",--Are those elves working as hard as they can? Perhaps you can "motivate" them?
vld_can_07_07 = "あのトンガリ耳のバカどもが。新年を拝みたいなら、もっと働け。そう伝えろ!",--If those pointy eared bastards want to see New Years Day, they better work harder. Tell them that!
vld_can_07_08 = "あの妖精共に本当のクリスマスを思い出させてやれ。銃とヤクのプレゼントだ!",--Remind those elves what Christmas is really about. The production of narcotics at the point of a gun!
vld_can_08_01 = "あいつら死んだぞ。全員。全妖精が。なんだこのクリスマス物語は?",--They're dead. All of them. Every elf. Dead. What the hell kind of Christmas story is this?
vld_can_08_02 = "妖精が全員死んだのか?クソ。クリスマスは中止だ、友よ。",--Are all of the elves dead? Shit. Christmas is cancelled, my friends.
vld_can_08_03 = "おもちゃの街が悲しみに包まれた日だ。妖精さんが全員死んだ。トナカイじゃなくてな。",--It is a sad day in Toytown. All of the elves are dead. Doesn't that just suck a reindeer's dick.
vld_can_09_01 = "よし、DCでパーティを続けるにはこれで十分だ! だが周囲にはBaltimore、Harrisburg、Phillyがある。お前らが作って俺が買えば、このまま東海岸で踊り続けられる。それか帰るかだ。",--All right, that's all I need to keep DC partying! But there's always Baltimore, Harrisburg, Philly. You keep making, I'll keep buying and we'll keep the East Coast dancing, yes? Or you can leave.
vld_can_09_02 = "クリスマスを盛り上げるにはこれで十分だ。だが、ほら、妖精さんに作らせ続けて、俺がもっと盛り上げることもできる。わかるだろ?それか帰るかだ。お前ら次第だ。",--That's enough to keep Christmas cheery. But, you know, you want to keep those elves churning out goodies, I can always spread a little more cheer, you understand? Or you can leave. Up to you.
vld_can_09_03 = "さて、これで脱出できる、ああ、いいだろ。それか...思いついた。そこに残って、妖精をいじめてキレイな「雪」をもっと作ってもいいぞ!",--Well, you can escape, sure, that's fine. Or.......here's an idea. You can stay, bully more elves and make more beautiful snow!
vld_can_10_01 = "",--Okay, the last elf fell off the shelf, yes. Fuck him. Time to leave and enjoy your Christmas bonus, friends!
vld_can_10_02 = "",--Ahhh, there's the last elf dead. Am I sad? No, fuck that elf. We got the toys, so it's time to leave.
vld_can_10_03 = "ああああ...そいつは最後の妖精さんだ。悲しいが、あいつらは役割を果たした。俺たちは必要な物を手に入れた。出発する時間だ、友よ!",--Aaaaand...that's the last elf gone. Sad, but they served their purpose. And we got what we need. Time to leave, friends!
vld_can_11_01 = "クリスマスの奇跡だ! よくやった、我が友よ。地球上に平和が訪れるかもしれないな...来年までは。",--It's a Christmas miracle! Well done, my friends. May there be peace on Earth...until next year.
vld_can_11_02 = "すばらしい! よくやった。今夜のDCはパーティだ!",--Excellent! Well done. DC will party tonight!
vld_can_11_03 = "",--You brought gold, frankincense and myrrh. Myrrh coke to Vlad!
vld_can_12_01 = "ここで俺のいとこからの贈り物を取れ。彼はお前らも暖かくして過ごせって言ってたぞ!",--Here, take this gift from my cousin. He said it should keep you warm!
vld_can_12_02 = "",--I might be in the business of taking, but don't say Vlad never gives back! It's christmas for fuck sake!
vld_can_12_03 = "",--Throw this in a doorway, it should help keeps those naughty children away from the presents they don't deserve!
vld_can_cbf_01 = "",--Every Christmas I set up a little operation - gifts for the children, and "gifts" for the parents, yes? Thing is, supplies are low this year. But! I have found an alternative. A clutch of assholes have an operation near here. Consider it a little toyshop, yes. I need you to get down there, take out the muscle and get the "elves" back to work.
vld_can_cnc_01 = "メリークリスマス、友よ! クリスマスの奇跡について手伝ってくれ。",--Merry christmas, my friends! I need you to help me with a little Christmas miracle.
vld_can_cnc_02 = "",--Office parties all over the capitol will be duller affairs if Uncle Vlad can't supply the Christmas "cheer". You can help.
vld_can_cnc_03 = "私の愛しのおもちゃ屋が問題を抱えてるんだ、親友よ。助けてやってくれないか?",--My little toymakers are having problems, my dear friends. Can you help?
brs_pt1_01_01 = "1分。おい、さっさとやれ。",--One minute. Hey, move your ass.
brs_pt1_01_02 = "1分。すぐ近くだ。",--One minute. So close.
brs_pt1_01_03 = "1分...すぐそこだ。",--One minute...almost there.
brs_pt1_01x_01 = "あと...",--There in....
brs_pt1_01x_02 = "頼む...",--Just give me...
brs_pt1_01x_03 = "もうすぐだ...",--Almost there....
brs_pt1_02_01 = "2分。ケツ穴野郎め、運転を練習しろ。",--Two minutes. Learn to drive, asshole.
brs_pt1_02_02 = "2分。腐れババァ、道を開けろ!",--Two minutes. Get off the road, old cunt!
brs_pt1_02_03 = "2分。おい、クソッタレめ!",--Two minutes. Hey, fuckface!
brs_pt1_03_01 = "3分...下道が混んでる!",--Three minutes...downtown traffic!
brs_pt1_03_02 = "3分...クソプリウスのドライバーめ!",--Three minutes...fucking Prius drivers!
brs_pt1_03_03 = "3分。チャリンコ共、首掻っ切るぞ!",--Three minutes. Cyclists! I'll cut your throat!
brs_pt1_04_01 = "",--Could be a while. Was it Maryland or Massachussetts Ave?
brs_pt1_04_02 = "",--Could be a while. Was it left at the Union or....?
brs_pt1_05_01 = "俺はここだ! ヤギを連れてこい!",--I'm here! Bring the goats!
brs_pt1_05_02 = "分かった、俺はここだ。ヤギを捕まえてこい!",--All right, I'm here. Now get the goats in!
brs_pt1_05_03 = "見えたぞ! ヤギを連れてこい!",--On the scene! Bring me the goats!
cpg_pt1_01_01 = "ヤギをおろせ!",--Put the goats down!
cpg_pt1_01_02 = "ヤギを地面に置いて手を上に上げろ。",--Place the goat on the floor and your hands in the air.
cpg_pt1_01_03 = "ヤギから離れて立て、この野郎!",--Step away from the goat, asshole!
cpg_pt1_01_04 = "ヤギを降ろさなければ撃つ。",--Lower the goat, or we shoot.
cpg_pt1_01_05 = "そのヤギは重要証言者だ。今すぐ降ろしなさい!",--That goat is an important witness. Drop it. Now!
cpg_pt1_01_06 = "ヤギの誘拐は連邦法違反だ。",--Abducting goats is a federal offence.
cpg_pt1_01_07 = "無法者達、ヤギを捨てなさい!",--Drop the goat, lawbreaker!
cpg_pt1_01_08 = "そのヤギはもうアメリカ政府の物だぞ、くそ野郎!",--That goat belongs to Uncle Sam now, asshole!
cpg_pt1_01_09 = "そのくそヤギから離れろ、ピエロ共!",--Leave the damn goats alone, clowns!
cpg_pt1_01_10 = "ヤギを連れて行くなら逃がさないぞ、馬鹿野郎!",--You're not leaving here with the goats, assholes!
vld_pt1_cbf_01 = "Hectorがくたばったことでヤクの市場に穴ができちまった。自然は足らざるを補う。クソッタレだ。そこら中から間抜け共がやってくる。ホンジュラス人の連中が手を広げようとしている。こいつらが根を張る前に、潰しちまおう。密輸団の連中をバラバラにして、ブツは頂きだ。単純だろ? ",--Hector's death left a vacuum in the powder trade. Nature abhors a vacuum. Fucking abhors it! There's muck-fuckers crawling in from everywhere. Bunch of Hondurans are trying to spread. Let's hit them before they can take root. Break up their smuggling ring. Steal their product. What can go wrong?
vld_pt1_cnc_01 = "ある密輸を叩き潰してくれ。Cokeを奪うだけが、ちょいとした問題がある...",--I need you to break up a smuggling operation. Get the coke. There's just one small complication....
vld_pt1_cnc_02 = "マヌケどもがDCでのヤク取引に手を出し始めた。奴らのブツを奪え。叩き潰せ。ただ一つ言うことがある...",--Some fucks are trying to develop a coke operation in DC. Get their product. Break it up. Just one small detail...
vld_pt1_cnc_03 = "あるホンジュラスのカルテルがDCに乗り出そうとしてやがる。ラバ(運び屋)を使ってるが、それだけじゃない。今にわかる...",--A Honduran cartel are trying to set up in DC. Using mules. Except not mules. You'll see....
vld_pt1_intro_01 = "よし、そろそろ...本当の事を話す。Cokeが入ってるのは...ヤギだ。そう、ヤギだ。しかも逃げちまった。ハハ、やんちゃなヤギだよな、ええ?!探し出せ!",--Okay, time for...honesty. The coke is packed in...goats. Yes, goats. And they've escaped. Haha, tricky goats, huh?! Find them!
vld_pt1_intro_02 = "あー、友よ。その「ラバ」はその...実はヤギだ。$NL;そして、えー、逃げやがった。こいつらを探せ。",--Ah, my friends. So, the "mules", you see...well, they're actually goats. And they've..errr, escaped. Find them for me.
vld_pt1_intro_03 = "あー、聞けよ。コカインをヤギに隠されたんだ。そう、ヤギだ。$NL; そしてそいつらは逃げた。全部見つけてくれ。",--Ahhh, listen. The coke is being smuggled in goats. Yes, goats. G. O. T's. And they've escaped. Find them all.
vld_pt1_01_01 = "よく見ろ、そして特に音に注意しろ。",--Keep your eyes open, yes, but especially your ears.
vld_pt1_01_02 = "耳を澄ませ。ヤギは...鳴いてるはずだ。",--Listen out for the goats. They'll be making...goat noises.
vld_pt1_01_03 = "耳を澄まして聞け。聞こえるのは..",--Keep listening. Listen for...
vld_pt1_02_01 = "ヤギの声だ...鳴き喚いてるぞ!まあ、5ポンドのCokeをケツに突っ込まれてりゃな。",--Just....goat "noises"! Screaming. Well, wouldn't you with 5lbs of coke up your ass?
vld_pt1_02_02 = "俺はデイヴィッド・アッテンボローじゃねえぞ!クロアチア人でもな。だが...ヤギの鳴き声だ!",--I ain't Sir David Attenborough! Or Igor the Croat. Just....goat noises!
vld_pt1_02_03 = "ケツにCokeの詰まった家畜の鳴き声っぽいものなら何でもいい。",--Whatever noise you expect from a farm animal with a bag of coke buried in it's shitpipe.
vld_pt1_03_01 = "俺の運転手のBorisが来るだろうから、お前らは彼に乗せてもらえ。",--Boris, my driver, will come and pick you guys up.
vld_pt1_03_02 = "Borisが向かっている途中だ。間違ってないだろ、Boris?",--Boris is on his way. Isn't that right, Boris?
vld_pt1_03_03 = "お前らの方に一人送る。Boris?",--I have a man on the way for you. Boris?
vld_pt1_04_01 = "ヤギがアパートの上の方に居るようだ。捕まえに行け!",--Looks like one of the goats is up in that apartment. Get up there!
vld_pt1_04_02 = "アパートの上にヤギがいる。追いかけろ! 中を探せ。",--A goat got into an apartment up there. Get after it! Look for a way in.
vld_pt1_04_03 = "誰かヤギを連れていこうとした奴がいるな。特別なペットが欲しかったんだろ、ええ?セルビア人とその\"特別な\"ペットみたいにな。\"トクベツ\"だよ。アパートに入って救出してこい。",--Someone tried to take a goat. Make special pet, yeah? Like Igor the Serb and his "special" pets. "Special". Get into that apartment and rescue it.
vld_pt1_05_01 = "そうだ!入りやがれ、この毛玉野郎!",--Yes! Get in there, you hairy little bastard!
vld_pt1_05_02 = "そこに居やがれ、クソ野郎!",--And stay there, you little shit!
vld_pt1_05_03 = "動くんじゃないぞ。クソ頭突きヤギめ...",--And don't fucking move. Fucking goat prick...
vld_pt1_05_04 = "そこに居ろ...草を食ってて角が生えてる変な目をしたどうしようもないクソッタレめ!",--And stay...you grass-chewin', horn-growin', freaky-eyed MOTHERFUCKER!
vld_pt1_05_05 = "動いたらお前を愛してる奴と二人きりにさせるぞ、この野郎。",--You move and it is Igor time for you, asshole.
vld_pt1_05_06 = "別の1匹だ。良いぞ!",--Another one. Good!
vld_pt1_05_07 = "ヤギを連れてこい!",--Keep bringing goats!
vld_pt1_05_08 = "ヤギを捕まえ続けろ!",--Keep on with the goat catching thing!
vld_pt1_05_09 = "マテ!ツケ!",--Stay! Heel!
vld_pt1_05_10 = "そこに居ろ、さもなくばハラールの肉にするぞ。",--Stay there, or it's the halal butcher for you.
vld_pt1_05_11 = "もう逃げるんじゃないぞ、小さなヤギよ。",--Don't run away again, little goat.
vld_pt1_05_12 = "別のヤギを確保。",--Another goat secured.
vld_pt1_05_13 = "もう逃げようとか考えるなよ、シチューの具にするぞ!",--Don't think about running again, or it's the stewpot for you!
vld_pt1_05_14 = "動くなよ。さもなくば弱火でじっくりと丸焼きにするぞ。",--Don't move. Or I'll slow-fucking-roast you.
vld_pt1_05_15 = "動いたら\"クソッ\"て後悔するより前に獣姦好きのベッドに放り込んでやるぞ。",--You move, and you'll be in Igors bed before you can say "oh shit".
vld_pt1_05_16 = "かけっこは終わりだ、ヤギくん。",--No more runny-run for you, goat-boy.
vld_pt1_05_17 = "入りやがれ、この醜いチビ助め!",--Get in there, ya ugly little fuck!
vld_pt1_05_18 = "もう冒険はできないぞ、小さな友よ。",--No more adventures for you, little friend.
vld_pt1_05_19 = "お前の冒険は終わった、クソッタレなヤギよ。",--Your adventure is over, you goat-fuck.
vld_pt1_05_20 = "そうだ! 良いぞ! ヤギだ!!",--Yes! Good! Goats!!
vld_pt1_06_01 = "まさに掘り出しもんてやつだ、なあ?",--A real bargain, yes?
vld_pt1_06_02 = "あのイタズラ好きを探せ!",--Found the tricksy little shit!
vld_pt1_06_03 = "見つけたぞ、このくそちびめ!",--There you are, you little fucker!
vld_pt1_07_01 = "良いぞ、良いぞ! 今来たBorisが街はずれの農場に案内する。$NL;彼はCokeを...取り出せる。",--Nice. Good! Now, Boris is going to lead you to a farm outside the city. There he can...extract the coke.
vld_pt1_07_02 = "郊外に俺の小さく素敵な農場がある。Borisがそこへ案内する。彼はCokeの包みを取り出せる。",--I have a pleasant little farm outside the city. Boris will lead you there. He can remove those packets of coke.
vld_pt1_07_03 = "いい仕事だ、友よ。だがまだ半分だ。Borisに付いて行け。街はずれの農場まで案内する、そして彼は...Cokeを取り出せる。彼を守れ。",--Nice job, friends, but you're only halfway there. Follow Boris. He'll lead you to a farm outside the city, where he can..you know...extract the coke. Protect him.
pln_pt1_brf_01 = "このHondurian Cartelは、Downtownを通るトラックでブツを運ぼうとしている。Vladはそいつを襲撃する計画を立てた。俺達は後始末係だ。つまり、襲撃後に突入して、ブツがきっちり運び出されるようにする。地上部隊ってわけだな。",--This Honduran cartel has a truck moving its product through Downtown. Vlad has arranged to have it hit. We're on clean-up. We go in afterwards, make sure the product gets out. Boots on the ground, you know?
pln_pt1_01_01 = "オーケー、聞いたな。ブツはヤギの腹の中にあって、そのヤギが街中に行っちまった。こいつらを集めろ。",--Okay. Well, you heard the man. The product is IN the goats, and the goats are all over downtown. Round 'em up.
pln_pt1_01_02 = "あー、Vladが言ってたんだ...ヤギの腹の中にヤクがあって、そのヤギは...街中に行っちまった。トラックに載せろ。",--Well, as Vlad said...the coke is in the goats, and the goats are...well, all over downtown. Track 'em down.
pln_pt1_01_03 = "Vlad、お前はイカレてるよ...OK、野郎ども。これも仕事だ。あるときは核弾頭、ある時はヤギだ。探せ。",--Vlad, you crazy...okay, guys. That's the deal. Sometimes it's nukes, sometimes it's goats. Get looking.
pln_pt1_02_01 = "ヤギの声は聞こえるか?",--Well, what does a goat sound like?
pln_pt1_02_02 = "ヤギってどう鳴くんだ?",--What noise does a goat make?
pln_pt1_02_03 = "どんな音だ?",--What sort of noise?
pln_pt1_03_01 = "これで全部だろう!山を越えたな。車に乗って脱出だ。",--That should be all of them! Time to ride out. Get in the wheels and get out of there.
pln_pt1_03_02 = "こいつで全部だ。野郎共、車をトラックに入れろ。",--That's all the goats secured. Now get in your car and high tail it out of there.
pln_pt1_03_03 = "これで全部だ。車に乗って走り出せ!",--That's all of them. Get in the car and scoot!
pln_pt1_04_01 = "退散の時間だ。車に乗れ!",--Gang, it's time to bug. Get in the car!
pln_pt1_04_02 = "みんな、ヤギは捕まえたな、車を出せ!",--Crew, you got the goats, now hit the gas!
pln_pt1_04_03 = "野郎ども、仕事は終わった。移動の時間だ! 車に乗れ!",--Job's done here, guys. Time to roll! Into the car!
pln_pt1_05_01 = "ヤギを運ぶなら車を使えば早く済むぞ。",--You'll close this out quicker if you use the car to move the goats.
pln_pt1_05_02 = "ヤギを車に運べ。でもシートに糞はさせないようにな。",--Haul the goats in the car. Just don't let 'em crap on the upholstery.
pln_pt1_05_03 = "手早くヤギを集めに戻れ。車を使え!",--Gotta get them goats back quickly. Use the car!
pln_pt1_06_01 = "ギャング共、一匹のヤギがアパートの中に居るのを忘れるな。",--Gang, don't forget one of those goats is up in the apartment.
pln_pt1_06_02 = "アパートの中のヤギを忘れるな。",--Don't forget the goat in that apartment block.
pln_pt1_06_03 = "アパートの中に取り残されたヤギがいる。",--There's still a goat in the apartment building there.
pln_pt1_07_01 = "このアパートにはスプリンクラーが付いているから、どこかにあるバルブを操作しろ。",--The apartment has a sprinkler system, so there's got to be a valve somewhere.
pln_pt1_07_02 = "この手のアパートは全部スプリンクラーが付いている。バルブを探せ。",--All these apartments have sprinkler systems. Just look for the valve.
pln_pt1_07_03 = "こういう場所にはスプリンクラー設置が義務だ。バルブを探せ!",--These places are required to have sprinkler systems. Find the valve!
pln_pt1_08_01 = "そのバルブがスプリンクラーを制御してる。起動しろ!",--There's valves that control the sprinklers, turn them on!
pln_pt1_08_02 = "バルブを見つけろ。スプリンクラーを動かせ!",--Look for the valves. Get the sprinklers going!
pln_pt1_08_03 = "バルブを探せ。俺たちはスプリンクラーを作動させなきゃならん。",--Find those valves. We need the sprinklers working.
pln_pt1_09_01 = "よくやった、これらのスプリンクラーが火を消してくれるだろうよ。",--Great, those sprinklers will put out the fire.
pln_pt1_09_02 = "雨よ降れ!",--Let it rain!
pln_pt1_09_03 = "よくやった、作動してるぞ!",--Great. It's working!
pln_pt1_10_01 = "よくやった! 鎮火されるぞ。",--Outstanding! Fire's dying down.
pln_pt1_10_02 = "鎮火するぞ。世間には俺たちがやってることは意味不明だろうな!",--Fire's out. And people think all we do is cause chaos!
pln_pt1_10_03 = "これで火事は収まる。お前らは民衆のヒーローだ!",--That's the fire dealt with. You guys are civil heroes!
pln_pt1_11_01 = "どうやって登ったんだ? まあいい...ファンを止める配電盤を探せ。",--How did the goat get up there? Whatever...look for the circuit box to stop the fan.
pln_pt1_11_02 = "ヤギがファンにしがみついてる? おかしな一日だ。ファンを止める配電盤を探せ。",--A goat in a fan? This day gets weirder. Find the circuit box to halt the fan.
pln_pt1_11_03 = "ヤギがああなっちまったのはなんか理由があると思うが、とりあえずファンを止めよう。配電盤を探せ。",--Sure there's gotta be a good reason that goat is up in the fan. Just find the circuit box. Stop the fan.
pln_pt1_12_01 = "配電盤をハッキングすればファンが止まる。",--Hacking the circuit box will stop the fan.
pln_pt1_12_02 = "配電盤は外にあるようだ。ハッキングすればファンが止まるだろう。",--Circuit box is likely outside. Hacking it will stop the fan.
pln_pt1_12_03 = "野郎ども、配電盤を探せ。ファンを止めるにはそれを弄らなきゃならない。",--Find the circuit box, crew. You need to hack it to halt the fan.
pln_pt1_13_01 = "ヤギが通電部にいる。電源を遮断しろ。",--That goat is carrying a live charge. Disable the power.
pln_pt1_13_02 = "ヤギは優れた電気工事士らしい。電源を切れ。",--Goats are great conductors of electricity. Turn off the power.
pln_pt1_13_03 = "ヤギが通電部に居る! 電源を遮断しろ!",--That goat has live current running through it! Disable the power!
pln_pt1_14_01 = "そのヤギには気をつけろ! 野郎共、まずは電源を切るんだ!",--Beware the goat! Guys, you need to disable the power first!
pln_pt1_14_02 = "そのヤギはヤバイ! まず電気を切れ!",--The goat is deadly! Kill the electricity first!
pln_pt1_14_03 = "ヤギが感電してやがる! 電源を落とせ!",--The goat is electrictrified! Turn off the power!
pln_pt1_15_01 = "いや、違うやつだ。別のを試せ。",--Nope, wrong one. Try another.
pln_pt1_15_02 = "これじゃない。違うやつを試せ。",--That didn't do it. Try a different one.
pln_pt1_15_03 = "うーむ...違う。これは作動していない。別のやつを試せ。",--Uhhh...no, that didn't work. Try another one.
pln_pt1_16_01 = "電源が落ちた。あのヤギを確保しろ!",--Power's down! Get that goat!
pln_pt1_16_02 = "素晴らしい。安全にヤギを捕まえられる。",--Great. You can safely grab the goat now!
pln_pt1_16_03 = "よしいいぞ、すぐにヤギを捕獲しろ!",--All right, nice. Now fetch the goat!
pln_pt1_17_01 = "それにしてもどうやったんだ...?",--How did it even...?
pln_pt1_17_02 = "見当もつかん...",--I can't work out how it...
pln_pt1_17_03 = "あんなとこで何やってたんだ...?",--What was it doing up...?
pln_pt1_17_04 = "一体どうやったんだろな...?",--Okay, but how did it....?
pln_pt1_17_05 = "どうやったのかわからねえ。",--I still can't figure out how.
pln_pt1_17_06 = "どう登ったのか謎だな。",--How it got up there is a mystery.
pln_pt1_18_01 = "別のがいるな!足場に行って捕まえろ!気をつけろよ!漏電してるようだ!電源を落とせ!",--There's another one! Caught in the scaffolding! Watch out! Looks like it's electrocuted! Disable the power!
pln_pt1_18_02 = "ギャング共、見えるか?ヤギがあの足場にいるぞ!だが、おっと気をつけろ!あのハシゴは電気が流れてるぞ。電源を落とせ!",--Gang, you see it? Another goat in the scaffolds! But - woah, be careful! Looks like that ladder is electrocuted!
pln_pt1_18_03 = "見ろ、ハシゴの上だ!ヤギがいるな。だが、ちょっと待て!あのハシゴは通電してるようだ。電源を落とせ!",--Look, up in the scaffold! Another goat. But, hold up! It looks like that ladder is electrocuted. Disable power!
pln_pt1_19_01 = "工事の足場にいるヤギを忘れるなよ。",--Don't forget the goat in the scaffold.
pln_pt1_19_02 = "工事の足場にヤギがいるぞ。",--There's still a goat in the scaffold.
pln_pt1_19_03 = "忘れるなよ - 足場でヤギが立ち往生してる。",--Remember - there's a goat stuck in the scaffolds.
pln_pt1_20_01 = "どうやらあのヤギは電源にかじりついたようだな。ハシゴに電気が流れてる。電源を落とせ!",--Looks like the goat managed to nibble through the power. Ladder's electrocuted. Disable the power!
pln_pt1_20_02 = "あのヤギはトラブルメーカーだな。どうやったのかしらんが電気が通ってる。配電盤で切ってこい。",--That goat's a trouble maker. He somehow turned on the power. Disable it at the power box.
pln_pt1_20_03 = "あのヤギがハシゴに電気を流したのか。配電盤を探して切るんだ。",--The goat managed to electrify the ladder. Look for the power box to turn it off.
pln_pt1_21_01 = "ハシゴに触るな! 配電盤で遮断しろ!",--Don't touch the ladder! Disable the powerboxes!
pln_pt1_21_02 = "ハシゴが通電してる、配電盤で遮断しろ!",--Ladder's electrified. Disable it at the power box!
pln_pt1_21_03 = "配電盤をどうにかしなきゃ、ハシゴが使えんぞ!",--You need to deal with the power box to use the ladder!
pln_pt1_22_01 = "店の中を調べろ。俺たちのヤギが入り込んだかもしれん。ドリルを使え!",--Check inside that store. Likely one of our goats wandered in. Drill it open!
pln_pt1_22_02 = "ひょっとするとヤギが店に入り込んでるかもな。ドリルでドアを開けろ!",--I'm guessing a goat managed to get into the store. Drill the door!
pln_pt1_22_03 = "あの店を探してみた方が良さそうだ。ドアをドリルで開けろ、ギャング共!",--That store looks like a good spot to search. Drill the door, gang!
pln_pt1_23_01 = "あの店にヤギが居るのは間違いない。ドアにドリルを使え!",--Pretty sure there will be a goat inside the store. Get a drill on the door!
pln_pt1_23_02 = "ヤギはお買い物好きだな!ドリルで店を開けろ!",--Goats love shopping! Drill your way into the store.
pln_pt1_23_03 = "あの店を忘れるなよ。ドアをドリルで開けろ。ヤギが中にいるって賭けてもいいぜ。",--Don't forget the store. Drill the door. I bet my cut there's a goat inside.
pln_pt1_24_01 = "仕事のためだ開けろ!ヤギ探しのお仕事だ!",--Open for business! The business of finding goats!
pln_pt1_24_02 = "よし、店が開いた! ヤギを探せ!",--Store is open! Find that goat!
pln_pt1_24_03 = "入ったな、じゃあヤギを追え!",--We're in. Now get after that goat!
pln_pt1_25_01 = "あのヤギはここを登って動けなくなったんだな。降ろしてやろう。SAWで街灯を倒せ!",--That goat climbed up there. Got stuck. We need him down. Saw the streetlight!
pln_pt1_25_02 = "優しく呼びかけてヤギを降ろそうなんて思うなよ。SAWで街灯を切り倒せ!",--You're not going to tempt that goat down with nice words and treats. Saw the streetlight!
pln_pt1_25_03 = "SAWを街灯に使え、それしかあのヤギを降ろす方法はない。",--Get a saw on that streetlight. It's the only way to bring the goat down.
pln_pt1_26_01 = "ヤギが街灯にぶら下がってやがる! SAWで切り倒してやれ。",--Guys, there's a goat stuck in the streetlight! Saw it down.
pln_pt1_26_02 = "街灯にぶら下がってるヤギのことも忘れるなよ、SAWで引きずり下ろしてやるんだ。",--Don't forget the goat in the streetlight. Saw it to bring him down.
pln_pt1_26_03 = "いいか、SAWを街灯に使ってヤギを降ろしてやるんだ。",--Remember, you need to get a saw on the streetlight to bring down the goat.
pln_pt1_27_01 = "街灯が倒れたぞ、ヤギを捕まえろ!",--Streetlight is down. Grab the goat!
pln_pt1_27_02 = "街灯を切断し終えたな、ヤギを捕まえろ!",--That's the streetlight done. Now grab that goat!
pln_pt1_27_03 = "よし、これで街灯は終わりだ。ヤギを捕らえろ!",--All right! Streetlight is history. Grab the goat!
pln_pt1_28_01 = "サツどもがヤギを連れて行くぞ!取り戻せ!",--The cops are taking our goats! Get them back!
pln_pt1_28_02 = "サツがヤギを現場の外に連れ出そうとしてるぞ。",--Cop is trying to move a goat out of the AO.
pln_pt1_28_03 = "サツがヤギを救助してやがる! こんな事に税金を使ってるのか!?",--Cops are rescuing the goats! Is this what tax money pays for!?
brs_pt2_intro_01 = "ヤギを納屋に入れるのを手伝ってくれ。",--Help me get the goats into the barn.
brs_pt2_intro_02 = "ここへヤギを入れてくれないか。",--Can you guys help me get the goats in here.
brs_pt2_intro_03 = "ここにヤギを入れよう。",--Let's get the goats in here.
brs_pt2_01_01 = "オーケー、必要なものは全部揃ってるな? Crowbar、ジップタイ、潤滑油。準備よし!マジで汚いから手袋をしなきゃな。",--Okay. Do I have everything? Crowbar, zipties, lube. All ready! Gloves on for some really dirty work.
brs_pt2_01_02 = "さて、汚仕事のはじまりだ。昔はMariupolの税関で働いてたんだ。 手袋を付けてと。",--Now, time for the real dirty work. I used to work as a customs officer in Mariupol. Snap the gloves on.
brs_pt2_01_03 = "ここからは賑やかになるぞ。うるさくて汚く、そして臭い。もう待ちきれんよ。早くやろう、な?",--This next part is noisy. Noisy, and dirty and smelly. I can't wait. Let's do this, huh?
brs_pt2_02_01 = "ホンジュラス共だ! つけてやがったのか!クソ!",--It's the Hondurans! They fucking followed us! Shit!
brs_pt2_02_02 = "クソッタレのホンジュラスに見つかった! 連中はどうやって俺たちを追ってきた?!",--The fucking Hondurans found us! How did they follow us?!
brs_pt2_02_03 = "クソ! ホンジュラス共だ! すぐそこに居る! 俺たちを殺しに来たんだ!",--Fuck! The Hondurans! They're here! They're going to kill us!
brs_pt2_03_01 = "クソッタレ、外で何が起こってるんだ。クソ、ここは暑いな。",--Holy shit, what's going on outside? Oh, it's hot in here.
brs_pt2_03_02 = "おい、もう出ても安全か? ここは年寄りのケツみたいな臭いがする。",--Hey, is it safe out there yet? It's smells like old ass in here.
brs_pt2_03_03 = "お前ら、まだ出ないほうがいいのか? ゴキブリを飲んじまったぞ。",--Guys, safe to come out yet? I swallowed a cockroach.
brs_pt2_03_04 = "もう出てもいいか? あのパンパン鳴ってるのは爆竹か?",--Is it safe to come out yet? Are those loud bangs firecrackers?
brs_pt2_03_05 = "もう出ていいか? まだ奴らいるのか?",--Can I come out yet? Are they gone?
brs_pt2_03_06 = "ヤギは大丈夫か? おお神よ、誰かヤギの事を想ってやってくれ!",--Are the goats safe? Please, God, someone think of the goats!
brs_pt2_03_07 = "ここに食べかけのチョコバーがあるぞ。う～～～ん、木の実の香りがする。あっ...チョコバーじゃなかった。",--There's a half-eaten candy bar here. Mmmmm nutty. Oh....wasn't a candy bar.
brs_pt2_03_08 = "もう奴らいっちまったか?出てもいいよな?",--Are they gone yet? Is it safe to come out?
brs_pt2_03_09 = "もう作業に戻れるか?携帯のバッテリーが5%まで減っちまった。",--Can we get back to work yet? I'm down to 5% on my cell.
brs_pt2_03_10 = "この中何か生き物がいるぞ。",--There's something else alive in here.
brs_pt2_03_11 = "ブッシュ大統領の頃からこのゴミ箱が空になったことはないんだろうな。パパ・ブッシュの方だ!",--I don't think this trash can has been emptied since Bush was in power. Bush senior!
brs_pt2_03_12 = "今頃Shevchenko夫人は可愛い息子に会いに棺桶に入ってるだろうな。",--Mrs Shevchenko would roll in her grave to see her little boy now.
vld_pt2_01_01 = "幸いにも、君たちには知的犯罪者Vladがついている。いい考えがある。",--Fortunately, you have the criminal mind of Vlad on your side. I have an idea.
vld_pt2_01_02 = "君たちのVladおじさんが何の手助けもせず放っとくと思ったか?恥を知れ!",--You think your Uncle Vlad would leave you there and not have support? Shame on you!
vld_pt2_01_03 = "友よ、落ち着け。Vladには考えがある。お前らはVladのアイデアが好きだ、そうだろう?",--Stay cool, my friends. Vlad has an idea. You like Vlad's ideas, yeah?
vld_pt2_02_01 = "俺の義兄弟...あの飲んだくれの老いぼれがスカイフックケージを持ってくる。",--My brother-in-law - you remember that old soak - will be coming in with a skyhook cage.
vld_pt2_02_02 = "俺の義理の兄弟を送った。スカイフックケージを届けてくれるぞ。事故らなければ。",--I'm sending in my brother-in-law. He'll drop a skyhook cage. If he can avoid crashing.
vld_pt2_02_03 = "俺の義理の兄弟が向かってる。スカイフックケージを落としてくれる。",--My brother-in-law is on his way. He will drop a skyhook cage for you.
vld_pt2_03_01 = "待て、ヤギを全部載せてないぞ。俺をナメてるのか? 俺は全部のヤギが欲しいんだ。",--Wait, you didn't get ALL of the goats. Is my asshole your plaything? I want ALL the goats.
vld_pt2_03_02 = "おい、ヤギが何頭かいないぞ。Vladは悲しい。なあ、うれしいVladが見たいだろ。",--Hey, we're missing some of the goats. This makes Vlad sad. Trust me, you want a happy Vlad.
vld_pt2_03_03 = "待て、何頭かヤギがいなくなってるぞ。何でいなくなってんだよ!?",--Wait, some of the goats are missing. Why are some of the goats missing?!
vld_pt2_04_01 = "それでいい!ヤギはCokeをもたらす!ガシャガシャチーン、大儲けだ、友よ!さあて、カレーが食べたい奴はいるか?",--That's it! We got the goats, we got the coke! Ka-ching-fucking-ching, my friends! Now, who wants to come over for a curry?
vld_pt2_04_02 = "よくやってくれた、親愛なる友よ。マジで愛してるぜ。このCokeほどじゃないが、大好きだ!",--Well done, dear friends. I fucking love you all. Not as much as I love all of this coke, but still quite a lot!
vld_pt2_04_03 = "なんて素晴らしい年始めだろう。山ほどのCokeと一緒にドライブだ!おめでとう、親愛なる友よ。",--What a great way to start the year. With a mountain of fucking coke to move! Congratulations, dear friends.
pln_pt2_brf_01 = "オーケー、最悪の状況は乗り越えたな。 Vladの運び屋が郊外の農場にヤギを運んで、包みを取り出す準備が出来た。側で待て。周辺を監視してろ。簡単な仕事だ、そうだろう?",--Okay, I think the worst is behind us. Vlad's driver got the goats to a farm outside the city, ready to perform the extraction of the packages. Stick around. Watch the perimeter. Easy work, right?
pln_pt2_01_01 = "奴らを倒せ!",--Drop them, crew!
pln_pt2_01_02 = "近づけさせるな!",--Don't let them close, gang!
pln_pt2_01_03 = "やっちまえ!",--Take them out!
pln_pt2_02_01 = "銃声で警官がやってくるぞ。ヤギに近寄らせるなよ。",--That gunfire will bring the cops. We can't let them get the goats.
pln_pt2_02_02 = "今のドンパチできっと警察が来る。ヤギから遠ざけなきゃな。",--The shooting's bound to draw the cops. We need to get the goats away.
pln_pt2_02_03 = "今ので必ずFBIが来る。ヤギを運び出す手を考えないとな。",--That'll surely bring the feds. Gotta think of a way to get the goats out of here.
pln_pt2_03_01 = "おお、聞き慣れた声だ。墜落だけはしないよう祈るぜ。",--Oh, that voice is familiar. Just hope he doesn't crash.
pln_pt2_03_02 = "あいつが丘に激突しないことを祈るぜ。引き続き警官どもを追い払え。",--Hope he doesn't hit a hill. Keep the cops at bay.
pln_pt2_03_03 = "今回は墜落しないよう祈ろう。サツ共を寄せ付けるな。",--Let's hope he stays in the air this time. Hold the cops off.
pln_pt2_04_01 = "警察が来るぞ!気合をいれろ!",--Cops are here! Brace yourselves!
pln_pt2_04_02 = "警察が来たな。支度しろ、お前ら!",--Here's the cops. Get ready, crew!
pln_pt2_04_03 = "サツどもだ!食い止めろ!",--It's the cops! Hold the line!
pln_pt2_05_01 = "納屋の周りに板があるはずだ。窓を塞ぐのに使え。",--There's gotta be boards around that barn. Use 'em to block the windows.
pln_pt2_05_02 = "窓を塞げるものが納屋にはあるはずだ。",--I'm sure you'll find something in that barn to close off the windows.
pln_pt2_05_03 = "その納屋には窓に打ち付けられるものが置いてあるに違いない。",--That barn must have something lying around you can nail across the windows.
pln_pt2_06_01 = "やることは分かってるな。外に出て、ケージのパーツを拾って組み立てるんだ。",--You know what to do guys. Go out there, grab the cage parts and assemble it.
pln_pt2_06_02 = "よしお前ら、外に行ってケージを組み立ててこい!",--Okay gang - now get out there and assemble the cage!
pln_pt2_06_03 = "ぐずぐずするなよ。ケージを組み立てるんだ!",--Don't dawdle, crew. Assemble that cage!
pln_pt2_07_01 = "ここは激しすぎるな。ケージはサイロで組ませる。",--There's way too much heat here. I'll have my guys assemble the cage at the silo.
pln_pt2_07_02 = "銃撃が激しすぎる。サイロで組むんだ!",--Too much fire here. We'll assemble at the silo!
pln_pt2_07_03 = "警官に包囲されたな。サイロで組み立てよう。",--Cops have this locked down. We're going to assemble at the silo.
pln_pt2_08_01 = "ここじゃキツい。橋で組み立てさせる。",--It's too damned heavy here. The guys will set up at the bridge.
pln_pt2_08_02 = "うお、なんて数だ!橋で組み立てさせる。",--Oh, there's a lot of firepower here! The guys will assemble the cage at the bridge.
pln_pt2_08_03 = "戦闘が激しすぎる。橋で組み立てさせる。",--Too much action here. I'll have the guys build the cage at the bridge.
pln_pt2_09_01 = "ケージを組むのは道路の上が最適だろう。",--Reckon the best place for the guys to build the cage is on the road.
pln_pt2_09_02 = "オーケー、ケージは道路で組ませる。",--Okay, I'll have the guys put the cage together on the road.
pln_pt2_09_03 = "ここは騒がしすぎる。そこの道路がケージを組ませるのに一番よさそうだ。",--Too much going on here. The road looks best for the guys to assemble the cage.
pln_pt2_10_01 = "それでいい!次はヤギを放り込め!",--That's it! Now put all the goats in it!
pln_pt2_10_02 = "いいぞ!次はヤギを掴んで投げ入れろ!",--Good! Now grab the goats and throw them in!
pln_pt2_10_03 = "よくやったな。次はヤギを入れるんだ。",--Nice job, gang. Now start getting the goats in.
pln_pt2_11_01 = "オーケー。準備できたらバルーンを上げてパイロットにケージを回収させよう。",--Okay. When you're ready, raise the balloon and the pilot will collect the cage.
pln_pt2_11_02 = "準備が済んだら、バルーンを上げてパイロットに回収にこさせよう。",--When you're ready, raise the balloon and the pilot will swing by and collect.
pln_pt2_11_03 = "後はバルーンを上げてパイロットに任せよう。",--Now just raise the balloon and let the pilot do the rest.
pln_pt2_12_01 = "バルーンが出たぞ。おい、アンタにも見えてるか?",--There's the balloon. Hey, you see it, guy?
pln_pt2_12_02 = "バルーンが上がった。あれが見えるか?",--Balloon is up. Are you seeing it?
pln_pt2_12_03 = "設置完了。バルーンが見えるか?",--We're ready. You seeing the balloon?
pln_pt2_13_01 = "聞こえたか、お前ら。ヤギを危険にさらすなよ。",--You heard him, gang. Just keep the heat off the goats.
pln_pt2_13_02 = "皆、了解したな?パイロットが向かってる。ヤギを守れ。",--Crew, you copy that? Pilot is inbound. Protect the goats.
pln_pt2_13_03 = "飛行機が撃ち合いの中飛んでくるぞ。サツどもにヤギを奪われるなよ。",--Pilot is coming in hot, guys. don't let the cops grab any goats.
pln_pt2_14_01 = "分かってるよな。外に出るんだ。ケージを組み立てろ!",--You know what to do. Get out there. Assemble the cage!
pln_pt2_14_02 = "オーケー。繰り返しだ。外に出て、ケージを組むんだ。",--Okay crew. Same thing. Get out there, and get the cage built.
pln_pt2_14_03 = "前回と一緒だ。ケージの準備だ。",--As before, gang. Get that cage prepared.
pln_pt2_15_01 = "上出来だ!それじゃズラかるぞ!トラックから車を出せ!",--Excellent! Now get outta there! Grab your car from the truck!
pln_pt2_15_02 = "素晴らしい!さあ脱出だ。全員車に乗り込め!",--Fantastic! Time to leave. Grab the car, crew!
pln_pt2_15_03 = "こいつはいい!ヤギとおさらばだぜ!俺たちも出発するぞ!",--Outstanding! That's all the goats! Now time to hit the road, gang!
pln_pt2_16_01 = "頼むぜお前ら。ここまできてヘマこくなよ。車に乗って、出発だ!",--Come on, crew. Don't fuck up now. Get the car, and hit the road!
pln_pt2_16_02 = "お前ら!もうここに用はない。車に乗って急いで発進しろ!",--Guys! We're done here. Grab your wheels and burn rubber!
pln_pt2_16_03 = "何でまだそこにいるんだ?急げよ、車に乗り込んで全速前進!",--Why you still there? Come on, into the car and floor it!
pln_pt2_17_01 = "おっと、全員乗り込むまで待てよ!",--Woah, wait til everyone is in the car!
pln_pt2_17_02 = "全員車に乗れ!今すぐにだ!",--Everyone! In the car! Now!
pln_pt2_17_03 = "待て待て、全員乗り込むまで行くな。",--Hold it, hold it - wait til everyone's in the car.
pln_pt2_18_01 = "おい、どこへ行くんだ?車に戻れ!",--Hey, where you going? Back in the car!
pln_pt2_18_02 = "車に戻れ!乗るんだ!",--Back in the car! Time to ride!
pln_pt2_18_03 = "車に乗ってろよ、まったく!",--Stay in the car, dammit!
pln_pt2_19_01 = "脱出口は用意してある。橋がかかった道の向こう側にTwitchがトラックで来ている。あとは車ごと乗り込むだけでゴールだ!",--You're getaway is all ready. There's a bridge just down the road, and Twitch is on the other side, with a truck. Just drive right up into the truck and we are done!
pln_pt2_19_02 = "よし、聞いてくれ。Twitchがこの先の橋を渡った向こうで待ってる。トラックでな。そこへ車ごとまっすぐ乗り込めば、この仕事はおしまいだ。",--Okay, listen. Twitch is waiting for you up ahead, just on the other side of the bridge. He's got a truck. Just drive straight up on into it, and this caper is closed.
pln_pt2_19_03 = "よし、聞いてくれ。これが脱出路だ。この先の橋を渡ると、トンネルにトラックが見えてくる。Twitchだ。あとはトラックの中に車を停めれば、めでたしめでたしだ。",--All right, listen up. Here's the getaway. Get past the bridge up ahead, and you'll see a truck in a tunnel. That's Twitch. Just park straight up into the truck, and we can close the book on this one.
pln_pt2_20_01 = "ずる賢い警官どもが橋を外しやがった。制御室へ行って架けなおせ。",--The crafty cops have closed off the bridge. Go to the control room to turn it back.
pln_pt2_20_02 = "くそ、サツどもに橋を外されたぞ!そこの制御室に入って、もとに戻せ。なんとしても向こう側へ渡るんだ!",--Damn, the cops turned the bridge! Get into the control room there, and turn it back. You need to be on the other side!
pln_pt2_20_03 = "ああっ!警察が橋を外したな!しょうがない、誰かが制御室に入って橋を戻せ。向こう側へ行かなきゃならんからな!",--Ah! Cops have turned the bridge! All right, one of you get into that control room and turn it back. We need to get on the other side!
pln_pt2_21_01 = "オーケイ、橋が戻り始めた。くそっ、遅えな!サツどもを近づけるなよ!",--Okay, the bridge is turning back. Damn, it's slow! Just hold off the cops!
pln_pt2_21_02 = "よし、橋が戻り始めた。数分はかかりそうだがな。サツどもを寄せ付けるなよ、お前ら!",--All right, bridge is turning back. Gonna take a few minutes though. Hold off the cops, gang!
pln_pt2_21_03 = "よし。いいぞ。橋が戻ってきた。といっても数分はかかりそうだ。死ぬなよ、みんな!",--Right. Okay. Bridge is turning back now. But it'll take a few minutes. Stay alive, gang!
pln_pt2_22_01 = "サツが橋を止めたぞ。装置を操作して動かし続けろ!",--The cops stopped the bridge. Use the controls to keep it turning!
pln_pt2_22_02 = "畜生め!サツどもが橋を停止させたな。誰か、制御室に入って再起動してこい!",--Godammit! Cops halted the bridge. One of you - get in there, restart it!
pln_pt2_22_03 = "ああクソ、サツが橋を止めたな。再起動が必要だ。誰か、やってこい!",--Ah crap, cops stopped turning the bridge. It needs to be restarted. One of you, get on that!
pln_pt2_23_01 = "制御室のボタンを押して橋を戻せ!",--Use the button in the control room to reset the bridge.
