vld_moon_15_03 = "",--Tin Boy's got a snow-white soul! Hahaha!
vld_moon_16_01 = "",--Fuck the other toys - get Tin Boy!
vld_moon_16_02 = "",--Get that Tin Boy with my cocaine!
vld_moon_16_03 = "",--Tin Boy - where aaare you?
vld_moon_17_01 = "ハハハ!10インチ? 俺にピッタリだな、もちろん靴のサイズじゃないぜ...",--10? That's my size! And I don't mean shoes...
vld_moon_17_02 = "",--Get those fucking shoes!
vld_moon_17_03 = "",--What an idiot! Find the shoes!
vld_moon_18_01 = "靴のクソ箱発見までにどんだけかかるんだろうな。",--How hard can it be to find a fucking shoe box?
vld_moon_18_02 = "",--I miss the old Soviet shoes. Not so many stupid models to choose from!
vld_moon_18_03 = "",--Come on, compute with the computer!
vld_moon_19_01 = "",--Alright, it should be in the storage. Drill the fucking door.
vld_moon_19_02 = "",--Drill that door open, find the shoes, get my cocaine!
vld_moon_19_03 = "ドアをぶち破って俺のcokeの靴箱を入手しろ!",--Drill the door open and get my cocaine shoe box!
vld_moon_20_01 = "",--Get those fucking shoes!
vld_moon_20_02 = "",--Get the shoes with my cocaine!
vld_moon_20_03 = "",--Get my cocaine!
vld_moon_21_01 = "",--There are too many fucking boxes here!
vld_moon_21_02 = "",--Where. Are. The. Shoes? Where?!
vld_moon_21_03 = "",--So where are they?!
vld_moon_22_01 = "",--I can't believe this place is so messy.
vld_moon_22_02 = "",--What's in these boxes?
vld_moon_22_03 = "箱だらけじゃねえか! これはTVゲームか何かか?",--Fucking boxes everywhere. It's like that video game...
vld_moon_23_01 = "",--VR? What the fuck is that?
vld_moon_23_02 = "",--VR. Very... enhanced... reality. What bullshit.
vld_moon_23_03 = "コカインにVR...何ともすばらしい響きじゃないか。",--Cocaine and VR - what an interesting mix.
vld_moon_24_01 = "VRはどこに隠しやがった? もしや代替現実ゲームなのか?",--Where did they hide that fucking VR set? In an alternate reality?
vld_moon_24_02 = "",--The VR set is virtually not here. Or should that be actually? I don't know - which is it?
vld_moon_24_03 = "",--VR - Vlad's Rejoicing. That's what this means to me.
vld_moon_25_01 = "",--Ah a safe! How interesting!
vld_moon_25_02 = "",--I'm sure a tiny little safe is not a problem for you.
vld_moon_25_03 = "",--I would have hid it in the safe too. But I'm a cynical man.
vld_moon_26_01 = "",--I love opening Christmas presents!
vld_moon_26_02 = "",--Come on, what are you waiting for?
vld_moon_26_03 = "",--Get the stuff, my friends!
vld_moon_27_01 = "",--I love a good wine with my borscht! Tasty!
vld_moon_27_02 = "",--Get the wine! But don't start drinking - it's enough with one drunk Santa!
vld_moon_27_03 = "",--Wine and cocaine! We could just sell it as a party pack!
vld_moon_28_01 = "",--Get that Red Red Resurrection or whatever it was called!
vld_moon_28_02 = "ワインの輸入業をすべきかもな! ヴラッド·ワイン! いい響きだ。",--Maybe I should start importing wine too! Vlad's Wines! I like the sound of it.
vld_moon_28_03 = "",--Wine, women and song! And cocaine! Merry Christmas!
vld_moon_29_01 = "俺の友Bileがすぐにパーティに来てくれるぜ。歓迎してくれよ。",--Our friend Bile will soon be around for the afterparty. Make sure you welcome him.
vld_moon_29_02 = "",--Watch for the helicopter. We're taking this stuff to the sky.
vld_moon_29_03 = "",--Rescue from above is coming soon, my friends!
vld_moon_30_01 = "",--Now decorate the tree with these fine things!
vld_moon_30_02 = "ツリーを復活させるんだ。雪で...!",--Make the tree come alive, with snow!
vld_moon_30_03 = "",--I want a beautiful Christmas tree with presents in it!
vld_moon_31_01 = "",--Listen my friends... I've been thinking... that's a very nice Christmas tree. I think I'll take it. I will send the helicopter to pick it up.
vld_moon_31_02 = "その木を待っていた! デカいクリスマス·ロケットが宙に浮くぜ! ハハハ!",--I want the tree. It shall fly into the sky like a big Christmas rocket! Hahaha!
vld_moon_31_03 = "",--That tree is very nice. We will steal it.
vld_moon_32_01 = "",--Ladies and gentlemen, can you place some explosives please?
vld_moon_32_02 = "",--Listen...I need you to make me a big bang.
vld_moon_32_03 = "",--I think it would be nice to blow the roof off this mall!
vld_moon_33_01 = "",--Ok, we need to lift this little baby out.
vld_moon_33_02 = "",--This tree is going to fly, my friends!
vld_moon_33_03 = "",--It's a nice tree, and we will take it. Don't damage it!
vld_moon_34_01 = "",--This tree is leaving. So is Santa!
vld_moon_34_02 = "",--Let's make like a tree and leave, my friends!
vld_moon_34_03 = "",--Tree is leaving - get Santa aboard!
vld_moon_35_01 = "",--He'd better hold on tight. It'd be a shame if he fell out of the sky and died.
vld_moon_35_02 = "",--Maybe he'll get lost walking those 2 meters to the tree.
vld_moon_35_03 = "",--I hope he doesn't pass out again at the last moment.
vld_moon_36_01 = "",--Bile will be back soon. Hold on my friends!
vld_moon_36_02 = "",--Maybe do some shopping while you wait?
vld_moon_36_03 = "",--Just wait there, you'll be picked up soon. I promise!
vld_moon_37_01 = "",--And off we go my friends!
vld_moon_37_02 = "",--Merry Christmas! Let's get out of here!
vld_moon_37_03 = "",--This was fun, yes? But it's time to go!
vld_moon_38_01 = "",--Every year around christmas I get a little nostalgic you know. Old times, old enemies.
vld_moon_38_02 = "",--One of my best Christmases was that one time when I killed a dirty snitch on Christmas morning. Tied him to a Christmas tree in front of his family and set him on fire. It was beautiful.
vld_moon_38_03 = "",--I love shopping. I just don't like to pay. Vlad doesn't pay, he takes what he wants.
vld_moon_38_04 = "",--I hope these fucking cops go home and reconsider their actions. They didn't treat Santa very well, so there will be no presents this year.
vld_moon_38_05 = "",--I always do good business around Christmas. People spend a lot of money. It's the stress, they need my stuff.
vld_moon_38_06 = "",--They say you should work with family because you can trust them. But this guy, I can only trust him to be an idiot and to fuck up.
vld_moon_38_07 = "",--My wife said she might go shopping here tomorrow. I should warn her that it'll probably be closed. (laughs)
vld_moon_38_08 = "",--There is something about the sound of shattering shop windows that I find very pleasing. I don't know why.
vld_moon_38_09 = "",--They say always treat others like they treat you. And I've been treated very badly, many times.
vld_moon_38_10 = "",--I bet these cops don't believe in Santa Claus. But I do! And he's a fucking pain in the ass!
vld_moon_39_01 = "",--Hey! Don't destroy the tree!
vld_moon_39_02 = "",--Leave the tree alone! I like it!
vld_moon_39_03 = "",--That's a beautiful tree! Stop it, you barbarians!
vld_moon_39_04 = "破壊したけりゃすればいいし、殺しもいい。だがツリーはダメだ!",--You can destroy anything you want, and kill anyone you want, but leave the tree alone!
vld_moon_39_05 = "",--Don't shoot the tree! You'll ruin Christmas!
vld_moon_39_06 = "",--Hey, I have plans for that tree! Don't destroy it!
vld_moon_39_07 = "",--Not the tree! Stop shooting at it!
vld_moon_39_08 = "",--Don't shoot the tree! It's an endangered species!
vld_moon_39_09 = "",--Don't shoot the Christmas tree!
vld_moon_39_10 = "",--What the fuck did that tree do to you? Huh?
vld_moon_cbf_01 = "",--My brother-in-law, that useless piece of trash, was transporting some snow for me - Colombian snow, you know, for Christmas. But he fucked up and was followed by the cops. He was hiding at the Midtown Mall, but I think the cops got him. Fucking American cops, there's no Christmas spirit in this country! I'm a friendly guy, and Christmas is about forgiving, but this is not ok. Not ok! You have to help me, my friends.
cpt_wwh_01_01 = "よく来てくれた! 二度と生きて出られないと思ってたよ。ほどいてくれないか?",--Well look at this! I thought I was never getting out of here. You untie me please?
cpt_wwh_01_02 = "ああ、神よ。The Butcherが助けを送ってくれました。はやく解いてくれ。",--Ah, good. Butcher has send help. Untie me now please.
cpt_wwh_01_03 = "ナント! ついにThe Butcherの助けが来たか。ほどいてくれ!",--Do pekla! [hell] Finally, Butcher send help. You untie me please!
cpt_wwh_02_01 = "わしが船に戻って指示を出す。",--I get back to ship alone. Will contact you with instructions.
cpt_wwh_02_02 = "船に戻って指示を出すぞ。",--I will go back to boat and contact you with instructions.
cpt_wwh_02_03 = "船に戻ったら指示を出すぞ。",--I contact you with instructions when I am back on ship.
cpt_wwh_03_01 = "もしもし?聞こえるか? 国際水域まで行くには燃料がもっと必要だ。",--Hello? I am coming through? Boat will need more fuel to make international waters.
cpt_wwh_03_02 = "聞こえてるか? 国際水域まで行くのに燃料がもっと必要だ。",--You hear me? We need more fuel for ship to make international waters.
cpt_wwh_03_03 = "よし、わしらは国際水域まで逃げることになるが、燃料が必要だ。",--OK, we need reach international waters with ship, but must have more diesel fuel.
cpt_wwh_04_01 = "燃料の配管ホースと軽油のタンクを探してくれ。",--Look around for hose line and tank of diesel.
cpt_wwh_04_02 = "軽油タンクとホースが埠頭のどこかにある。",--Diesel tank and hose somewhere around dock.
cpt_wwh_04_03 = "燃料タンクとホースをどこかその辺で見つけてくれないか。",--See if you can find fuel tank and hose somewhere near.
cpt_wwh_05_01 = "よし、じゃあホースを燃料ポンプに繋いでくれ。",--Good, now take hose to fuel pump.
cpt_wwh_05_02 = "ああ完璧だ。それじゃあホースをポンプに繋いでくれ。",--Ah, perfect. You now take hose to pump.
cpt_wwh_05_03 = "すぐにホースをポンプに繋いでくれ。",--Hose needs to connect with pump now.
cpt_wwh_06_01 = "ホースを船に繋いでくれ、早く。",--Connect hose to ship, now.
cpt_wwh_06_02 = "ホースを船につなぐんだ。",--Hose needs to connect to ship.
cpt_wwh_06_03 = "ホースを引いて船につないでくれ。",--Bring hose and connect to ship.
cpt_wwh_07_01 = "それじゃあ次はポンプを始動して燃料を送ってくれ。",--So, now start pump to transfer fuel.
cpt_wwh_07_02 = "給油ポンプを始動してくれ。",--Start fuel transfer with pump.
cpt_wwh_07_03 = "ポンプが始動すれば軽油が注がれる。",--Diesel will fill when pump is started.
cpt_wwh_08_01 = "おう、よしよし。燃料が入って来た。",--Ah, good. Fuel is moving.
cpt_wwh_08_02 = "燃料が船に入ってきてるぞ。",--Diesel is now filling in ship.
cpt_wwh_08_03 = "よしきた! 船に燃料が注がれてるぞ。",--There! Fuel is now filling in boat.
cpt_wwh_09_01 = "ポンプが止まったぞ。",--Something wrong with pump.
cpt_wwh_09_02 = "ポンプを調べないと。動いてないぞ。",--You must check pump. Is not working.
cpt_wwh_09_03 = "ポンプが止まった。調べてくれないか。",--Pump has stopped. Please check it-
cpt_wwh_10_01 = "ホースが外れたか。",--Something wrong with hose.
cpt_wwh_10_02 = "ホースが外されたぞ。",--Hose has been disconnected.
cpt_wwh_10_03 = "ホースを繋いでくれ、燃料がこぼれてる!",--You must reconnect hose, is pumping air!
cpt_wwh_11_01 = "全て元通りだ。",--Everything working again.
cpt_wwh_11_02 = "よし、また入り始めたぞ。",--Good, is working again.
cpt_wwh_11_03 = "また軽油が入りはじめたぞ。",--Diesel oil is pumping again.
cpt_wwh_12_01 = "給油は十分だ。",--Pumping is enough.
cpt_wwh_12_02 = "船の燃料が満杯になったぞ、よくやった。",--Fuel tank is full, well done.
cpt_wwh_12_03 = "もう給油は十分だ。",--We have enough diesel now.
cpt_wwh_13_01 = "出航だ! 係留ロープを外してくれ!",--Time to go! Help remove moorings from dock!
cpt_wwh_13_02 = "船を繋いでるロープを外してくれんか!",--Can you please loose ship from dock!
cpt_wwh_13_03 = "次は埠頭とつながってるロープを外してくれ!",--Now we need remove mooring ropes from dock!
cpt_wwh_14_01 = "ロープが繋がったままだ。",--Ropes still connected.
cpt_wwh_14_02 = "ロープが幾つかほどかれてないぞ。",--Some moorings still not removed.
cpt_wwh_14_03 = "全てのロープを解かにゃならん。",--All mooring ropes must be taken off.
cpt_wwh_15_01 = "よし、出発だ! 船に乗れ!",--Now, we go! Get on ship!
cpt_wwh_15_02 = "出発の時だ、友よ! 乗船しろ!",--Is time to leave, comrades! All aboard!
cpt_wwh_15_03 = "皆船に乗ってくれ。すぐに離れるぞ!",--Get on ship everyone. We must leave now!
cpt_wwh_16_01 = "タラップを外して奴らから船を守ってくれ!",--Move gangways and defend ship from attackers!
cpt_wwh_16_02 = "船が攻撃を受けてる。タラップを外して防衛してくれ!",--Ship is being attacked. Defend and remove gangways!
cpt_wwh_16_03 = "タラップを外して船を守ってくれ!",--Gangways must be removed and ship defended.
cpt_wwh_17_01 = "警官が船に残ってる!",--Cops are still on the boat!
cpt_wwh_17_02 = "警官は全て片付けてくれ!",--Get rid of all cops!
cpt_wwh_17_03 = "船上にまだ警官がいるぞ。",--Ship is still attacked by cops onboard.
cpt_wwh_18_01 = "必要な半分の燃料が入った。",--We have half of needed fuel.
cpt_wwh_18_02 = "50パーセントまで入った。",--50 percent full.
cpt_wwh_18_03 = "必要な量の半分まできた。",--Needed diesel is now at half.
cpt_wwh_19_01 = "燃料はあと少しだ。",--Only little more diesel.
cpt_wwh_19_02 = "まだちょっと足りない。",--Not much more.
cpt_wwh_19_03 = "あとほんの少しあればいける。",--Just little fuel to go.
crw_wwh_01_01 = "奴らに船長が捕らわれた! 助け出してくれませんか?",--They locked up the Captain! You get him out please?
crw_wwh_01_02 = "船長は扉の向こうに捕まってるが、SAWなら開けられる。",--The Captain is trapped behind door, you can break with saw.
crw_wwh_01_03 = "SAWがあれば船長を助けられる。彼は扉の向こうにいる。",--You must help free Captain with saw, he is behind door.
pln_wwh_01_01 = "おい、どうなってやがる? Locke、どういうことだ?",--Hey, what the hell is going on? Locke, what are you doing?
pln_wwh_01_02 = "どういうつもりだ、Locke? うちの連中におふざけはしない方がいいぞ。",--Locke, what are you up to? You better not be messing with my crew.
pln_wwh_01_03 = "ふざけるなよLocke、俺の仲間を怒らせるんじゃない。話が違うぞ!",--Damn it Locke, you better not be messing with my crew. We had a contract!
pln_wwh_02_01 = "ワナだ! あの野郎裏切りやがったな。SWATのお出ましだ、突破しろ!",--It's a setup! Damn brak sold us out. Swats incoming. You'll need to fight your way out.
pln_wwh_02_02 = "くそっ、裏切られた。敵が来るぞ、戦闘に備えろ。",--Damn it, we've been double-crossed. You've got incoming, get ready to fight.
pln_wwh_02_03 = "面倒な事になったな、Lockeが俺たちを裏切った。敵を突破しないと逃げられんぞ。",--You're in trouble gang, Locke sold us out. You're going to have to fight your way out of there.
pln_wwh_03_01 = "今はLockeの事は忘れろ、あのクズは後で始末しよう。",--Forget Locke for now, we'll take care of that scumbag later.
pln_wwh_03_02 = "Lockeは逃げたが、後で必ずツケを払わせてやる。",--Locke got away, but we'll have our payback later.
pln_wwh_03_03 = "Lockeが逃げたな、あの裏切り者め、後で必ず捕まえてやろう。約束だ。",--Locke is gone, that backstabber, but we'll get him for this later. Mark my words.
pln_wwh_04_01 = "The Butcherの船がそこの埠頭にある。どうやら彼女も裏切られたようだな。船員たちを助けてやれば乗せてくれるかもしれん。",--The ship by the docks belongs to the Butcher. Looks like she got sold out too. Help them out and maybe they'll give us a ride out.
pln_wwh_04_02 = "その埠頭にあるのはThe Butcherの船だ! Lockeは彼女も裏切ったのか。船員たちを助けて船に乗せてもらえ。",--The ship by the docks belongs to the Butcher! Locke sold her out too. Give them a hand and maybe they'll give you a ride.
pln_wwh_04_03 = "LockeはThe Butcherの事も裏切ったんだな。埠頭に彼女の船の一隻がある。船員たちを助け出せば船に乗れるぞ。",--Locke sold the Butcher out too. The ship by the dock is one of hers. Go help 'em out and maybe we can hitch a boat-ride.
pln_wwh_05_01 = "捕虜を解放しろ。",--You need to free all the hostages.
pln_wwh_05_02 = "船乗り達を解放するんだ。",--Free every sailor you can.
pln_wwh_05_03 = "そのままThe Butcherの手下の解放を続けろ。",--Keep freeing the Butcher's people.
pln_wwh_06_01 = "おい、誰かが助けを呼んでるぞ。向こうの方だ。",--Hey, someone needs help. Get over there.
pln_wwh_06_02 = "向こうに行って乗組員を助けろ。",--Get over there and help the crew.
pln_wwh_06_03 = "お前たちの助けが必要だ、早く向こうへ行け。",--Your help is needed guys, get over there ASAP.
pln_wwh_07_01 = "よし、こいつは役に立つぞ。",--OK, great that saw will come in handy.
pln_wwh_07_02 = "よくやった、そのSAWは必要になる。",--Great guys, you're going to need that saw.
pln_wwh_07_03 = "SAWか?よし、こいつは使える。",--A saw? Good, that's gonna come in handy.
pln_wwh_08_01 = "船長を助けてやるんだ。SAWを扉に設置しろ。",--You should help the Captain, gang. Take that saw and put it to use on the door.
pln_wwh_08_02 = "そのSAWを扉に使って船長を助け出せ!",--Use the saw on that door, get the Captain out!
pln_wwh_08_03 = "船長を助けなきゃならん、扉を切り開け!",--You need to help the Captain, cut the door open!
pln_wwh_09_01 = "そのSAWは信頼性のあるほうじゃなさそうだ、目を離すなよ。",--That saw doesn't seem too realiable, keep an eye on it.
pln_wwh_09_02 = "故障に備えてSAWの側にいろよ。",--Don't get too far away from that saw in case it breaks down.
pln_wwh_09_03 = "SAWの作業が終わるまで見張ってろよ。",--Keep an eye on that saw until it's done.
pln_wwh_10_01 = "くそ、SAWを再起動させろ!",--Damn, get the saw going again.
pln_wwh_10_02 = "SAWが止まったぞ。",--The saw stopped running.
pln_wwh_10_03 = "サツどもがSAWを止めやがった。できるだけ早く再起動させるんだ。",--The cops got to the Saw. Restart it ASAP.
pln_wwh_11_01 = "よし良いぞ。今度は止めさせるな。",--OK, good. Keep it running this time.
pln_wwh_11_02 = "サツ共を近づけて止めさせるなよ。",--Keep the cops away so it doesn't stop cutting.
pln_wwh_11_03 = "またSAWがいるのか?上等だ。",--Sawing again? Great.
pln_wwh_12_01 = "切断できたようだぞ。扉を開け!",--I heard the blade cut through. Get that door open!
pln_wwh_12_02 = "よし、扉を開けろ!",--OK, now open that door!
pln_wwh_12_03 = "SAWが終わったな、中に入れ!",--The saw is finished, get through that door!
pln_wwh_13_01 = "あの船が唯一の脱出手段だから、船長の言うことは何でも聞け。",--That boat is your only way out of there, so do whatever the Captain needs.
pln_wwh_13_02 = "脱出したいなら船長の言うことを聞け。",--You'll have to help the Captain if you want to get out of there.
pln_wwh_13_03 = "船長の要求は何でも聞くんだぞ。今の俺じゃお前たちを逃がしてやれないから、暖かい本土に戻るためのチケットを持つのは彼だけだ。",--Do whatever the Captain asks guys. I can't get you out any other way right now, so he's your only ticket back to warm weather.
pln_wwh_brf_01 = "船長の要求は何でも聞くんだぞ。今の俺にお前たちを逃がしてやる手は無いから、暖かい本土に戻るためのチケットを持ってるのは彼だけだ。",--Locke has asked for help guarding a weapons transaction in Alaska. Says he's not expecting trouble, but want some reliable security just in case. Looks like it might be an easy Payday if you can put up with the cold.
pln_wwh_end_01 = "楽な仕事のはずが、とんだ災難だったな。Lockeの事は任せとけ、必ず探し出してやる。",--Now there's a plan that went straight to hell. Don't worry about Locke, I'll find out where he went.
pln_wwh_end_02 = "もっとマシな一日になるはずだったんだがな。ともかくLockeにはいずれ必ずツケを払わせてやる。奴は逃げ切れんよ、俺たちと違ってな。",--Today could've been better, guys. But we'll have to deal with Locke eventually. He'll be running from more people than us.
pln_wwh_end_03 = "あの状況でよく頑張ったな。俺はこれから電話して...Lockeの野郎に何があったか調べるとしよう。",--That went as well as it could under the circumstances. I'll make some calls... find out what really happened to Locke.
bos_fri_01_01 = "おい! そいつは貴重な絵だぞ!",--Hey! That's priceless art!
bos_fri_01_02 = "俺の絵に何するつもりだ?!",--What are you doing to my paintings?!
